36 static bool isDeclWithinFunction(const Decl *D) {
37  const DeclContext *DC = D->getDeclContext();
38  if (DC->isFunctionOrMethod())
39  return true;
40 
41  if (DC->isRecord())
42  return cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DC)->isLocalClass();
43 
44  return false;
45 }
46 
47 template<typename DeclT>
48 static bool SubstQualifier(Sema &SemaRef, const DeclT *OldDecl, DeclT *NewDecl,
49  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs) {
50  if (!OldDecl->getQualifierLoc())
51  return false;
52 
53  assert((NewDecl->getFriendObjectKind() ||
54  !OldDecl->getLexicalDeclContext()->isDependentContext()) &&
55  "non-friend with qualified name defined in dependent context");
56  Sema::ContextRAII SavedContext(
57  SemaRef,
58  const_cast<DeclContext *>(NewDecl->getFriendObjectKind()
59  ? NewDecl->getLexicalDeclContext()
60  : OldDecl->getLexicalDeclContext()));
61 
62  NestedNameSpecifierLoc NewQualifierLoc
63  = SemaRef.SubstNestedNameSpecifierLoc(OldDecl->getQualifierLoc(),
64  TemplateArgs);
65 
66  if (!NewQualifierLoc)
67  return true;
68 
69  NewDecl->setQualifierInfo(NewQualifierLoc);
70  return false;
71 }
72 
73 bool TemplateDeclInstantiator::SubstQualifier(const DeclaratorDecl *OldDecl,
74  DeclaratorDecl *NewDecl) {
75  return ::SubstQualifier(SemaRef, OldDecl, NewDecl, TemplateArgs);
76 }

78 bool TemplateDeclInstantiator::SubstQualifier(const TagDecl *OldDecl,
79  TagDecl *NewDecl) {
80  return ::SubstQualifier(SemaRef, OldDecl, NewDecl, TemplateArgs);

86 static void instantiateDependentAlignedAttr(
87  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
88  const AlignedAttr *Aligned, Decl *New, bool IsPackExpansion) {
89  if (Aligned->isAlignmentExpr()) {
90  // The alignment expression is a constant expression.
91  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
92  S, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
93  ExprResult Result = S.SubstExpr(Aligned->getAlignmentExpr(), TemplateArgs);
94  if (!Result.isInvalid())
95  S.AddAlignedAttr(New, *Aligned, Result.getAs<Expr>(), IsPackExpansion);
96  } else {
97  TypeSourceInfo *Result = S.SubstType(Aligned->getAlignmentType(),
98  TemplateArgs, Aligned->getLocation(),
99  DeclarationName());
100  if (Result)
101  S.AddAlignedAttr(New, *Aligned, Result, IsPackExpansion);
102  }
103 }
104 
105 static void instantiateDependentAlignedAttr(
106  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
107  const AlignedAttr *Aligned, Decl *New) {
108  if (!Aligned->isPackExpansion()) {
109  instantiateDependentAlignedAttr(S, TemplateArgs, Aligned, New, false);
110  return;
111  }
112 
113  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
114  if (Aligned->isAlignmentExpr())
115  S.collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(Aligned->getAlignmentExpr(),
116  Unexpanded);
117  else
118  S.collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(Aligned->getAlignmentType()->getTypeLoc(),
119  Unexpanded);
120  assert(!Unexpanded.empty() && "Pack expansion without parameter packs?");
121 
122  // Determine whether we can expand this attribute pack yet.
123  bool Expand = true, RetainExpansion = false;
124  Optional<unsigned> NumExpansions;
125  // FIXME: Use the actual location of the ellipsis.
126  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc = Aligned->getLocation();
127  if (S.CheckParameterPacksForExpansion(EllipsisLoc, Aligned->getRange(),
128  Unexpanded, TemplateArgs, Expand,
129  RetainExpansion, NumExpansions))
130  return;
131 
132  if (!Expand) {
133  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(S, -1);
134  instantiateDependentAlignedAttr(S, TemplateArgs, Aligned, New, true);
135  } else {
136  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
137  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(S, I);
138  instantiateDependentAlignedAttr(S, TemplateArgs, Aligned, New, false);
139  }
140  }
141 }
142 
143 static void instantiateDependentAssumeAlignedAttr(
144  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
145  const AssumeAlignedAttr *Aligned, Decl *New) {
146  // The alignment expression is a constant expression.
147  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
148  S, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
149 
150  Expr *E, *OE = nullptr;
151  ExprResult Result = S.SubstExpr(Aligned->getAlignment(), TemplateArgs);
152  if (Result.isInvalid())
153  return;
154  E = Result.getAs<Expr>();
155 
156  if (Aligned->getOffset()) {
157  Result = S.SubstExpr(Aligned->getOffset(), TemplateArgs);
158  if (Result.isInvalid())
159  return;
160  OE = Result.getAs<Expr>();
161  }
162 
163  S.AddAssumeAlignedAttr(New, *Aligned, E, OE);
164 }

172  ExprResult Result = S.SubstExpr(Aligned->getAlignment(), TemplateArgs);
173  if (!Result.isInvalid())

177 static void instantiateDependentAllocAlignAttr(
178  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
179  const AllocAlignAttr *Align, Decl *New) {

183  S.getASTContext().UnsignedLongLongTy, Align->getLocation());

187 static void instantiateDependentAnnotationAttr(
188  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
189  const AnnotateAttr *Attr, Decl *New) {
190  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
191  S, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
192 
193  // If the attribute has delayed arguments it will have to instantiate those
194  // and handle them as new arguments for the attribute.
195  bool HasDelayedArgs = Attr->delayedArgs_size();
196 
197  ArrayRef<Expr *> ArgsToInstantiate =
198  HasDelayedArgs
199  ? ArrayRef<Expr *>{Attr->delayedArgs_begin(), Attr->delayedArgs_end()}
200  : ArrayRef<Expr *>{Attr->args_begin(), Attr->args_end()};
201 
202  SmallVector<Expr *, 4> Args;
203  if (S.SubstExprs(ArgsToInstantiate,
204  /*IsCall=*/false, TemplateArgs, Args))
205  return;
206 
207  StringRef Str = Attr->getAnnotation();
208  if (HasDelayedArgs) {
209  if (Args.size() < 1) {
210  S.Diag(Attr->getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_too_few_arguments)
211  << Attr << 1;
212  return;
213  }
214 
215  if (!S.checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(*Attr, Args[0], Str))
216  return;
217 
218  llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 4> ActualArgs;
219  ActualArgs.insert(ActualArgs.begin(), Args.begin() + 1, Args.end());
220  std::swap(Args, ActualArgs);
221  }
222  S.AddAnnotationAttr(New, *Attr, Str, Args);
223 }
224 
225 static Expr *instantiateDependentFunctionAttrCondition(
226  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
227  const Attr *A, Expr *OldCond, const Decl *Tmpl, FunctionDecl *New) {
228  Expr *Cond = nullptr;
229  {
230  Sema::ContextRAII SwitchContext(S, New);
231  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
232  S, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
233  ExprResult Result = S.SubstExpr(OldCond, TemplateArgs);
234  if (Result.isInvalid())
235  return nullptr;
236  Cond = Result.getAs<Expr>();
237  }
238  if (!Cond->isTypeDependent()) {
239  ExprResult Converted = S.PerformContextuallyConvertToBool(Cond);
240  if (Converted.isInvalid())
241  return nullptr;
242  Cond = Converted.get();
243  }
244 
245  SmallVector<PartialDiagnosticAt, 8> Diags;
246  if (OldCond->isValueDependent() && !Cond->isValueDependent() &&
247  !Expr::isPotentialConstantExprUnevaluated(Cond, New, Diags)) {
248  S.Diag(A->getLocation(), diag::err_attr_cond_never_constant_expr) << A;
249  for (const auto &P : Diags)
250  S.Diag(P.first, P.second);
251  return nullptr;
252  }
253  return Cond;
254 }

256 static void instantiateDependentEnableIfAttr(
257  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
258  const EnableIfAttr *EIA, const Decl *Tmpl, FunctionDecl *New) {
259  Expr *Cond = instantiateDependentFunctionAttrCondition(
260  S, TemplateArgs, EIA, EIA->getCond(), Tmpl, New);
261 
262  if (Cond)
263  New->addAttr(new (S.getASTContext()) EnableIfAttr(S.getASTContext(), *EIA,
264  Cond, EIA->getMessage()));
265 }
266 
267 static void instantiateDependentDiagnoseIfAttr(
268  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
269  const DiagnoseIfAttr *DIA, const Decl *Tmpl, FunctionDecl *New) {
270  Expr *Cond = instantiateDependentFunctionAttrCondition(
271  S, TemplateArgs, DIA, DIA->getCond(), Tmpl, New);
272 
273  if (Cond)
274  New->addAttr(new (S.getASTContext()) DiagnoseIfAttr(
275  S.getASTContext(), *DIA, Cond, DIA->getMessage(),
276  DIA->getDiagnosticType(), DIA->getArgDependent(), New));
277 }

279 // Constructs and adds to New a new instance of CUDALaunchBoundsAttr using
280 // template A as the base and arguments from TemplateArgs.
281 static void instantiateDependentCUDALaunchBoundsAttr(
282  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
283  const CUDALaunchBoundsAttr &Attr, Decl *New) {
284  // The alignment expression is a constant expression.
285  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
286  S, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
287 
288  ExprResult Result = S.SubstExpr(Attr.getMaxThreads(), TemplateArgs);
289  if (Result.isInvalid())
290  return;
291  Expr *MaxThreads = Result.getAs<Expr>();
292 
293  Expr *MinBlocks = nullptr;
294  if (Attr.getMinBlocks()) {
295  Result = S.SubstExpr(Attr.getMinBlocks(), TemplateArgs);
296  if (Result.isInvalid())
297  return;
298  MinBlocks = Result.getAs<Expr>();
299  }
300 
301  S.AddLaunchBoundsAttr(New, Attr, MaxThreads, MinBlocks);
302 }

305 instantiateDependentModeAttr(Sema &S,

312 /// Instantiation of 'declare simd' attribute and its arguments.
313 static void instantiateOMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr(
314  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
315  const OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr &Attr, Decl *New) {
316  // Allow 'this' in clauses with varlists.
317  if (auto *FTD = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(New))
318  New = FTD->getTemplatedDecl();
319  auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(New);
320  auto *ThisContext = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(FD->getDeclContext());
321  SmallVector<Expr *, 4> Uniforms, Aligneds, Alignments, Linears, Steps;
322  SmallVector<unsigned, 4> LinModifiers;
323 
324  auto SubstExpr = [&](Expr *E) -> ExprResult {
325  if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E->IgnoreParenImpCasts()))
326  if (auto *PVD = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(DRE->getDecl())) {
327  Sema::ContextRAII SavedContext(S, FD);
328  LocalInstantiationScope Local(S);
329  if (FD->getNumParams() > PVD->getFunctionScopeIndex())
330  Local.InstantiatedLocal(
331  PVD, FD->getParamDecl(PVD->getFunctionScopeIndex()));
332  return S.SubstExpr(E, TemplateArgs);
333  }
334  Sema::CXXThisScopeRAII ThisScope(S, ThisContext, Qualifiers(),
335  FD->isCXXInstanceMember());
336  return S.SubstExpr(E, TemplateArgs);
337  };
338 
339  // Substitute a single OpenMP clause, which is a potentially-evaluated
340  // full-expression.
341  auto Subst = [&](Expr *E) -> ExprResult {
342  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Evaluated(
343  S, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated);
344  ExprResult Res = SubstExpr(E);
345  if (Res.isInvalid())
346  return Res;
347  return S.ActOnFinishFullExpr(Res.get(), false);
348  };
349 
350  ExprResult Simdlen;
351  if (auto *E = Attr.getSimdlen())
352  Simdlen = Subst(E);
353 
354  if (Attr.uniforms_size() > 0) {
355  for(auto *E : Attr.uniforms()) {
356  ExprResult Inst = Subst(E);
357  if (Inst.isInvalid())
358  continue;
359  Uniforms.push_back(Inst.get());
360  }
361  }
362 
363  auto AI = Attr.alignments_begin();
364  for (auto *E : Attr.aligneds()) {
365  ExprResult Inst = Subst(E);
366  if (Inst.isInvalid())
367  continue;
368  Aligneds.push_back(Inst.get());
369  Inst = ExprEmpty();
370  if (*AI)
371  Inst = S.SubstExpr(*AI, TemplateArgs);
372  Alignments.push_back(Inst.get());
373  ++AI;
374  }
375 
376  auto SI = Attr.steps_begin();
377  for (auto *E : Attr.linears()) {
378  ExprResult Inst = Subst(E);
379  if (Inst.isInvalid())
380  continue;
381  Linears.push_back(Inst.get());
382  Inst = ExprEmpty();
383  if (*SI)
384  Inst = S.SubstExpr(*SI, TemplateArgs);
385  Steps.push_back(Inst.get());
386  ++SI;
387  }
388  LinModifiers.append(Attr.modifiers_begin(), Attr.modifiers_end());
389  (void)S.ActOnOpenMPDeclareSimdDirective(
390  S.ConvertDeclToDeclGroup(New), Attr.getBranchState(), Simdlen.get(),
391  Uniforms, Aligneds, Alignments, Linears, LinModifiers, Steps,
392  Attr.getRange());
393 }
394 
395 /// Instantiation of 'declare variant' attribute and its arguments.
396 static void instantiateOMPDeclareVariantAttr(
397  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
398  const OMPDeclareVariantAttr &Attr, Decl *New) {
399  // Allow 'this' in clauses with varlists.
400  if (auto *FTD = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(New))
401  New = FTD->getTemplatedDecl();
402  auto *FD = cast<FunctionDecl>(New);
403  auto *ThisContext = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(FD->getDeclContext());
404 
405  auto &&SubstExpr = [FD, ThisContext, &S, &TemplateArgs](Expr *E) {
406  if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E->IgnoreParenImpCasts()))
407  if (auto *PVD = dyn_cast<ParmVarDecl>(DRE->getDecl())) {
408  Sema::ContextRAII SavedContext(S, FD);
409  LocalInstantiationScope Local(S);
410  if (FD->getNumParams() > PVD->getFunctionScopeIndex())
411  Local.InstantiatedLocal(
412  PVD, FD->getParamDecl(PVD->getFunctionScopeIndex()));
413  return S.SubstExpr(E, TemplateArgs);
414  }
415  Sema::CXXThisScopeRAII ThisScope(S, ThisContext, Qualifiers(),
416  FD->isCXXInstanceMember());
417  return S.SubstExpr(E, TemplateArgs);
418  };
419 
420  // Substitute a single OpenMP clause, which is a potentially-evaluated
421  // full-expression.
422  auto &&Subst = [&SubstExpr, &S](Expr *E) {
423  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Evaluated(
424  S, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated);
425  ExprResult Res = SubstExpr(E);
426  if (Res.isInvalid())
427  return Res;
428  return S.ActOnFinishFullExpr(Res.get(), false);
429  };
430 
431  ExprResult VariantFuncRef;
432  if (Expr *E = Attr.getVariantFuncRef()) {
433  // Do not mark function as is used to prevent its emission if this is the
434  // only place where it is used.
435  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
436  S, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
437  VariantFuncRef = Subst(E);
438  }
439 
440  // Copy the template version of the OMPTraitInfo and run substitute on all
441  // score and condition expressiosn.
442  OMPTraitInfo &TI = S.getASTContext().getNewOMPTraitInfo();
443  TI = *Attr.getTraitInfos();
444 
445  // Try to substitute template parameters in score and condition expressions.
446  auto SubstScoreOrConditionExpr = [&S, Subst](Expr *&E, bool) {
447  if (E) {
448  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
449  S, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
450  ExprResult ER = Subst(E);
451  if (ER.isUsable())
452  E = ER.get();
453  else
454  return true;
455  }
456  return false;
457  };
458  if (TI.anyScoreOrCondition(SubstScoreOrConditionExpr))
459  return;
460 
461  Expr *E = VariantFuncRef.get();
462 
463  // Check function/variant ref for `omp declare variant` but not for `omp
464  // begin declare variant` (which use implicit attributes).
465  Optional<std::pair<FunctionDecl *, Expr *>> DeclVarData =
466  S.checkOpenMPDeclareVariantFunction(S.ConvertDeclToDeclGroup(New), E, TI,
467  Attr.appendArgs_size(),
468  Attr.getRange());
469 
470  if (!DeclVarData)
471  return;
472 
473  E = DeclVarData.getValue().second;
474  FD = DeclVarData.getValue().first;
475 
476  if (auto *VariantDRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E->IgnoreParenImpCasts())) {
477  if (auto *VariantFD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(VariantDRE->getDecl())) {
478  if (auto *VariantFTD = VariantFD->getDescribedFunctionTemplate()) {
479  if (!VariantFTD->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
480  return;
481  Sema::TentativeAnalysisScope Trap(S);
482  const TemplateArgumentList *TAL = TemplateArgumentList::CreateCopy(
483  S.Context, TemplateArgs.getInnermost());
484 
485  auto *SubstFD = S.InstantiateFunctionDeclaration(VariantFTD, TAL,
486  New->getLocation());
487  if (!SubstFD)
488  return;
489  QualType NewType = S.Context.mergeFunctionTypes(
490  SubstFD->getType(), FD->getType(),
491  /* OfBlockPointer */ false,
492  /* Unqualified */ false, /* AllowCXX */ true);
493  if (NewType.isNull())
494  return;
495  S.InstantiateFunctionDefinition(
496  New->getLocation(), SubstFD, /* Recursive */ true,
497  /* DefinitionRequired */ false, /* AtEndOfTU */ false);
498  SubstFD->setInstantiationIsPending(!SubstFD->isDefined());
499  E = DeclRefExpr::Create(S.Context, NestedNameSpecifierLoc(),
500  SourceLocation(), SubstFD,
501  /* RefersToEnclosingVariableOrCapture */ false,
502  /* NameLoc */ SubstFD->getLocation(),
503  SubstFD->getType(), ExprValueKind::VK_PRValue);
504  }
505  }
506  }
507 
508  SmallVector<Expr *, 8> NothingExprs;
509  SmallVector<Expr *, 8> NeedDevicePtrExprs;
510  SmallVector<OMPDeclareVariantAttr::InteropType, 8> AppendArgs;
511 
512  for (Expr *E : Attr.adjustArgsNothing()) {
513  ExprResult ER = Subst(E);
514  if (ER.isInvalid())
515  continue;
516  NothingExprs.push_back(ER.get());
517  }
518  for (Expr *E : Attr.adjustArgsNeedDevicePtr()) {
519  ExprResult ER = Subst(E);
520  if (ER.isInvalid())
521  continue;
522  NeedDevicePtrExprs.push_back(ER.get());
523  }
524  llvm::append_range(AppendArgs, Attr.appendArgs());
525 
526  S.ActOnOpenMPDeclareVariantDirective(
527  FD, E, TI, NothingExprs, NeedDevicePtrExprs, AppendArgs, SourceLocation(),
528  SourceLocation(), Attr.getRange());
529 }

531 static void instantiateDependentAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr(
532  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
533  const AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr &Attr, Decl *New) {
534  // Both min and max expression are constant expressions.
535  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
536  S, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
537 
538  ExprResult Result = S.SubstExpr(Attr.getMin(), TemplateArgs);
539  if (Result.isInvalid())
540  return;
541  Expr *MinExpr = Result.getAs<Expr>();
542 
543  Result = S.SubstExpr(Attr.getMax(), TemplateArgs);
544  if (Result.isInvalid())
545  return;
546  Expr *MaxExpr = Result.getAs<Expr>();
547 
548  S.addAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr(New, Attr, MinExpr, MaxExpr);
549 }
550 
551 static ExplicitSpecifier
552 instantiateExplicitSpecifier(Sema &S,
553  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
554  ExplicitSpecifier ES, FunctionDecl *New) {
555  if (!ES.getExpr())
556  return ES;
557  Expr *OldCond = ES.getExpr();
558  Expr *Cond = nullptr;
559  {
560  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
561  S, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
562  ExprResult SubstResult = S.SubstExpr(OldCond, TemplateArgs);
563  if (SubstResult.isInvalid()) {
564  return ExplicitSpecifier::Invalid();
565  }
566  Cond = SubstResult.get();
567  }
568  ExplicitSpecifier Result(Cond, ES.getKind());
569  if (!Cond->isTypeDependent())
570  S.tryResolveExplicitSpecifier(Result);
571  return Result;
572 }

574 static void instantiateDependentAMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr(
575  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
576  const AMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr &Attr, Decl *New) {
577  // Both min and max expression are constant expressions.
578  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
579  S, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
580 
581  ExprResult Result = S.SubstExpr(Attr.getMin(), TemplateArgs);
582  if (Result.isInvalid())
583  return;
584  Expr *MinExpr = Result.getAs<Expr>();
585 
586  Expr *MaxExpr = nullptr;
587  if (auto Max = Attr.getMax()) {
588  Result = S.SubstExpr(Max, TemplateArgs);
589  if (Result.isInvalid())
590  return;
591  MaxExpr = Result.getAs<Expr>();
592  }
593 
594  S.addAMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr(New, Attr, MinExpr, MaxExpr);
595 }

607 static void instantiateIntelFPGABankWidthAttr(
608  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
609  const IntelFPGABankWidthAttr *Attr, Decl *New) {

614  S.AddIntelFPGABankWidthAttr(New, *Attr, Result.getAs<Expr>());

832  const WorkGroupSizeHintAttr *A, Decl *New) {

839  if (YResult.isInvalid())

846  ZResult.get());

887 // This doesn't take any template parameters, but we have a custom action that
888 // needs to happen when the kernel itself is instantiated. We need to run the
889 // ItaniumMangler to mark the names required to name this kernel.
890 static void instantiateDependentSYCLKernelAttr(
891  Sema &S, const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
892  const SYCLKernelAttr &Attr, Decl *New) {
893  New->addAttr(Attr.clone(S.getASTContext()));
894 }
895 
896 /// Determine whether the attribute A might be relevant to the declaration D.
897 /// If not, we can skip instantiating it. The attribute may or may not have
898 /// been instantiated yet.
899 static bool isRelevantAttr(Sema &S, const Decl *D, const Attr *A) {
900  // 'preferred_name' is only relevant to the matching specialization of the
901  // template.
902  if (const auto *PNA = dyn_cast<PreferredNameAttr>(A)) {
903  QualType T = PNA->getTypedefType();
904  const auto *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D);
905  if (!T->isDependentType() && !RD->isDependentContext() &&
906  !declaresSameEntity(T->getAsCXXRecordDecl(), RD))
907  return false;
908  for (const auto *ExistingPNA : D->specific_attrs<PreferredNameAttr>())
909  if (S.Context.hasSameType(ExistingPNA->getTypedefType(),
910  PNA->getTypedefType()))
911  return false;
912  return true;
913  }
914 
915  return true;
916 }
917 
918 void Sema::InstantiateAttrsForDecl(
919  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs, const Decl *Tmpl,
920  Decl *New, LateInstantiatedAttrVec *LateAttrs,
921  LocalInstantiationScope *OuterMostScope) {
922  if (NamedDecl *ND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(New)) {
923  // FIXME: This function is called multiple times for the same template
924  // specialization. We should only instantiate attributes that were added
925  // since the previous instantiation.
926  for (const auto *TmplAttr : Tmpl->attrs()) {
927  if (!isRelevantAttr(*this, New, TmplAttr))
928  continue;
929 
930  // FIXME: If any of the special case versions from InstantiateAttrs become
931  // applicable to template declaration, we'll need to add them here.
932  CXXThisScopeRAII ThisScope(
933  *this, dyn_cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(ND->getDeclContext()),
934  Qualifiers(), ND->isCXXInstanceMember());
935 
936  Attr *NewAttr = sema::instantiateTemplateAttributeForDecl(
937  TmplAttr, Context, *this, TemplateArgs);
938  if (NewAttr && isRelevantAttr(*this, New, NewAttr))
939  New->addAttr(NewAttr);
940  }
941  }
942 }
943 
944 static Sema::RetainOwnershipKind
945 attrToRetainOwnershipKind(const Attr *A) {
946  switch (A->getKind()) {
947  case clang::attr::CFConsumed:
948  return Sema::RetainOwnershipKind::CF;
949  case clang::attr::OSConsumed:
950  return Sema::RetainOwnershipKind::OS;
951  case clang::attr::NSConsumed:
952  return Sema::RetainOwnershipKind::NS;
953  default:
954  llvm_unreachable("Wrong argument supplied");
955  }
956 }
957 
958 void Sema::InstantiateAttrs(const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
959  const Decl *Tmpl, Decl *New,
960  LateInstantiatedAttrVec *LateAttrs,
961  LocalInstantiationScope *OuterMostScope) {
962  for (const auto *TmplAttr : Tmpl->attrs()) {
963  if (!isRelevantAttr(*this, New, TmplAttr))
964  continue;
965 
966  // FIXME: This should be generalized to more than just the AlignedAttr.
967  const AlignedAttr *Aligned = dyn_cast<AlignedAttr>(TmplAttr);
968  if (Aligned && Aligned->isAlignmentDependent()) {
969  instantiateDependentAlignedAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, Aligned, New);
970  continue;
971  }
972 
973  if (const auto *AssumeAligned = dyn_cast<AssumeAlignedAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
974  instantiateDependentAssumeAlignedAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, AssumeAligned, New);
975  continue;
976  }
977 
978  if (const auto *AlignValue = dyn_cast<AlignValueAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
979  instantiateDependentAlignValueAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, AlignValue, New);
980  continue;
981  }
982 
983  if (const auto *AllocAlign = dyn_cast<AllocAlignAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
984  instantiateDependentAllocAlignAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, AllocAlign, New);
985  continue;
986  }
987 
988  if (const auto *Annotate = dyn_cast<AnnotateAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
989  instantiateDependentAnnotationAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, Annotate, New);
990  continue;
991  }
992 
993  if (const auto *EnableIf = dyn_cast<EnableIfAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
994  instantiateDependentEnableIfAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, EnableIf, Tmpl,
995  cast<FunctionDecl>(New));
996  continue;
997  }
998 
999  if (const auto *DiagnoseIf = dyn_cast<DiagnoseIfAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1000  instantiateDependentDiagnoseIfAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, DiagnoseIf, Tmpl,
1001  cast<FunctionDecl>(New));
1002  continue;
1003  }
1004 
1005  if (const auto *CUDALaunchBounds =
1006  dyn_cast<CUDALaunchBoundsAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1007  instantiateDependentCUDALaunchBoundsAttr(*this, TemplateArgs,
1008  *CUDALaunchBounds, New);
1009  continue;
1010  }
1011 
1012  if (const auto *Mode = dyn_cast<ModeAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1013  instantiateDependentModeAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, *Mode, New);
1014  continue;
1015  }
1016 
1017  if (const auto *OMPAttr = dyn_cast<OMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1018  instantiateOMPDeclareSimdDeclAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, *OMPAttr, New);
1019  continue;
1020  }
1021 
1022  if (const auto *OMPAttr = dyn_cast<OMPDeclareVariantAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1023  instantiateOMPDeclareVariantAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, *OMPAttr, New);
1024  continue;
1025  }
1026 
1027  if (const auto *AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSize =
1028  dyn_cast<AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1029  instantiateDependentAMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSizeAttr(
1030  *this, TemplateArgs, *AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSize, New);
1031  }
1032 
1033  if (const auto *AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSize =
1034  dyn_cast<AMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1035  instantiateDependentAMDGPUWavesPerEUAttr(*this, TemplateArgs,
1036  *AMDGPUFlatWorkGroupSize, New);
1037  }
1038 
1039  if (const auto *IntelFPGABankWidth =
1040  dyn_cast<IntelFPGABankWidthAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1041  instantiateIntelFPGABankWidthAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, IntelFPGABankWidth,
1042  New);
1043  }
1044 
1045  if (const auto *IntelFPGANumBanks =
1046  dyn_cast<IntelFPGANumBanksAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1047  instantiateIntelFPGANumBanksAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, IntelFPGANumBanks,
1048  New);
1049  }
1050  if (const auto *IntelFPGAPrivateCopies =
1051  dyn_cast<IntelFPGAPrivateCopiesAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1052  instantiateIntelFPGAPrivateCopiesAttr(*this, TemplateArgs,
1053  IntelFPGAPrivateCopies, New);
1054  }
1055  if (const auto *IntelFPGAMaxReplicates =
1056  dyn_cast<IntelFPGAMaxReplicatesAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1057  instantiateIntelFPGAMaxReplicatesAttr(*this, TemplateArgs,
1058  IntelFPGAMaxReplicates, New);
1059  }
1060  if (const auto *IntelFPGABankBits =
1061  dyn_cast<IntelFPGABankBitsAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1062  instantiateIntelFPGABankBitsAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, IntelFPGABankBits,
1063  New);
1064  }
1065  if (const auto *IntelFPGAForcePow2Depth =
1066  dyn_cast<IntelFPGAForcePow2DepthAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1067  instantiateIntelFPGAForcePow2DepthAttr(*this, TemplateArgs,
1068  IntelFPGAForcePow2Depth, New);
1069  }
1070  if (const auto *SYCLIntelPipeIO = dyn_cast<SYCLIntelPipeIOAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1071  instantiateSYCLIntelPipeIOAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, SYCLIntelPipeIO, New);
1072  continue;
1073  }
1074  if (const auto *IntelReqdSubGroupSize =
1075  dyn_cast<IntelReqdSubGroupSizeAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1076  instantiateIntelReqdSubGroupSize(*this, TemplateArgs,
1077  IntelReqdSubGroupSize, New);
1078  continue;
1079  }
1080  if (const auto *SYCLIntelNumSimdWorkItems =
1081  dyn_cast<SYCLIntelNumSimdWorkItemsAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1082  instantiateSYCLIntelNumSimdWorkItemsAttr(*this, TemplateArgs,
1083  SYCLIntelNumSimdWorkItems, New);
1084  continue;
1085  }
1086  if (const auto *SYCLIntelSchedulerTargetFmaxMhz =
1087  dyn_cast<SYCLIntelSchedulerTargetFmaxMhzAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1088  instantiateSYCLIntelSchedulerTargetFmaxMhzAttr(
1089  *this, TemplateArgs, SYCLIntelSchedulerTargetFmaxMhz, New);
1090  continue;
1091  }
1092  if (const auto *SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDim =
1093  dyn_cast<SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1094  instantiateSYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDimAttr(*this, TemplateArgs,
1095  SYCLIntelMaxGlobalWorkDim, New);
1096  continue;
1097  }
1098  if (const auto *SYCLIntelLoopFuse =
1099  dyn_cast<SYCLIntelLoopFuseAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1100  instantiateSYCLIntelLoopFuseAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, SYCLIntelLoopFuse,
1101  New);
1102  continue;
1103  }
1104  if (const auto *SYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffset =
1105  dyn_cast<SYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffsetAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1106  instantiateSYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffsetAttr(
1107  *this, TemplateArgs, SYCLIntelNoGlobalWorkOffset, New);
1108  continue;
1109  }
1110  if (const auto *ReqdWorkGroupSize =
1111  dyn_cast<ReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1112  instantiateReqdWorkGroupSizeAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, ReqdWorkGroupSize,
1113  New);
1114  continue;
1115  }
1116  if (const auto *SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSize =
1117  dyn_cast<SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1118  instantiateSYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSizeAttr(*this, TemplateArgs,
1119  SYCLIntelMaxWorkGroupSize, New);
1120  continue;
1121  }
1122  if (const auto *SYCLIntelMaxConcurrency =
1123  dyn_cast<SYCLIntelFPGAMaxConcurrencyAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1124  instantiateSYCLIntelFPGAMaxConcurrencyAttr(*this, TemplateArgs,
1125  SYCLIntelMaxConcurrency, New);
1126  }
1127  if (const auto *SYCLIntelFPGAInitiationInterval =
1128  dyn_cast<SYCLIntelFPGAInitiationIntervalAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1129  instantiateSYCLIntelFPGAInitiationIntervalAttr(
1130  *this, TemplateArgs, SYCLIntelFPGAInitiationInterval, New);
1131  continue;
1132  }
1133  if (const auto *SYCLIntelESimdVectorize =
1134  dyn_cast<SYCLIntelESimdVectorizeAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1135  instantiateSYCLIntelESimdVectorizeAttr(*this, TemplateArgs,
1136  SYCLIntelESimdVectorize, New);
1137  continue;
1138  }
1139  if (const auto *SYCLAddIRAttributesFunction =
1140  dyn_cast<SYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1141  instantiateSYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr(
1142  *this, TemplateArgs, SYCLAddIRAttributesFunction, New);
1143  continue;
1144  }
1145  if (const auto *SYCLAddIRAttributesKernelParameter =
1146  dyn_cast<SYCLAddIRAttributesKernelParameterAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1147  instantiateSYCLAddIRAttributesKernelParameterAttr(
1148  *this, TemplateArgs, SYCLAddIRAttributesKernelParameter, New);
1149  continue;
1150  }
1151  if (const auto *SYCLAddIRAttributesGlobalVariable =
1152  dyn_cast<SYCLAddIRAttributesGlobalVariableAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1153  instantiateSYCLAddIRAttributesGlobalVariableAttr(
1154  *this, TemplateArgs, SYCLAddIRAttributesGlobalVariable, New);
1155  continue;
1156  }
1157  if (const auto *A = dyn_cast<WorkGroupSizeHintAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1158  instantiateWorkGroupSizeHintAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, A, New);
1159  continue;
1160  }
1161  if (const auto *A = dyn_cast<SYCLDeviceHasAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1162  instantiateSYCLDeviceHasAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, A, New);
1163  continue;
1164  }
1165  if (const auto *A = dyn_cast<SYCLUsesAspectsAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1166  instantiateSYCLUsesAspectsAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, A, New);
1167  continue;
1168  }
1169  // Existing DLL attribute on the instantiation takes precedence.
1170  if (TmplAttr->getKind() == attr::DLLExport ||
1171  TmplAttr->getKind() == attr::DLLImport) {
1172  if (New->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>() || New->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>()) {
1173  continue;
1174  }
1175  }
1176 
1177  if (const auto *ABIAttr = dyn_cast<ParameterABIAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1178  AddParameterABIAttr(New, *ABIAttr, ABIAttr->getABI());
1179  continue;
1180  }
1181 
1182  if (isa<NSConsumedAttr>(TmplAttr) || isa<OSConsumedAttr>(TmplAttr) ||
1183  isa<CFConsumedAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1184  AddXConsumedAttr(New, *TmplAttr, attrToRetainOwnershipKind(TmplAttr),
1185  /*template instantiation=*/true);
1186  continue;
1187  }
1188 
1189  if (auto *A = dyn_cast<PointerAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1190  if (!New->hasAttr<PointerAttr>())
1191  New->addAttr(A->clone(Context));
1192  continue;
1193  }
1194 
1195  if (auto *A = dyn_cast<OwnerAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1196  if (!New->hasAttr<OwnerAttr>())
1197  New->addAttr(A->clone(Context));
1198  continue;
1199  }
1200 
1201  if (auto *A = dyn_cast<SYCLKernelAttr>(TmplAttr)) {
1202  instantiateDependentSYCLKernelAttr(*this, TemplateArgs, *A, New);
1203  continue;
1204  }
1205 
1206  assert(!TmplAttr->isPackExpansion());
1207  if (TmplAttr->isLateParsed() && LateAttrs) {
1208  // Late parsed attributes must be instantiated and attached after the
1209  // enclosing class has been instantiated. See Sema::InstantiateClass.
1210  LocalInstantiationScope *Saved = nullptr;
1211  if (CurrentInstantiationScope)
1212  Saved = CurrentInstantiationScope->cloneScopes(OuterMostScope);
1213  LateAttrs->push_back(LateInstantiatedAttribute(TmplAttr, Saved, New));
1214  } else {
1215  // Allow 'this' within late-parsed attributes.
1216  auto *ND = cast<NamedDecl>(New);
1217  auto *ThisContext = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(ND->getDeclContext());
1218  CXXThisScopeRAII ThisScope(*this, ThisContext, Qualifiers(),
1219  ND->isCXXInstanceMember());
1220 
1221  Attr *NewAttr = sema::instantiateTemplateAttribute(TmplAttr, Context,
1222  *this, TemplateArgs);
1223  if (NewAttr && isRelevantAttr(*this, New, TmplAttr))
1224  New->addAttr(NewAttr);
1225  }
1226  }
1227 }
1228 
1229 /// In the MS ABI, we need to instantiate default arguments of dllexported
1230 /// default constructors along with the constructor definition. This allows IR
1231 /// gen to emit a constructor closure which calls the default constructor with
1232 /// its default arguments.
1233 void Sema::InstantiateDefaultCtorDefaultArgs(CXXConstructorDecl *Ctor) {
1234  assert(Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() &&
1235  Ctor->isDefaultConstructor());
1236  unsigned NumParams = Ctor->getNumParams();
1237  if (NumParams == 0)
1238  return;
1239  DLLExportAttr *Attr = Ctor->getAttr<DLLExportAttr>();
1240  if (!Attr)
1241  return;
1242  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumParams; ++I) {
1243  (void)CheckCXXDefaultArgExpr(Attr->getLocation(), Ctor,
1244  Ctor->getParamDecl(I));
1245  DiscardCleanupsInEvaluationContext();
1246  }
1247 }
1248 
1249 /// Get the previous declaration of a declaration for the purposes of template
1250 /// instantiation. If this finds a previous declaration, then the previous
1251 /// declaration of the instantiation of D should be an instantiation of the
1252 /// result of this function.
1253 template<typename DeclT>
1254 static DeclT *getPreviousDeclForInstantiation(DeclT *D) {
1255  DeclT *Result = D->getPreviousDecl();
1256 
1257  // If the declaration is within a class, and the previous declaration was
1258  // merged from a different definition of that class, then we don't have a
1259  // previous declaration for the purpose of template instantiation.
1260  if (Result && isa<CXXRecordDecl>(D->getDeclContext()) &&
1261  D->getLexicalDeclContext() != Result->getLexicalDeclContext())
1262  return nullptr;
1263 
1264  return Result;
1265 }

1322 
1323 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::InstantiateTypedefNameDecl(TypedefNameDecl *D,
1324  bool IsTypeAlias) {
1325  bool Invalid = false;
1326  TypeSourceInfo *DI = D->getTypeSourceInfo();
1327  if (DI->getType()->isInstantiationDependentType() ||
1328  DI->getType()->isVariablyModifiedType()) {
1329  DI = SemaRef.SubstType(DI, TemplateArgs,
1330  D->getLocation(), D->getDeclName());
1331  if (!DI) {
1332  Invalid = true;
1333  DI = SemaRef.Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(SemaRef.Context.IntTy);
1334  }
1335  } else {
1336  SemaRef.MarkDeclarationsReferencedInType(D->getLocation(), DI->getType());
1337  }
1338 
1339  // HACK: 2012-10-23 g++ has a bug where it gets the value kind of ?: wrong.
1340  // libstdc++ relies upon this bug in its implementation of common_type. If we
1341  // happen to be processing that implementation, fake up the g++ ?:
1342  // semantics. See LWG issue 2141 for more information on the bug. The bugs
1343  // are fixed in g++ and libstdc++ 4.9.0 (2014-04-22).
1344  const DecltypeType *DT = DI->getType()->getAs<DecltypeType>();
1345  CXXRecordDecl *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D->getDeclContext());
1346  if (DT && RD && isa<ConditionalOperator>(DT->getUnderlyingExpr()) &&
1347  DT->isReferenceType() &&
1348  RD->getEnclosingNamespaceContext() == SemaRef.getStdNamespace() &&
1349  RD->getIdentifier() && RD->getIdentifier()->isStr("common_type") &&
1350  D->getIdentifier() && D->getIdentifier()->isStr("type") &&
1351  SemaRef.getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(D->getBeginLoc()))
1352  // Fold it to the (non-reference) type which g++ would have produced.
1353  DI = SemaRef.Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(
1354  DI->getType().getNonReferenceType());
1355 
1356  // Create the new typedef
1357  TypedefNameDecl *Typedef;
1358  if (IsTypeAlias)
1359  Typedef = TypeAliasDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getBeginLoc(),
1360  D->getLocation(), D->getIdentifier(), DI);
1361  else
1362  Typedef = TypedefDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getBeginLoc(),
1363  D->getLocation(), D->getIdentifier(), DI);
1364  if (Invalid)
1365  Typedef->setInvalidDecl();
1366 
1367  // If the old typedef was the name for linkage purposes of an anonymous
1368  // tag decl, re-establish that relationship for the new typedef.
1369  if (const TagType *oldTagType = D->getUnderlyingType()->getAs<TagType>()) {
1370  TagDecl *oldTag = oldTagType->getDecl();
1371  if (oldTag->getTypedefNameForAnonDecl() == D && !Invalid) {
1372  TagDecl *newTag = DI->getType()->castAs<TagType>()->getDecl();
1373  assert(!newTag->hasNameForLinkage());
1374  newTag->setTypedefNameForAnonDecl(Typedef);
1375  }
1376  }
1377 
1378  if (TypedefNameDecl *Prev = getPreviousDeclForInstantiation(D)) {
1379  NamedDecl *InstPrev = SemaRef.FindInstantiatedDecl(D->getLocation(), Prev,
1380  TemplateArgs);
1381  if (!InstPrev)
1382  return nullptr;
1383 
1384  TypedefNameDecl *InstPrevTypedef = cast<TypedefNameDecl>(InstPrev);
1385 
1386  // If the typedef types are not identical, reject them.
1387  SemaRef.isIncompatibleTypedef(InstPrevTypedef, Typedef);
1388 
1389  Typedef->setPreviousDecl(InstPrevTypedef);
1390  }
1391 
1392  SemaRef.InstantiateAttrs(TemplateArgs, D, Typedef);
1393 
1394  if (D->getUnderlyingType()->getAs<DependentNameType>())
1395  SemaRef.inferGslPointerAttribute(Typedef);
1396 
1397  Typedef->setAccess(D->getAccess());
1398  Typedef->setReferenced(D->isReferenced());
1399 
1400  return Typedef;
1401 }
1402 
1403 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitTypedefDecl(TypedefDecl *D) {
1404  Decl *Typedef = InstantiateTypedefNameDecl(D, /*IsTypeAlias=*/false);
1405  if (Typedef)
1406  Owner->addDecl(Typedef);
1407  return Typedef;
1408 }

1410 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitTypeAliasDecl(TypeAliasDecl *D) {
1411  Decl *Typedef = InstantiateTypedefNameDecl(D, /*IsTypeAlias=*/true);
1412  if (Typedef)
1413  Owner->addDecl(Typedef);
1414  return Typedef;
1415 }

1417 Decl *
1418 TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitTypeAliasTemplateDecl(TypeAliasTemplateDecl *D) {
1419  // Create a local instantiation scope for this type alias template, which
1420  // will contain the instantiations of the template parameters.
1421  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(SemaRef);
1422 
1423  TemplateParameterList *TempParams = D->getTemplateParameters();
1424  TemplateParameterList *InstParams = SubstTemplateParams(TempParams);
1425  if (!InstParams)
1426  return nullptr;
1427 
1428  TypeAliasDecl *Pattern = D->getTemplatedDecl();
1429 
1430  TypeAliasTemplateDecl *PrevAliasTemplate = nullptr;
1431  if (getPreviousDeclForInstantiation<TypedefNameDecl>(Pattern)) {
1432  DeclContext::lookup_result Found = Owner->lookup(Pattern->getDeclName());
1433  if (!Found.empty()) {
1434  PrevAliasTemplate = dyn_cast<TypeAliasTemplateDecl>(Found.front());
1435  }
1436  }
1437 
1438  TypeAliasDecl *AliasInst = cast_or_null<TypeAliasDecl>(
1439  InstantiateTypedefNameDecl(Pattern, /*IsTypeAlias=*/true));
1440  if (!AliasInst)
1441  return nullptr;
1442 
1443  TypeAliasTemplateDecl *Inst
1444  = TypeAliasTemplateDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getLocation(),
1445  D->getDeclName(), InstParams, AliasInst);
1446  AliasInst->setDescribedAliasTemplate(Inst);
1447  if (PrevAliasTemplate)
1448  Inst->setPreviousDecl(PrevAliasTemplate);
1449 
1450  Inst->setAccess(D->getAccess());
1451 
1452  if (!PrevAliasTemplate)
1453  Inst->setInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate(D);
1454 
1455  Owner->addDecl(Inst);
1456 
1457  return Inst;
1458 }
