1460 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitBindingDecl(BindingDecl *D) {
1461  auto *NewBD = BindingDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getLocation(),
1462  D->getIdentifier());
1463  NewBD->setReferenced(D->isReferenced());
1464  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(D, NewBD);
1465  return NewBD;
1466 }
1467 
1468 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitDecompositionDecl(DecompositionDecl *D) {
1469  // Transform the bindings first.
1470  SmallVector<BindingDecl*, 16> NewBindings;
1471  for (auto *OldBD : D->bindings())
1472  NewBindings.push_back(cast<BindingDecl>(VisitBindingDecl(OldBD)));
1473  ArrayRef<BindingDecl*> NewBindingArray = NewBindings;
1474 
1475  auto *NewDD = cast_or_null<DecompositionDecl>(
1476  VisitVarDecl(D, /*InstantiatingVarTemplate=*/false, &NewBindingArray));
1477 
1478  if (!NewDD || NewDD->isInvalidDecl())
1479  for (auto *NewBD : NewBindings)
1480  NewBD->setInvalidDecl();
1481 
1482  return NewDD;
1483 }
1484 
1485 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitVarDecl(VarDecl *D) {
1486  return VisitVarDecl(D, /*InstantiatingVarTemplate=*/false);
1487 }
1488 
1489 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitVarDecl(VarDecl *D,
1490  bool InstantiatingVarTemplate,
1491  ArrayRef<BindingDecl*> *Bindings) {
1492 
1493  // Do substitution on the type of the declaration
1494  TypeSourceInfo *DI = SemaRef.SubstType(
1495  D->getTypeSourceInfo(), TemplateArgs, D->getTypeSpecStartLoc(),
1496  D->getDeclName(), /*AllowDeducedTST*/true);
1497  if (!DI)
1498  return nullptr;
1499 
1500  if (DI->getType()->isFunctionType()) {
1501  SemaRef.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_variable_instantiates_to_function)
1502  << D->isStaticDataMember() << DI->getType();
1503  return nullptr;
1504  }
1505 
1506  DeclContext *DC = Owner;
1507  if (D->isLocalExternDecl())
1508  SemaRef.adjustContextForLocalExternDecl(DC);
1509 
1510  // Build the instantiated declaration.
1511  VarDecl *Var;
1512  if (Bindings)
1513  Var = DecompositionDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, DC, D->getInnerLocStart(),
1514  D->getLocation(), DI->getType(), DI,
1515  D->getStorageClass(), *Bindings);
1516  else
1517  Var = VarDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, DC, D->getInnerLocStart(),
1518  D->getLocation(), D->getIdentifier(), DI->getType(),
1519  DI, D->getStorageClass());
1520 
1521  // In ARC, infer 'retaining' for variables of retainable type.
1522  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
1523  SemaRef.inferObjCARCLifetime(Var))
1524  Var->setInvalidDecl();
1525 
1526  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().OpenCL)
1527  SemaRef.deduceOpenCLAddressSpace(Var);
1528 
1529  // Substitute the nested name specifier, if any.
1530  if (SubstQualifier(D, Var))
1531  return nullptr;
1532 
1533  SemaRef.BuildVariableInstantiation(Var, D, TemplateArgs, LateAttrs, Owner,
1534  StartingScope, InstantiatingVarTemplate);
1535  if (D->isNRVOVariable() && !Var->isInvalidDecl()) {
1536  QualType RT;
1537  if (auto *F = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(DC))
1538  RT = F->getReturnType();
1539  else if (isa<BlockDecl>(DC))
1540  RT = cast<FunctionType>(SemaRef.getCurBlock()->FunctionType)
1541  ->getReturnType();
1542  else
1543  llvm_unreachable("Unknown context type");
1544 
1545  // This is the last chance we have of checking copy elision eligibility
1546  // for functions in dependent contexts. The sema actions for building
1547  // the return statement during template instantiation will have no effect
1548  // regarding copy elision, since NRVO propagation runs on the scope exit
1549  // actions, and these are not run on instantiation.
1550  // This might run through some VarDecls which were returned from non-taken
1551  // 'if constexpr' branches, and these will end up being constructed on the
1552  // return slot even if they will never be returned, as a sort of accidental
1553  // 'optimization'. Notably, functions with 'auto' return types won't have it
1554  // deduced by this point. Coupled with the limitation described
1555  // previously, this makes it very hard to support copy elision for these.
1556  Sema::NamedReturnInfo Info = SemaRef.getNamedReturnInfo(Var);
1557  bool NRVO = SemaRef.getCopyElisionCandidate(Info, RT) != nullptr;
1558  Var->setNRVOVariable(NRVO);
1559  }
1560 
1561  Var->setImplicit(D->isImplicit());
1562 
1563  if (Var->isStaticLocal())
1564  SemaRef.CheckStaticLocalForDllExport(Var);
1565 
1566  // Only add this if we aren't instantiating a variable template. We'll end up
1567  // adding the VarTemplateSpecializationDecl later.
1568  if (!InstantiatingVarTemplate)
1569  SemaRef.addSyclVarDecl(Var);
1570  return Var;
1571 }
1572 
1573 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitAccessSpecDecl(AccessSpecDecl *D) {
1574  AccessSpecDecl* AD
1575  = AccessSpecDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, D->getAccess(), Owner,
1576  D->getAccessSpecifierLoc(), D->getColonLoc());
1577  Owner->addHiddenDecl(AD);
1578  return AD;
1579 }
1580 
1581 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitFieldDecl(FieldDecl *D) {
1582  bool Invalid = false;
1583  TypeSourceInfo *DI = D->getTypeSourceInfo();
1584  if (DI->getType()->isInstantiationDependentType() ||
1585  DI->getType()->isVariablyModifiedType()) {
1586  DI = SemaRef.SubstType(DI, TemplateArgs,
1587  D->getLocation(), D->getDeclName());
1588  if (!DI) {
1589  DI = D->getTypeSourceInfo();
1590  Invalid = true;
1591  } else if (DI->getType()->isFunctionType()) {
1592  // C++ [temp.arg.type]p3:
1593  // If a declaration acquires a function type through a type
1594  // dependent on a template-parameter and this causes a
1595  // declaration that does not use the syntactic form of a
1596  // function declarator to have function type, the program is
1597  // ill-formed.
1598  SemaRef.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_field_instantiates_to_function)
1599  << DI->getType();
1600  Invalid = true;
1601  }
1602  } else {
1603  SemaRef.MarkDeclarationsReferencedInType(D->getLocation(), DI->getType());
1604  }
1605 
1606  Expr *BitWidth = D->getBitWidth();
1607  if (Invalid)
1608  BitWidth = nullptr;
1609  else if (BitWidth) {
1610  // The bit-width expression is a constant expression.
1611  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
1612  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
1613 
1614  ExprResult InstantiatedBitWidth
1615  = SemaRef.SubstExpr(BitWidth, TemplateArgs);
1616  if (InstantiatedBitWidth.isInvalid()) {
1617  Invalid = true;
1618  BitWidth = nullptr;
1619  } else
1620  BitWidth = InstantiatedBitWidth.getAs<Expr>();
1621  }
1622 
1623  FieldDecl *Field = SemaRef.CheckFieldDecl(D->getDeclName(),
1624  DI->getType(), DI,
1625  cast<RecordDecl>(Owner),
1626  D->getLocation(),
1627  D->isMutable(),
1628  BitWidth,
1629  D->getInClassInitStyle(),
1630  D->getInnerLocStart(),
1631  D->getAccess(),
1632  nullptr);
1633  if (!Field) {
1634  cast<Decl>(Owner)->setInvalidDecl();
1635  return nullptr;
1636  }
1637 
1638  SemaRef.InstantiateAttrs(TemplateArgs, D, Field, LateAttrs, StartingScope);
1639 
1640  if (Field->hasAttrs())
1641  SemaRef.CheckAlignasUnderalignment(Field);
1642 
1643  if (Invalid)
1644  Field->setInvalidDecl();
1645 
1646  if (!Field->getDeclName()) {
1647  // Keep track of where this decl came from.
1648  SemaRef.Context.setInstantiatedFromUnnamedFieldDecl(Field, D);
1649  }
1650  if (CXXRecordDecl *Parent= dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Field->getDeclContext())) {
1651  if (Parent->isAnonymousStructOrUnion() &&
1652  Parent->getRedeclContext()->isFunctionOrMethod())
1653  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(D, Field);
1654  }
1655 
1656  Field->setImplicit(D->isImplicit());
1657  Field->setAccess(D->getAccess());
1658  Owner->addDecl(Field);
1659 
1660  return Field;
1661 }
1662 
1663 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitMSPropertyDecl(MSPropertyDecl *D) {
1664  bool Invalid = false;
1665  TypeSourceInfo *DI = D->getTypeSourceInfo();
1666 
1667  if (DI->getType()->isVariablyModifiedType()) {
1668  SemaRef.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_property_is_variably_modified)
1669  << D;
1670  Invalid = true;
1671  } else if (DI->getType()->isInstantiationDependentType()) {
1672  DI = SemaRef.SubstType(DI, TemplateArgs,
1673  D->getLocation(), D->getDeclName());
1674  if (!DI) {
1675  DI = D->getTypeSourceInfo();
1676  Invalid = true;
1677  } else if (DI->getType()->isFunctionType()) {
1678  // C++ [temp.arg.type]p3:
1679  // If a declaration acquires a function type through a type
1680  // dependent on a template-parameter and this causes a
1681  // declaration that does not use the syntactic form of a
1682  // function declarator to have function type, the program is
1683  // ill-formed.
1684  SemaRef.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_field_instantiates_to_function)
1685  << DI->getType();
1686  Invalid = true;
1687  }
1688  } else {
1689  SemaRef.MarkDeclarationsReferencedInType(D->getLocation(), DI->getType());
1690  }
1691 
1692  MSPropertyDecl *Property = MSPropertyDecl::Create(
1693  SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getLocation(), D->getDeclName(), DI->getType(),
1694  DI, D->getBeginLoc(), D->getGetterId(), D->getSetterId());
1695 
1696  SemaRef.InstantiateAttrs(TemplateArgs, D, Property, LateAttrs,
1697  StartingScope);
1698 
1699  if (Invalid)
1700  Property->setInvalidDecl();
1701 
1702  Property->setAccess(D->getAccess());
1703  Owner->addDecl(Property);
1704 
1705  return Property;
1706 }
1707 
1708 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitIndirectFieldDecl(IndirectFieldDecl *D) {
1709  NamedDecl **NamedChain =
1710  new (SemaRef.Context)NamedDecl*[D->getChainingSize()];
1711 
1712  int i = 0;
1713  for (auto *PI : D->chain()) {
1714  NamedDecl *Next = SemaRef.FindInstantiatedDecl(D->getLocation(), PI,
1715  TemplateArgs);
1716  if (!Next)
1717  return nullptr;
1718 
1719  NamedChain[i++] = Next;
1720  }
1721 
1722  QualType T = cast<FieldDecl>(NamedChain[i-1])->getType();
1723  IndirectFieldDecl *IndirectField = IndirectFieldDecl::Create(
1724  SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getLocation(), D->getIdentifier(), T,
1725  {NamedChain, D->getChainingSize()});
1726 
1727  for (const auto *Attr : D->attrs())
1728  IndirectField->addAttr(Attr->clone(SemaRef.Context));
1729 
1730  IndirectField->setImplicit(D->isImplicit());
1731  IndirectField->setAccess(D->getAccess());
1732  Owner->addDecl(IndirectField);
1733  return IndirectField;
1734 }
1735 
1736 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitFriendDecl(FriendDecl *D) {
1737  // Handle friend type expressions by simply substituting template
1738  // parameters into the pattern type and checking the result.
1739  if (TypeSourceInfo *Ty = D->getFriendType()) {
1740  TypeSourceInfo *InstTy;
1741  // If this is an unsupported friend, don't bother substituting template
1742  // arguments into it. The actual type referred to won't be used by any
1743  // parts of Clang, and may not be valid for instantiating. Just use the
1744  // same info for the instantiated friend.
1745  if (D->isUnsupportedFriend()) {
1746  InstTy = Ty;
1747  } else {
1748  InstTy = SemaRef.SubstType(Ty, TemplateArgs,
1749  D->getLocation(), DeclarationName());
1750  }
1751  if (!InstTy)
1752  return nullptr;
1753 
1754  FriendDecl *FD = SemaRef.CheckFriendTypeDecl(D->getBeginLoc(),
1755  D->getFriendLoc(), InstTy);
1756  if (!FD)
1757  return nullptr;
1758 
1759  FD->setAccess(AS_public);
1760  FD->setUnsupportedFriend(D->isUnsupportedFriend());
1761  Owner->addDecl(FD);
1762  return FD;
1763  }
1764 
1765  NamedDecl *ND = D->getFriendDecl();
1766  assert(ND && "friend decl must be a decl or a type!");
1767 
1768  // All of the Visit implementations for the various potential friend
1769  // declarations have to be carefully written to work for friend
1770  // objects, with the most important detail being that the target
1771  // decl should almost certainly not be placed in Owner.
1772  Decl *NewND = Visit(ND);
1773  if (!NewND) return nullptr;
1774 
1775  FriendDecl *FD =
1776  FriendDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getLocation(),
1777  cast<NamedDecl>(NewND), D->getFriendLoc());
1778  FD->setAccess(AS_public);
1779  FD->setUnsupportedFriend(D->isUnsupportedFriend());
1780  Owner->addDecl(FD);
1781  return FD;
1782 }
1783 
1784 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitStaticAssertDecl(StaticAssertDecl *D) {
1785  Expr *AssertExpr = D->getAssertExpr();
1786 
1787  // The expression in a static assertion is a constant expression.
1788  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
1789  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
1790 
1791  ExprResult InstantiatedAssertExpr
1792  = SemaRef.SubstExpr(AssertExpr, TemplateArgs);
1793  if (InstantiatedAssertExpr.isInvalid())
1794  return nullptr;
1795 
1796  return SemaRef.BuildStaticAssertDeclaration(D->getLocation(),
1797  InstantiatedAssertExpr.get(),
1798  D->getMessage(),
1799  D->getRParenLoc(),
1800  D->isFailed());
1801 }
1802 
1803 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitEnumDecl(EnumDecl *D) {
1804  EnumDecl *PrevDecl = nullptr;
1805  if (EnumDecl *PatternPrev = getPreviousDeclForInstantiation(D)) {
1806  NamedDecl *Prev = SemaRef.FindInstantiatedDecl(D->getLocation(),
1807  PatternPrev,
1808  TemplateArgs);
1809  if (!Prev) return nullptr;
1810  PrevDecl = cast<EnumDecl>(Prev);
1811  }
1812 
1813  EnumDecl *Enum =
1814  EnumDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getBeginLoc(),
1815  D->getLocation(), D->getIdentifier(), PrevDecl,
1816  D->isScoped(), D->isScopedUsingClassTag(), D->isFixed());
1817  if (D->isFixed()) {
1818  if (TypeSourceInfo *TI = D->getIntegerTypeSourceInfo()) {
1819  // If we have type source information for the underlying type, it means it
1820  // has been explicitly set by the user. Perform substitution on it before
1821  // moving on.
1822  SourceLocation UnderlyingLoc = TI->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc();
1823  TypeSourceInfo *NewTI = SemaRef.SubstType(TI, TemplateArgs, UnderlyingLoc,
1824  DeclarationName());
1825  if (!NewTI || SemaRef.CheckEnumUnderlyingType(NewTI))
1826  Enum->setIntegerType(SemaRef.Context.IntTy);
1827  else
1828  Enum->setIntegerTypeSourceInfo(NewTI);
1829  } else {
1830  assert(!D->getIntegerType()->isDependentType()
1831  && "Dependent type without type source info");
1832  Enum->setIntegerType(D->getIntegerType());
1833  }
1834  }
1835 
1836  SemaRef.InstantiateAttrs(TemplateArgs, D, Enum);
1837 
1838  Enum->setInstantiationOfMemberEnum(D, TSK_ImplicitInstantiation);
1839  Enum->setAccess(D->getAccess());
1840  // Forward the mangling number from the template to the instantiated decl.
1841  SemaRef.Context.setManglingNumber(Enum, SemaRef.Context.getManglingNumber(D));
1842  // See if the old tag was defined along with a declarator.
1843  // If it did, mark the new tag as being associated with that declarator.
1844  if (DeclaratorDecl *DD = SemaRef.Context.getDeclaratorForUnnamedTagDecl(D))
1845  SemaRef.Context.addDeclaratorForUnnamedTagDecl(Enum, DD);
1846  // See if the old tag was defined along with a typedef.
1847  // If it did, mark the new tag as being associated with that typedef.
1848  if (TypedefNameDecl *TND = SemaRef.Context.getTypedefNameForUnnamedTagDecl(D))
1849  SemaRef.Context.addTypedefNameForUnnamedTagDecl(Enum, TND);
1850  if (SubstQualifier(D, Enum)) return nullptr;
1851  Owner->addDecl(Enum);
1852 
1853  EnumDecl *Def = D->getDefinition();
1854  if (Def && Def != D) {
1855  // If this is an out-of-line definition of an enum member template, check
1856  // that the underlying types match in the instantiation of both
1857  // declarations.
1858  if (TypeSourceInfo *TI = Def->getIntegerTypeSourceInfo()) {
1859  SourceLocation UnderlyingLoc = TI->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc();
1860  QualType DefnUnderlying =
1861  SemaRef.SubstType(TI->getType(), TemplateArgs,
1862  UnderlyingLoc, DeclarationName());
1863  SemaRef.CheckEnumRedeclaration(Def->getLocation(), Def->isScoped(),
1864  DefnUnderlying, /*IsFixed=*/true, Enum);
1865  }
1866  }
1867 
1868  // C++11 [temp.inst]p1: The implicit instantiation of a class template
1869  // specialization causes the implicit instantiation of the declarations, but
1870  // not the definitions of scoped member enumerations.
1871  //
1872  // DR1484 clarifies that enumeration definitions inside of a template
1873  // declaration aren't considered entities that can be separately instantiated
1874  // from the rest of the entity they are declared inside of.
1875  if (isDeclWithinFunction(D) ? D == Def : Def && !Enum->isScoped()) {
1876  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(D, Enum);
1877  InstantiateEnumDefinition(Enum, Def);
1878  }
1879 
1880  return Enum;
1881 }
1882 
1883 void TemplateDeclInstantiator::InstantiateEnumDefinition(
1884  EnumDecl *Enum, EnumDecl *Pattern) {
1885  Enum->startDefinition();
1886 
1887  // Update the location to refer to the definition.
1888  Enum->setLocation(Pattern->getLocation());
1889 
1890  SmallVector<Decl*, 4> Enumerators;
1891 
1892  EnumConstantDecl *LastEnumConst = nullptr;
1893  for (auto *EC : Pattern->enumerators()) {
1894  // The specified value for the enumerator.
1895  ExprResult Value((Expr *)nullptr);
1896  if (Expr *UninstValue = EC->getInitExpr()) {
1897  // The enumerator's value expression is a constant expression.
1898  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
1899  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
1900 
1901  Value = SemaRef.SubstExpr(UninstValue, TemplateArgs);
1902  }
1903 
1904  // Drop the initial value and continue.
1905  bool isInvalid = false;
1906  if (Value.isInvalid()) {
1907  Value = nullptr;
1908  isInvalid = true;
1909  }
1910 
1911  EnumConstantDecl *EnumConst
1912  = SemaRef.CheckEnumConstant(Enum, LastEnumConst,
1913  EC->getLocation(), EC->getIdentifier(),
1914  Value.get());
1915 
1916  if (isInvalid) {
1917  if (EnumConst)
1918  EnumConst->setInvalidDecl();
1919  Enum->setInvalidDecl();
1920  }
1921 
1922  if (EnumConst) {
1923  SemaRef.InstantiateAttrs(TemplateArgs, EC, EnumConst);
1924 
1925  EnumConst->setAccess(Enum->getAccess());
1926  Enum->addDecl(EnumConst);
1927  Enumerators.push_back(EnumConst);
1928  LastEnumConst = EnumConst;
1929 
1930  if (Pattern->getDeclContext()->isFunctionOrMethod() &&
1931  !Enum->isScoped()) {
1932  // If the enumeration is within a function or method, record the enum
1933  // constant as a local.
1934  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(EC, EnumConst);
1935  }
1936  }
1937  }
1938 
1939  SemaRef.ActOnEnumBody(Enum->getLocation(), Enum->getBraceRange(), Enum,
1940  Enumerators, nullptr, ParsedAttributesView());
1941 }
1942 
1943 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitEnumConstantDecl(EnumConstantDecl *D) {
1944  llvm_unreachable("EnumConstantDecls can only occur within EnumDecls.");
1945 }
1946 
1947 Decl *
1948 TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitBuiltinTemplateDecl(BuiltinTemplateDecl *D) {
1949  llvm_unreachable("BuiltinTemplateDecls cannot be instantiated.");
1950 }
1951 
1952 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitClassTemplateDecl(ClassTemplateDecl *D) {
1953  bool isFriend = (D->getFriendObjectKind() != Decl::FOK_None);
1954 
1955  // Create a local instantiation scope for this class template, which
1956  // will contain the instantiations of the template parameters.
1957  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(SemaRef);
1958  TemplateParameterList *TempParams = D->getTemplateParameters();
1959  TemplateParameterList *InstParams = SubstTemplateParams(TempParams);
1960  if (!InstParams)
1961  return nullptr;
1962 
1963  CXXRecordDecl *Pattern = D->getTemplatedDecl();
1964 
1965  // Instantiate the qualifier. We have to do this first in case
1966  // we're a friend declaration, because if we are then we need to put
1967  // the new declaration in the appropriate context.
1968  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc = Pattern->getQualifierLoc();
1969  if (QualifierLoc) {
1970  QualifierLoc = SemaRef.SubstNestedNameSpecifierLoc(QualifierLoc,
1971  TemplateArgs);
1972  if (!QualifierLoc)
1973  return nullptr;
1974  }
1975 
1976  CXXRecordDecl *PrevDecl = nullptr;
1977  ClassTemplateDecl *PrevClassTemplate = nullptr;
1978 
1979  if (!isFriend && getPreviousDeclForInstantiation(Pattern)) {
1980  DeclContext::lookup_result Found = Owner->lookup(Pattern->getDeclName());
1981  if (!Found.empty()) {
1982  PrevClassTemplate = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateDecl>(Found.front());
1983  if (PrevClassTemplate)
1984  PrevDecl = PrevClassTemplate->getTemplatedDecl();
1985  }
1986  }
1987 
1988  // If this isn't a friend, then it's a member template, in which
1989  // case we just want to build the instantiation in the
1990  // specialization. If it is a friend, we want to build it in
1991  // the appropriate context.
1992  DeclContext *DC = Owner;
1993  if (isFriend) {
1994  if (QualifierLoc) {
1995  CXXScopeSpec SS;
1996  SS.Adopt(QualifierLoc);
1997  DC = SemaRef.computeDeclContext(SS);
1998  if (!DC) return nullptr;
1999  } else {
2000  DC = SemaRef.FindInstantiatedContext(Pattern->getLocation(),
2001  Pattern->getDeclContext(),
2002  TemplateArgs);
2003  }
2004 
2005  // Look for a previous declaration of the template in the owning
2006  // context.
2007  LookupResult R(SemaRef, Pattern->getDeclName(), Pattern->getLocation(),
2008  Sema::LookupOrdinaryName,
2009  SemaRef.forRedeclarationInCurContext());
2010  SemaRef.LookupQualifiedName(R, DC);
2011 
2012  if (R.isSingleResult()) {
2013  PrevClassTemplate = R.getAsSingle<ClassTemplateDecl>();
2014  if (PrevClassTemplate)
2015  PrevDecl = PrevClassTemplate->getTemplatedDecl();
2016  }
2017 
2018  if (!PrevClassTemplate && QualifierLoc) {
2019  SemaRef.Diag(Pattern->getLocation(), diag::err_not_tag_in_scope)
2020  << D->getTemplatedDecl()->getTagKind() << Pattern->getDeclName() << DC
2021  << QualifierLoc.getSourceRange();
2022  return nullptr;
2023  }
2024 
2025  if (PrevClassTemplate) {
2026  TemplateParameterList *PrevParams
2027  = PrevClassTemplate->getMostRecentDecl()->getTemplateParameters();
2028 
2029  // Make sure the parameter lists match.
2030  if (!SemaRef.TemplateParameterListsAreEqual(InstParams, PrevParams, true,
2031  Sema::TPL_TemplateMatch))
2032  return nullptr;
2033 
2034  // Do some additional validation, then merge default arguments
2035  // from the existing declarations.
2036  if (SemaRef.CheckTemplateParameterList(InstParams, PrevParams,
2037  Sema::TPC_ClassTemplate))
2038  return nullptr;
2039  }
2040  }
2041 
2042  CXXRecordDecl *RecordInst = CXXRecordDecl::Create(
2043  SemaRef.Context, Pattern->getTagKind(), DC, Pattern->getBeginLoc(),
2044  Pattern->getLocation(), Pattern->getIdentifier(), PrevDecl,
2045  /*DelayTypeCreation=*/true);
2046 
2047  if (QualifierLoc)
2048  RecordInst->setQualifierInfo(QualifierLoc);
2049 
2050  SemaRef.InstantiateAttrsForDecl(TemplateArgs, Pattern, RecordInst, LateAttrs,
2051  StartingScope);
2052 
2053  ClassTemplateDecl *Inst
2054  = ClassTemplateDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, DC, D->getLocation(),
2055  D->getIdentifier(), InstParams, RecordInst);
2056  assert(!(isFriend && Owner->isDependentContext()));
2057  Inst->setPreviousDecl(PrevClassTemplate);
2058 
2059  RecordInst->setDescribedClassTemplate(Inst);
2060 
2061  if (isFriend) {
2062  if (PrevClassTemplate)
2063  Inst->setAccess(PrevClassTemplate->getAccess());
2064  else
2065  Inst->setAccess(D->getAccess());
2066 
2067  Inst->setObjectOfFriendDecl();
2068  // TODO: do we want to track the instantiation progeny of this
2069  // friend target decl?
2070  } else {
2071  Inst->setAccess(D->getAccess());
2072  if (!PrevClassTemplate)
2073  Inst->setInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate(D);
2074  }
2075 
2076  // Trigger creation of the type for the instantiation.
2077  SemaRef.Context.getInjectedClassNameType(RecordInst,
2078  Inst->getInjectedClassNameSpecialization());
2079 
2080  // Finish handling of friends.
2081  if (isFriend) {
2082  DC->makeDeclVisibleInContext(Inst);
2083  Inst->setLexicalDeclContext(Owner);
2084  RecordInst->setLexicalDeclContext(Owner);
2085  return Inst;
2086  }
2087 
2088  if (D->isOutOfLine()) {
2089  Inst->setLexicalDeclContext(D->getLexicalDeclContext());
2090  RecordInst->setLexicalDeclContext(D->getLexicalDeclContext());
2091  }
2092 
2093  Owner->addDecl(Inst);
2094 
2095  if (!PrevClassTemplate) {
2096  // Queue up any out-of-line partial specializations of this member
2097  // class template; the client will force their instantiation once
2098  // the enclosing class has been instantiated.
2099  SmallVector<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *, 4> PartialSpecs;
2100  D->getPartialSpecializations(PartialSpecs);
2101  for (unsigned I = 0, N = PartialSpecs.size(); I != N; ++I)
2102  if (PartialSpecs[I]->getFirstDecl()->isOutOfLine())
2103  OutOfLinePartialSpecs.push_back(std::make_pair(Inst, PartialSpecs[I]));
2104  }
2105 
2106  return Inst;
2107 }
2108 
2109 Decl *
2110 TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl(
2111  ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *D) {
2112  ClassTemplateDecl *ClassTemplate = D->getSpecializedTemplate();
2113 
2114  // Lookup the already-instantiated declaration in the instantiation
2115  // of the class template and return that.
2116  DeclContext::lookup_result Found
2117  = Owner->lookup(ClassTemplate->getDeclName());
2118  if (Found.empty())
2119  return nullptr;
2120 
2121  ClassTemplateDecl *InstClassTemplate
2122  = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateDecl>(Found.front());
2123  if (!InstClassTemplate)
2124  return nullptr;
2125 
2126  if (ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *Result
2127  = InstClassTemplate->findPartialSpecInstantiatedFromMember(D))
2128  return Result;
2129 
2130  return InstantiateClassTemplatePartialSpecialization(InstClassTemplate, D);
2131 }
2132 
2133 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitVarTemplateDecl(VarTemplateDecl *D) {
2134  assert(D->getTemplatedDecl()->isStaticDataMember() &&
2135  "Only static data member templates are allowed.");
2136 
2137  // Create a local instantiation scope for this variable template, which
2138  // will contain the instantiations of the template parameters.
2139  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(SemaRef);
2140  TemplateParameterList *TempParams = D->getTemplateParameters();
2141  TemplateParameterList *InstParams = SubstTemplateParams(TempParams);
2142  if (!InstParams)
2143  return nullptr;
2144 
2145  VarDecl *Pattern = D->getTemplatedDecl();
2146  VarTemplateDecl *PrevVarTemplate = nullptr;
2147 
2148  if (getPreviousDeclForInstantiation(Pattern)) {
2149  DeclContext::lookup_result Found = Owner->lookup(Pattern->getDeclName());
2150  if (!Found.empty())
2151  PrevVarTemplate = dyn_cast<VarTemplateDecl>(Found.front());
2152  }
2153 
2154  VarDecl *VarInst =
2155  cast_or_null<VarDecl>(VisitVarDecl(Pattern,
2156  /*InstantiatingVarTemplate=*/true));
2157  if (!VarInst) return nullptr;
2158 
2159  DeclContext *DC = Owner;
2160 
2161  VarTemplateDecl *Inst = VarTemplateDecl::Create(
2162  SemaRef.Context, DC, D->getLocation(), D->getIdentifier(), InstParams,
2163  VarInst);
2164  VarInst->setDescribedVarTemplate(Inst);
2165  Inst->setPreviousDecl(PrevVarTemplate);
2166 
2167  Inst->setAccess(D->getAccess());
2168  if (!PrevVarTemplate)
2169  Inst->setInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate(D);
2170 
2171  if (D->isOutOfLine()) {
2172  Inst->setLexicalDeclContext(D->getLexicalDeclContext());
2173  VarInst->setLexicalDeclContext(D->getLexicalDeclContext());
2174  }
2175 
2176  Owner->addDecl(Inst);
2177 
2178  if (!PrevVarTemplate) {
2179  // Queue up any out-of-line partial specializations of this member
2180  // variable template; the client will force their instantiation once
2181  // the enclosing class has been instantiated.
2182  SmallVector<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *, 4> PartialSpecs;
2183  D->getPartialSpecializations(PartialSpecs);
2184  for (unsigned I = 0, N = PartialSpecs.size(); I != N; ++I)
2185  if (PartialSpecs[I]->getFirstDecl()->isOutOfLine())
2186  OutOfLineVarPartialSpecs.push_back(
2187  std::make_pair(Inst, PartialSpecs[I]));
2188  }
2189 
2190  return Inst;
2191 }
2192 
2193 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitVarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl(
2194  VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *D) {
2195  assert(D->isStaticDataMember() &&
2196  "Only static data member templates are allowed.");
2197 
2198  VarTemplateDecl *VarTemplate = D->getSpecializedTemplate();
2199 
2200  // Lookup the already-instantiated declaration and return that.
2201  DeclContext::lookup_result Found = Owner->lookup(VarTemplate->getDeclName());
2202  assert(!Found.empty() && "Instantiation found nothing?");
2203 
2204  VarTemplateDecl *InstVarTemplate = dyn_cast<VarTemplateDecl>(Found.front());
2205  assert(InstVarTemplate && "Instantiation did not find a variable template?");
2206 
2207  if (VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *Result =
2208  InstVarTemplate->findPartialSpecInstantiatedFromMember(D))
2209  return Result;
2210 
2211  return InstantiateVarTemplatePartialSpecialization(InstVarTemplate, D);
2212 }
2213 
2214 Decl *
2215 TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitFunctionTemplateDecl(FunctionTemplateDecl *D) {
2216  // Create a local instantiation scope for this function template, which
2217  // will contain the instantiations of the template parameters and then get
2218  // merged with the local instantiation scope for the function template
2219  // itself.
2220  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(SemaRef);
2221 
2222  TemplateParameterList *TempParams = D->getTemplateParameters();
2223  TemplateParameterList *InstParams = SubstTemplateParams(TempParams);
2224  if (!InstParams)
2225  return nullptr;
2226 
2227  FunctionDecl *Instantiated = nullptr;
2228  if (CXXMethodDecl *DMethod = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D->getTemplatedDecl()))
2229  Instantiated = cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(VisitCXXMethodDecl(DMethod,
2230  InstParams));
2231  else
2232  Instantiated = cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(VisitFunctionDecl(
2233  D->getTemplatedDecl(),
2234  InstParams));
2235 
2236  if (!Instantiated)
2237  return nullptr;
2238 
2239  // Link the instantiated function template declaration to the function
2240  // template from which it was instantiated.
2241  FunctionTemplateDecl *InstTemplate
2242  = Instantiated->getDescribedFunctionTemplate();
2243  InstTemplate->setAccess(D->getAccess());
2244  assert(InstTemplate &&
2245  "VisitFunctionDecl/CXXMethodDecl didn't create a template!");
2246 
2247  bool isFriend = (InstTemplate->getFriendObjectKind() != Decl::FOK_None);
2248 
2249  // Link the instantiation back to the pattern *unless* this is a
2250  // non-definition friend declaration.
2251  if (!InstTemplate->getInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate() &&
2252  !(isFriend && !D->getTemplatedDecl()->isThisDeclarationADefinition()))
2253  InstTemplate->setInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate(D);
2254 
2255  // Make declarations visible in the appropriate context.
2256  if (!isFriend) {
2257  Owner->addDecl(InstTemplate);
2258  } else if (InstTemplate->getDeclContext()->isRecord() &&
2259  !getPreviousDeclForInstantiation(D)) {
2260  SemaRef.CheckFriendAccess(InstTemplate);
2261  }
2262 
2263  return InstTemplate;
2264 }
2265 
2266 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitCXXRecordDecl(CXXRecordDecl *D) {
2267  CXXRecordDecl *PrevDecl = nullptr;
2268  if (CXXRecordDecl *PatternPrev = getPreviousDeclForInstantiation(D)) {
2269  NamedDecl *Prev = SemaRef.FindInstantiatedDecl(D->getLocation(),
2270  PatternPrev,
2271  TemplateArgs);
2272  if (!Prev) return nullptr;
2273  PrevDecl = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Prev);
2274  }
2275 
2276  CXXRecordDecl *Record = nullptr;
2277  bool IsInjectedClassName = D->isInjectedClassName();
2278  if (D->isLambda())
2279  Record = CXXRecordDecl::CreateLambda(
2280  SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getLambdaTypeInfo(), D->getLocation(),
2281  D->getLambdaDependencyKind(), D->isGenericLambda(),
2282  D->getLambdaCaptureDefault());
2283  else
2284  Record = CXXRecordDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, D->getTagKind(), Owner,
2285  D->getBeginLoc(), D->getLocation(),
2286  D->getIdentifier(), PrevDecl,
2287  /*DelayTypeCreation=*/IsInjectedClassName);
2288  // Link the type of the injected-class-name to that of the outer class.
2289  if (IsInjectedClassName)
2290  (void)SemaRef.Context.getTypeDeclType(Record, cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Owner));
2291 
2292  // Substitute the nested name specifier, if any.
2293  if (SubstQualifier(D, Record))
2294  return nullptr;
2295 
2296  SemaRef.InstantiateAttrsForDecl(TemplateArgs, D, Record, LateAttrs,
2297  StartingScope);
2298 
2299  Record->setImplicit(D->isImplicit());
2300  // FIXME: Check against AS_none is an ugly hack to work around the issue that
2301  // the tag decls introduced by friend class declarations don't have an access
2302  // specifier. Remove once this area of the code gets sorted out.
2303  if (D->getAccess() != AS_none)
2304  Record->setAccess(D->getAccess());
2305  if (!IsInjectedClassName)
2306  Record->setInstantiationOfMemberClass(D, TSK_ImplicitInstantiation);
2307 
2308  // If the original function was part of a friend declaration,
2309  // inherit its namespace state.
2310  if (D->getFriendObjectKind())
2311  Record->setObjectOfFriendDecl();
2312 
2313  // Make sure that anonymous structs and unions are recorded.
2314  if (D->isAnonymousStructOrUnion())
2315  Record->setAnonymousStructOrUnion(true);
2316 
2317  if (D->isLocalClass())
2318  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(D, Record);
2319 
2320  // Forward the mangling number from the template to the instantiated decl.
2321  SemaRef.Context.setManglingNumber(Record,
2322  SemaRef.Context.getManglingNumber(D));
2323 
2324  // See if the old tag was defined along with a declarator.
2325  // If it did, mark the new tag as being associated with that declarator.
2326  if (DeclaratorDecl *DD = SemaRef.Context.getDeclaratorForUnnamedTagDecl(D))
2327  SemaRef.Context.addDeclaratorForUnnamedTagDecl(Record, DD);
2328 
2329  // See if the old tag was defined along with a typedef.
2330  // If it did, mark the new tag as being associated with that typedef.
2331  if (TypedefNameDecl *TND = SemaRef.Context.getTypedefNameForUnnamedTagDecl(D))
2332  SemaRef.Context.addTypedefNameForUnnamedTagDecl(Record, TND);
2333 
2334  Owner->addDecl(Record);
2335 
2336  // DR1484 clarifies that the members of a local class are instantiated as part
2337  // of the instantiation of their enclosing entity.
2338  if (D->isCompleteDefinition() && D->isLocalClass()) {
2339  Sema::LocalEagerInstantiationScope LocalInstantiations(SemaRef);
2340 
2341  SemaRef.InstantiateClass(D->getLocation(), Record, D, TemplateArgs,
2342  TSK_ImplicitInstantiation,
2343  /*Complain=*/true);
2344 
2345  // For nested local classes, we will instantiate the members when we
2346  // reach the end of the outermost (non-nested) local class.
2347  if (!D->isCXXClassMember())
2348  SemaRef.InstantiateClassMembers(D->getLocation(), Record, TemplateArgs,
2349  TSK_ImplicitInstantiation);
2350 
2351  // This class may have local implicit instantiations that need to be
2352  // performed within this scope.
2353  LocalInstantiations.perform();
2354  }
2355 
2356  SemaRef.DiagnoseUnusedNestedTypedefs(Record);
2357 
2358  if (IsInjectedClassName)
2359  assert(Record->isInjectedClassName() && "Broken injected-class-name");
2360 
2361  return Record;
2362 }
2363 
2364 /// Adjust the given function type for an instantiation of the
2365 /// given declaration, to cope with modifications to the function's type that
2366 /// aren't reflected in the type-source information.
2367 ///
2368 /// \param D The declaration we're instantiating.
2369 /// \param TInfo The already-instantiated type.
2370 static QualType adjustFunctionTypeForInstantiation(ASTContext &Context,
2371  FunctionDecl *D,
2372  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo) {
2373  const FunctionProtoType *OrigFunc
2374  = D->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
2375  const FunctionProtoType *NewFunc
2376  = TInfo->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
2377  if (OrigFunc->getExtInfo() == NewFunc->getExtInfo())
2378  return TInfo->getType();
2379 
2380  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo NewEPI = NewFunc->getExtProtoInfo();
2381  NewEPI.ExtInfo = OrigFunc->getExtInfo();
2382  return Context.getFunctionType(NewFunc->getReturnType(),
2383  NewFunc->getParamTypes(), NewEPI);
2384 }
2385 
2386 /// Normal class members are of more specific types and therefore
2387 /// don't make it here. This function serves three purposes:
2388 /// 1) instantiating function templates
2389 /// 2) substituting friend declarations
2390 /// 3) substituting deduction guide declarations for nested class templates
2391 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitFunctionDecl(
2392  FunctionDecl *D, TemplateParameterList *TemplateParams,
2393  RewriteKind FunctionRewriteKind) {
2394  // Check whether there is already a function template specialization for
2395  // this declaration.
2396  FunctionTemplateDecl *FunctionTemplate = D->getDescribedFunctionTemplate();
2397  if (FunctionTemplate && !TemplateParams) {
2398  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Innermost = TemplateArgs.getInnermost();
2399 
2400  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
2401  FunctionDecl *SpecFunc
2402  = FunctionTemplate->findSpecialization(Innermost, InsertPos);
2403 
2404  // If we already have a function template specialization, return it.
2405  if (SpecFunc)
2406  return SpecFunc;
2407  }
2408 
2409  bool isFriend;
2410  if (FunctionTemplate)
2411  isFriend = (FunctionTemplate->getFriendObjectKind() != Decl::FOK_None);
2412  else
2413  isFriend = (D->getFriendObjectKind() != Decl::FOK_None);
2414 
2415  bool MergeWithParentScope = (TemplateParams != nullptr) ||
2416  Owner->isFunctionOrMethod() ||
2417  !(isa<Decl>(Owner) &&
2418  cast<Decl>(Owner)->isDefinedOutsideFunctionOrMethod());
2419  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(SemaRef, MergeWithParentScope);
2420 
2421  ExplicitSpecifier InstantiatedExplicitSpecifier;
2422  if (auto *DGuide = dyn_cast<CXXDeductionGuideDecl>(D)) {
2423  InstantiatedExplicitSpecifier = instantiateExplicitSpecifier(
2424  SemaRef, TemplateArgs, DGuide->getExplicitSpecifier(), DGuide);
2425  if (InstantiatedExplicitSpecifier.isInvalid())
2426  return nullptr;
2427  }
2428 
2429  SmallVector<ParmVarDecl *, 4> Params;
2430  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = SubstFunctionType(D, Params);
2431  if (!TInfo)
2432  return nullptr;
2433  QualType T = adjustFunctionTypeForInstantiation(SemaRef.Context, D, TInfo);
2434 
2435  if (TemplateParams && TemplateParams->size()) {
2436  auto *LastParam =
2437  dyn_cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(TemplateParams->asArray().back());
2438  if (LastParam && LastParam->isImplicit() &&
2439  LastParam->hasTypeConstraint()) {
2440  // In abbreviated templates, the type-constraints of invented template
2441  // type parameters are instantiated with the function type, invalidating
2442  // the TemplateParameterList which relied on the template type parameter
2443  // not having a type constraint. Recreate the TemplateParameterList with
2444  // the updated parameter list.
2445  TemplateParams = TemplateParameterList::Create(
2446  SemaRef.Context, TemplateParams->getTemplateLoc(),
2447  TemplateParams->getLAngleLoc(), TemplateParams->asArray(),
2448  TemplateParams->getRAngleLoc(), TemplateParams->getRequiresClause());
2449  }
2450  }
2451 
2452  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc = D->getQualifierLoc();
2453  if (QualifierLoc) {
2454  QualifierLoc = SemaRef.SubstNestedNameSpecifierLoc(QualifierLoc,
2455  TemplateArgs);
2456  if (!QualifierLoc)
2457  return nullptr;
2458  }
2459 
2460  // FIXME: Concepts: Do not substitute into constraint expressions
2461  Expr *TrailingRequiresClause = D->getTrailingRequiresClause();
2462  if (TrailingRequiresClause) {
2463  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext ConstantEvaluated(
2464  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
2465  ExprResult SubstRC = SemaRef.SubstExpr(TrailingRequiresClause,
2466  TemplateArgs);
2467  if (SubstRC.isInvalid())
2468  return nullptr;
2469  TrailingRequiresClause = SubstRC.get();
2470  if (!SemaRef.CheckConstraintExpression(TrailingRequiresClause))
2471  return nullptr;
2472  }
2473 
2474  // If we're instantiating a local function declaration, put the result
2475  // in the enclosing namespace; otherwise we need to find the instantiated
2476  // context.
2477  DeclContext *DC;
2478  if (D->isLocalExternDecl()) {
2479  DC = Owner;
2480  SemaRef.adjustContextForLocalExternDecl(DC);
2481  } else if (isFriend && QualifierLoc) {
2482  CXXScopeSpec SS;
2483  SS.Adopt(QualifierLoc);
2484  DC = SemaRef.computeDeclContext(SS);
2485  if (!DC) return nullptr;
2486  } else {
2487  DC = SemaRef.FindInstantiatedContext(D->getLocation(), D->getDeclContext(),
2488  TemplateArgs);
2489  }
2490 
2491  DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo
2492  = SemaRef.SubstDeclarationNameInfo(D->getNameInfo(), TemplateArgs);
2493 
2494  if (FunctionRewriteKind != RewriteKind::None)
2495  adjustForRewrite(FunctionRewriteKind, D, T, TInfo, NameInfo);
2496 
2497  FunctionDecl *Function;
2498  if (auto *DGuide = dyn_cast<CXXDeductionGuideDecl>(D)) {
2499  Function = CXXDeductionGuideDecl::Create(
2500  SemaRef.Context, DC, D->getInnerLocStart(),
2501  InstantiatedExplicitSpecifier, NameInfo, T, TInfo,
2502  D->getSourceRange().getEnd());
2503  if (DGuide->isCopyDeductionCandidate())
2504  cast<CXXDeductionGuideDecl>(Function)->setIsCopyDeductionCandidate();
2505  Function->setAccess(D->getAccess());
2506  } else {
2507  Function = FunctionDecl::Create(
2508  SemaRef.Context, DC, D->getInnerLocStart(), NameInfo, T, TInfo,
2509  D->getCanonicalDecl()->getStorageClass(), D->UsesFPIntrin(),
2510  D->isInlineSpecified(), D->hasWrittenPrototype(), D->getConstexprKind(),
2511  TrailingRequiresClause);
2512  Function->setRangeEnd(D->getSourceRange().getEnd());
2513  }
2514 
2515  if (D->isInlined())
2516  Function->setImplicitlyInline();
2517 
2518  if (QualifierLoc)
2519  Function->setQualifierInfo(QualifierLoc);
2520 
2521  if (D->isLocalExternDecl())
2522  Function->setLocalExternDecl();
2523 
2524  DeclContext *LexicalDC = Owner;
2525  if (!isFriend && D->isOutOfLine() && !D->isLocalExternDecl()) {
2526  assert(D->getDeclContext()->isFileContext());
2527  LexicalDC = D->getDeclContext();
2528  }
2529 
2530  Function->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
2531 
2532  // Attach the parameters
2533  for (unsigned P = 0; P < Params.size(); ++P)
2534  if (Params[P])
2535  Params[P]->setOwningFunction(Function);
2536  Function->setParams(Params);
2537 
2538  if (TrailingRequiresClause)
2539  Function->setTrailingRequiresClause(TrailingRequiresClause);
2540 
2541  if (TemplateParams) {
2542  // Our resulting instantiation is actually a function template, since we
2543  // are substituting only the outer template parameters. For example, given
2544  //
2545  // template<typename T>
2546  // struct X {
2547  // template<typename U> friend void f(T, U);
2548  // };
2549  //
2550  // X<int> x;
2551  //
2552  // We are instantiating the friend function template "f" within X<int>,
2553  // which means substituting int for T, but leaving "f" as a friend function
2554  // template.
2555  // Build the function template itself.
2556  FunctionTemplate = FunctionTemplateDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, DC,
2557  Function->getLocation(),
2558  Function->getDeclName(),
2559  TemplateParams, Function);
2560  Function->setDescribedFunctionTemplate(FunctionTemplate);
2561 
2562  FunctionTemplate->setLexicalDeclContext(LexicalDC);
2563 
2564  if (isFriend && D->isThisDeclarationADefinition()) {
2565  FunctionTemplate->setInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate(
2566  D->getDescribedFunctionTemplate());
2567  }
2568  } else if (FunctionTemplate) {
2569  // Record this function template specialization.
2570  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Innermost = TemplateArgs.getInnermost();
2571  Function->setFunctionTemplateSpecialization(FunctionTemplate,
2572  TemplateArgumentList::CreateCopy(SemaRef.Context,
2573  Innermost),
2574  /*InsertPos=*/nullptr);
2575  } else if (isFriend && D->isThisDeclarationADefinition()) {
2576  // Do not connect the friend to the template unless it's actually a
2577  // definition. We don't want non-template functions to be marked as being
2578  // template instantiations.
2579  Function->setInstantiationOfMemberFunction(D, TSK_ImplicitInstantiation);
2580  }
2581 
2582  if (isFriend) {
2583  Function->setObjectOfFriendDecl();
2584  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FT = Function->getDescribedFunctionTemplate())
2585  FT->setObjectOfFriendDecl();
2586  }
2587 
2588  if (InitFunctionInstantiation(Function, D))
2589  Function->setInvalidDecl();
2590 
2591  bool IsExplicitSpecialization = false;
2592 
2593  LookupResult Previous(
2594  SemaRef, Function->getDeclName(), SourceLocation(),
2595  D->isLocalExternDecl() ? Sema::LookupRedeclarationWithLinkage
2596  : Sema::LookupOrdinaryName,
2597  D->isLocalExternDecl() ? Sema::ForExternalRedeclaration
2598  : SemaRef.forRedeclarationInCurContext());
2599 
2600  if (DependentFunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *Info
2601  = D->getDependentSpecializationInfo()) {
2602  assert(isFriend && "non-friend has dependent specialization info?");
2603 
2604  // Instantiate the explicit template arguments.
2605  TemplateArgumentListInfo ExplicitArgs(Info->getLAngleLoc(),
2606  Info->getRAngleLoc());
2607  if (SemaRef.SubstTemplateArguments(Info->arguments(), TemplateArgs,
2608  ExplicitArgs))
2609  return nullptr;
2610 
2611  // Map the candidate templates to their instantiations.
2612  for (unsigned I = 0, E = Info->getNumTemplates(); I != E; ++I) {
2613  Decl *Temp = SemaRef.FindInstantiatedDecl(D->getLocation(),
2614  Info->getTemplate(I),
2615  TemplateArgs);
2616  if (!Temp) return nullptr;
2617 
2618  Previous.addDecl(cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(Temp));
2619  }
2620 
2621  if (SemaRef.CheckFunctionTemplateSpecialization(Function,
2622  &ExplicitArgs,
2623  Previous))
2624  Function->setInvalidDecl();
2625 
2626  IsExplicitSpecialization = true;
2627  } else if (const ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo *Info =
2628  D->getTemplateSpecializationArgsAsWritten()) {
2629  // The name of this function was written as a template-id.
2630  SemaRef.LookupQualifiedName(Previous, DC);
2631 
2632  // Instantiate the explicit template arguments.
2633  TemplateArgumentListInfo ExplicitArgs(Info->getLAngleLoc(),
2634  Info->getRAngleLoc());
2635  if (SemaRef.SubstTemplateArguments(Info->arguments(), TemplateArgs,
2636  ExplicitArgs))
2637  return nullptr;
2638 
2639  if (SemaRef.CheckFunctionTemplateSpecialization(Function,
2640  &ExplicitArgs,
2641  Previous))
2642  Function->setInvalidDecl();
2643 
2644  IsExplicitSpecialization = true;
2645  } else if (TemplateParams || !FunctionTemplate) {
2646  // Look only into the namespace where the friend would be declared to
2647  // find a previous declaration. This is the innermost enclosing namespace,
2648  // as described in ActOnFriendFunctionDecl.
2649  SemaRef.LookupQualifiedName(Previous, DC->getRedeclContext());
2650 
2651  // In C++, the previous declaration we find might be a tag type
2652  // (class or enum). In this case, the new declaration will hide the
2653  // tag type. Note that this does does not apply if we're declaring a
2654  // typedef (C++ [dcl.typedef]p4).
2655  if (Previous.isSingleTagDecl())
2656  Previous.clear();
2657 
2658  // Filter out previous declarations that don't match the scope. The only
2659  // effect this has is to remove declarations found in inline namespaces
2660  // for friend declarations with unqualified names.
2661  SemaRef.FilterLookupForScope(Previous, DC, /*Scope*/ nullptr,
2662  /*ConsiderLinkage*/ true,
2663  QualifierLoc.hasQualifier());
2664  }
2665 
2666  SemaRef.CheckFunctionDeclaration(/*Scope*/ nullptr, Function, Previous,
2667  IsExplicitSpecialization);
2668 
2669  // Check the template parameter list against the previous declaration. The
2670  // goal here is to pick up default arguments added since the friend was
2671  // declared; we know the template parameter lists match, since otherwise
2672  // we would not have picked this template as the previous declaration.
2673  if (isFriend && TemplateParams && FunctionTemplate->getPreviousDecl()) {
2674  SemaRef.CheckTemplateParameterList(
2675  TemplateParams,
2676  FunctionTemplate->getPreviousDecl()->getTemplateParameters(),
2677  Function->isThisDeclarationADefinition()
2678  ? Sema::TPC_FriendFunctionTemplateDefinition
2679  : Sema::TPC_FriendFunctionTemplate);
2680  }
2681 
2682  // If we're introducing a friend definition after the first use, trigger
2683  // instantiation.
2684  // FIXME: If this is a friend function template definition, we should check
2685  // to see if any specializations have been used.
2686  if (isFriend && D->isThisDeclarationADefinition() && Function->isUsed(false)) {
2687  if (MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo =
2688  Function->getMemberSpecializationInfo()) {
2689  if (MSInfo->getPointOfInstantiation().isInvalid()) {
2690  SourceLocation Loc = D->getLocation(); // FIXME
2691  MSInfo->setPointOfInstantiation(Loc);
2692  SemaRef.PendingLocalImplicitInstantiations.push_back(
2693  std::make_pair(Function, Loc));
2694  }
2695  }
2696  }
2697 
2698  if (D->isExplicitlyDefaulted()) {
2699  if (SubstDefaultedFunction(Function, D))
2700  return nullptr;
2701  }
2702  if (D->isDeleted())
2703  SemaRef.SetDeclDeleted(Function, D->getLocation());
2704 
2705  NamedDecl *PrincipalDecl =
2706  (TemplateParams ? cast<NamedDecl>(FunctionTemplate) : Function);
2707 
2708  // If this declaration lives in a different context from its lexical context,
2709  // add it to the corresponding lookup table.
2710  if (isFriend ||
2711  (Function->isLocalExternDecl() && !Function->getPreviousDecl()))
2712  DC->makeDeclVisibleInContext(PrincipalDecl);
2713 
2714  if (Function->isOverloadedOperator() && !DC->isRecord() &&
2715  PrincipalDecl->isInIdentifierNamespace(Decl::IDNS_Ordinary))
2716  PrincipalDecl->setNonMemberOperator();
2717 
2718  return Function;
2719 }
2720 
2721 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitCXXMethodDecl(
2722  CXXMethodDecl *D, TemplateParameterList *TemplateParams,
2723  Optional<const ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo *> ClassScopeSpecializationArgs,
2724  RewriteKind FunctionRewriteKind) {
2725  FunctionTemplateDecl *FunctionTemplate = D->getDescribedFunctionTemplate();
2726  if (FunctionTemplate && !TemplateParams) {
2727  // We are creating a function template specialization from a function
2728  // template. Check whether there is already a function template
2729  // specialization for this particular set of template arguments.
2730  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Innermost = TemplateArgs.getInnermost();
2731 
2732  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
2733  FunctionDecl *SpecFunc
2734  = FunctionTemplate->findSpecialization(Innermost, InsertPos);
2735 
2736  // If we already have a function template specialization, return it.
2737  if (SpecFunc)
2738  return SpecFunc;
2739  }
2740 
2741  bool isFriend;
2742  if (FunctionTemplate)
2743  isFriend = (FunctionTemplate->getFriendObjectKind() != Decl::FOK_None);
2744  else
2745  isFriend = (D->getFriendObjectKind() != Decl::FOK_None);
2746 
2747  bool MergeWithParentScope = (TemplateParams != nullptr) ||
2748  !(isa<Decl>(Owner) &&
2749  cast<Decl>(Owner)->isDefinedOutsideFunctionOrMethod());
2750  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(SemaRef, MergeWithParentScope);
2751 
2752  // Instantiate enclosing template arguments for friends.
2753  SmallVector<TemplateParameterList *, 4> TempParamLists;
2754  unsigned NumTempParamLists = 0;
2755  if (isFriend && (NumTempParamLists = D->getNumTemplateParameterLists())) {
2756  TempParamLists.resize(NumTempParamLists);
2757  for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumTempParamLists; ++I) {
2758  TemplateParameterList *TempParams = D->getTemplateParameterList(I);
2759  TemplateParameterList *InstParams = SubstTemplateParams(TempParams);
2760  if (!InstParams)
2761  return nullptr;
2762  TempParamLists[I] = InstParams;
2763  }
2764  }
2765 
2766  ExplicitSpecifier InstantiatedExplicitSpecifier =
2767  instantiateExplicitSpecifier(SemaRef, TemplateArgs,
2768  ExplicitSpecifier::getFromDecl(D), D);
2769  if (InstantiatedExplicitSpecifier.isInvalid())
2770  return nullptr;
2771 
2772  // Implicit destructors/constructors created for local classes in
2773  // DeclareImplicit* (see SemaDeclCXX.cpp) might not have an associated TSI.
2774  // Unfortunately there isn't enough context in those functions to
2775  // conditionally populate the TSI without breaking non-template related use
2776  // cases. Populate TSIs prior to calling SubstFunctionType to make sure we get
2777  // a proper transformation.
2778  if (cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D->getParent())->isLambda() &&
2779  !D->getTypeSourceInfo() &&
2780  isa<CXXConstructorDecl, CXXDestructorDecl>(D)) {
2781  TypeSourceInfo *TSI =
2782  SemaRef.Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(D->getType());
2783  D->setTypeSourceInfo(TSI);
2784  }
2785 
2786  SmallVector<ParmVarDecl *, 4> Params;
2787  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = SubstFunctionType(D, Params);
2788  if (!TInfo)
2789  return nullptr;
2790  QualType T = adjustFunctionTypeForInstantiation(SemaRef.Context, D, TInfo);
2791 
2792  if (TemplateParams && TemplateParams->size()) {
2793  auto *LastParam =
2794  dyn_cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(TemplateParams->asArray().back());
2795  if (LastParam && LastParam->isImplicit() &&
2796  LastParam->hasTypeConstraint()) {
2797  // In abbreviated templates, the type-constraints of invented template
2798  // type parameters are instantiated with the function type, invalidating
2799  // the TemplateParameterList which relied on the template type parameter
2800  // not having a type constraint. Recreate the TemplateParameterList with
2801  // the updated parameter list.
2802  TemplateParams = TemplateParameterList::Create(
2803  SemaRef.Context, TemplateParams->getTemplateLoc(),
2804  TemplateParams->getLAngleLoc(), TemplateParams->asArray(),
2805  TemplateParams->getRAngleLoc(), TemplateParams->getRequiresClause());
2806  }
2807  }
2808 
2809  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc = D->getQualifierLoc();
2810  if (QualifierLoc) {
2811  QualifierLoc = SemaRef.SubstNestedNameSpecifierLoc(QualifierLoc,
2812  TemplateArgs);
2813  if (!QualifierLoc)
2814  return nullptr;
2815  }
2816 
2817  // FIXME: Concepts: Do not substitute into constraint expressions
2818  Expr *TrailingRequiresClause = D->getTrailingRequiresClause();
2819  if (TrailingRequiresClause) {
2820  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext ConstantEvaluated(
2821  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
2822  auto *ThisContext = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(Owner);
2823  Sema::CXXThisScopeRAII ThisScope(SemaRef, ThisContext,
2824  D->getMethodQualifiers(), ThisContext);
2825  ExprResult SubstRC = SemaRef.SubstExpr(TrailingRequiresClause,
2826  TemplateArgs);
2827  if (SubstRC.isInvalid())
2828  return nullptr;
2829  TrailingRequiresClause = SubstRC.get();
2830  if (!SemaRef.CheckConstraintExpression(TrailingRequiresClause))
2831  return nullptr;
2832  }
2833 
2834  DeclContext *DC = Owner;
2835  if (isFriend) {
2836  if (QualifierLoc) {
2837  CXXScopeSpec SS;
2838  SS.Adopt(QualifierLoc);
2839  DC = SemaRef.computeDeclContext(SS);
2840 
2841  if (DC && SemaRef.RequireCompleteDeclContext(SS, DC))
2842  return nullptr;
2843  } else {
2844  DC = SemaRef.FindInstantiatedContext(D->getLocation(),
2845  D->getDeclContext(),
2846  TemplateArgs);
2847  }
2848  if (!DC) return nullptr;
2849  }
2850 
2851  DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo
2852  = SemaRef.SubstDeclarationNameInfo(D->getNameInfo(), TemplateArgs);
2853 
2854  if (FunctionRewriteKind != RewriteKind::None)
2855  adjustForRewrite(FunctionRewriteKind, D, T, TInfo, NameInfo);
2856 
2857  // Build the instantiated method declaration.
2858  CXXRecordDecl *Record = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DC);
2859  CXXMethodDecl *Method = nullptr;
2860 
2861  SourceLocation StartLoc = D->getInnerLocStart();
2862  if (CXXConstructorDecl *Constructor = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(D)) {
2863  Method = CXXConstructorDecl::Create(
2864  SemaRef.Context, Record, StartLoc, NameInfo, T, TInfo,
2865  InstantiatedExplicitSpecifier, Constructor->UsesFPIntrin(),
2866  Constructor->isInlineSpecified(), false,
2867  Constructor->getConstexprKind(), InheritedConstructor(),
2868  TrailingRequiresClause);
2869  Method->setRangeEnd(Constructor->getEndLoc());
2870  } else if (CXXDestructorDecl *Destructor = dyn_cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(D)) {
2871  Method = CXXDestructorDecl::Create(
2872  SemaRef.Context, Record, StartLoc, NameInfo, T, TInfo,
2873  Destructor->UsesFPIntrin(), Destructor->isInlineSpecified(), false,
2874  Destructor->getConstexprKind(), TrailingRequiresClause);
2875  Method->setRangeEnd(Destructor->getEndLoc());
2876  Method->setDeclName(SemaRef.Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXDestructorName(
2877  SemaRef.Context.getCanonicalType(
2878  SemaRef.Context.getTypeDeclType(Record))));
2879  } else if (CXXConversionDecl *Conversion = dyn_cast<CXXConversionDecl>(D)) {
2880  Method = CXXConversionDecl::Create(
2881  SemaRef.Context, Record, StartLoc, NameInfo, T, TInfo,
2882  Conversion->UsesFPIntrin(), Conversion->isInlineSpecified(),
2883  InstantiatedExplicitSpecifier, Conversion->getConstexprKind(),
2884  Conversion->getEndLoc(), TrailingRequiresClause);
2885  } else {
2886  StorageClass SC = D->isStatic() ? SC_Static : SC_None;
2887  Method = CXXMethodDecl::Create(
2888  SemaRef.Context, Record, StartLoc, NameInfo, T, TInfo, SC,
2889  D->UsesFPIntrin(), D->isInlineSpecified(), D->getConstexprKind(),
2890  D->getEndLoc(), TrailingRequiresClause);
2891  }
2892 
2893  if (D->isInlined())
2894  Method->setImplicitlyInline();
2895 
2896  if (QualifierLoc)
2897  Method->setQualifierInfo(QualifierLoc);
2898 
2899  if (TemplateParams) {
2900  // Our resulting instantiation is actually a function template, since we
2901  // are substituting only the outer template parameters. For example, given
2902  //
2903  // template<typename T>
2904  // struct X {
2905  // template<typename U> void f(T, U);
2906  // };
2907  //
2908  // X<int> x;
2909  //
2910  // We are instantiating the member template "f" within X<int>, which means
2911  // substituting int for T, but leaving "f" as a member function template.
2912  // Build the function template itself.
2913  FunctionTemplate = FunctionTemplateDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, Record,
2914  Method->getLocation(),
2915  Method->getDeclName(),
2916  TemplateParams, Method);
2917  if (isFriend) {
2918  FunctionTemplate->setLexicalDeclContext(Owner);
2919  FunctionTemplate->setObjectOfFriendDecl();
2920  } else if (D->isOutOfLine())
2921  FunctionTemplate->setLexicalDeclContext(D->getLexicalDeclContext());
2922  Method->setDescribedFunctionTemplate(FunctionTemplate);
2923  } else if (FunctionTemplate) {
2924  // Record this function template specialization.
2925  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Innermost = TemplateArgs.getInnermost();
2926  Method->setFunctionTemplateSpecialization(FunctionTemplate,
2927  TemplateArgumentList::CreateCopy(SemaRef.Context,
2928  Innermost),
2929  /*InsertPos=*/nullptr);
2930  } else if (!isFriend) {
2931  // Record that this is an instantiation of a member function.
2932  Method->setInstantiationOfMemberFunction(D, TSK_ImplicitInstantiation);
2933  }
2934 
2935  // If we are instantiating a member function defined
2936  // out-of-line, the instantiation will have the same lexical
2937  // context (which will be a namespace scope) as the template.
2938  if (isFriend) {
2939  if (NumTempParamLists)
2940  Method->setTemplateParameterListsInfo(
2941  SemaRef.Context,
2942  llvm::makeArrayRef(TempParamLists.data(), NumTempParamLists));
2943 
2944  Method->setLexicalDeclContext(Owner);
2945  Method->setObjectOfFriendDecl();
2946  } else if (D->isOutOfLine())
2947  Method->setLexicalDeclContext(D->getLexicalDeclContext());
2948 
2949  // Attach the parameters
2950  for (unsigned P = 0; P < Params.size(); ++P)
2951  Params[P]->setOwningFunction(Method);
2952  Method->setParams(Params);
2953 
2954  if (InitMethodInstantiation(Method, D))
2955  Method->setInvalidDecl();
2956 
2957  LookupResult Previous(SemaRef, NameInfo, Sema::LookupOrdinaryName,
2958  Sema::ForExternalRedeclaration);
2959 
2960  bool IsExplicitSpecialization = false;
2961 
2962  // If the name of this function was written as a template-id, instantiate
2963  // the explicit template arguments.
2964  if (DependentFunctionTemplateSpecializationInfo *Info
2965  = D->getDependentSpecializationInfo()) {
2966  assert(isFriend && "non-friend has dependent specialization info?");
2967 
2968  // Instantiate the explicit template arguments.
2969  TemplateArgumentListInfo ExplicitArgs(Info->getLAngleLoc(),
2970  Info->getRAngleLoc());
2971  if (SemaRef.SubstTemplateArguments(Info->arguments(), TemplateArgs,
2972  ExplicitArgs))
2973  return nullptr;
2974 
2975  // Map the candidate templates to their instantiations.
2976  for (unsigned I = 0, E = Info->getNumTemplates(); I != E; ++I) {
2977  Decl *Temp = SemaRef.FindInstantiatedDecl(D->getLocation(),
2978  Info->getTemplate(I),
2979  TemplateArgs);
2980  if (!Temp) return nullptr;
2981 
2982  Previous.addDecl(cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(Temp));
2983  }
2984 
2985  if (SemaRef.CheckFunctionTemplateSpecialization(Method,
2986  &ExplicitArgs,
2987  Previous))
2988  Method->setInvalidDecl();
2989 
2990  IsExplicitSpecialization = true;
2991  } else if (const ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo *Info =
2992  ClassScopeSpecializationArgs.getValueOr(
2993  D->getTemplateSpecializationArgsAsWritten())) {
2994  SemaRef.LookupQualifiedName(Previous, DC);
2995 
2996  TemplateArgumentListInfo ExplicitArgs(Info->getLAngleLoc(),
2997  Info->getRAngleLoc());
2998  if (SemaRef.SubstTemplateArguments(Info->arguments(), TemplateArgs,
2999  ExplicitArgs))
3000  return nullptr;
3001 
3002  if (SemaRef.CheckFunctionTemplateSpecialization(Method,
3003  &ExplicitArgs,
3004  Previous))
3005  Method->setInvalidDecl();
3006 
3007  IsExplicitSpecialization = true;
3008  } else if (ClassScopeSpecializationArgs) {
3009  // Class-scope explicit specialization written without explicit template
3010  // arguments.
3011  SemaRef.LookupQualifiedName(Previous, DC);
3012  if (SemaRef.CheckFunctionTemplateSpecialization(Method, nullptr, Previous))
3013  Method->setInvalidDecl();
3014 
3015  IsExplicitSpecialization = true;
3016  } else if (!FunctionTemplate || TemplateParams || isFriend) {
3017  SemaRef.LookupQualifiedName(Previous, Record);
3018 
3019  // In C++, the previous declaration we find might be a tag type
3020  // (class or enum). In this case, the new declaration will hide the
3021  // tag type. Note that this does does not apply if we're declaring a
3022  // typedef (C++ [dcl.typedef]p4).
3023  if (Previous.isSingleTagDecl())
3024  Previous.clear();
3025  }
3026 
3027  SemaRef.CheckFunctionDeclaration(nullptr, Method, Previous,
3028  IsExplicitSpecialization);
3029 
3030  if (D->isPure())
3031  SemaRef.CheckPureMethod(Method, SourceRange());
3032 
3033  // Propagate access. For a non-friend declaration, the access is
3034  // whatever we're propagating from. For a friend, it should be the
3035  // previous declaration we just found.
3036  if (isFriend && Method->getPreviousDecl())
3037  Method->setAccess(Method->getPreviousDecl()->getAccess());
3038  else
3039  Method->setAccess(D->getAccess());
3040  if (FunctionTemplate)
3041  FunctionTemplate->setAccess(Method->getAccess());
3042 
3043  SemaRef.CheckOverrideControl(Method);
3044  SemaRef.CheckVirtualSYCLAddIRAttributesFunctionAttr(Method);
3045 
3046  // If a function is defined as defaulted or deleted, mark it as such now.
3047  if (D->isExplicitlyDefaulted()) {
3048  if (SubstDefaultedFunction(Method, D))
3049  return nullptr;
3050  }
3051  if (D->isDeletedAsWritten())
3052  SemaRef.SetDeclDeleted(Method, Method->getLocation());
3053 
3054  // If this is an explicit specialization, mark the implicitly-instantiated
3055  // template specialization as being an explicit specialization too.
3056  // FIXME: Is this necessary?
3057  if (IsExplicitSpecialization && !isFriend)
3058  SemaRef.CompleteMemberSpecialization(Method, Previous);
3059 
3060  // If there's a function template, let our caller handle it.
3061  if (FunctionTemplate) {
3062  // do nothing
3063 
3064  // Don't hide a (potentially) valid declaration with an invalid one.
3065  } else if (Method->isInvalidDecl() && !Previous.empty()) {
3066  // do nothing
3067 
3068  // Otherwise, check access to friends and make them visible.
3069  } else if (isFriend) {
3070  // We only need to re-check access for methods which we didn't
3071  // manage to match during parsing.
3072  if (!D->getPreviousDecl())
3073  SemaRef.CheckFriendAccess(Method);
3074 
3075  Record->makeDeclVisibleInContext(Method);
3076 
3077  // Otherwise, add the declaration. We don't need to do this for
3078  // class-scope specializations because we'll have matched them with
3079  // the appropriate template.
3080  } else {
3081  Owner->addDecl(Method);
3082  }
3083 
3084  // PR17480: Honor the used attribute to instantiate member function
3085  // definitions
3086  if (Method->hasAttr<UsedAttr>()) {
3087  if (const auto *A = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Owner)) {
3088  SourceLocation Loc;
3089  if (const MemberSpecializationInfo *MSInfo =
3090  A->getMemberSpecializationInfo())
3091  Loc = MSInfo->getPointOfInstantiation();
3092  else if (const auto *Spec = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(A))
3093  Loc = Spec->getPointOfInstantiation();
3094  SemaRef.MarkFunctionReferenced(Loc, Method);
3095  }
3096  }
3097 
3098  return Method;
3099 }

3103 }

3105 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitCXXDestructorDecl(CXXDestructorDecl *D) {

3113 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitParmVarDecl(ParmVarDecl *D) {
