3117 
3118 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitTemplateTypeParmDecl(
3119  TemplateTypeParmDecl *D) {
3120  assert(D->getTypeForDecl()->isTemplateTypeParmType());
3121 
3122  Optional<unsigned> NumExpanded;
3123 
3124  if (const TypeConstraint *TC = D->getTypeConstraint()) {
3125  if (D->isPackExpansion() && !D->isExpandedParameterPack()) {
3126  assert(TC->getTemplateArgsAsWritten() &&
3127  "type parameter can only be an expansion when explicit arguments "
3128  "are specified");
3129  // The template type parameter pack's type is a pack expansion of types.
3130  // Determine whether we need to expand this parameter pack into separate
3131  // types.
3132  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
3133  for (auto &ArgLoc : TC->getTemplateArgsAsWritten()->arguments())
3134  SemaRef.collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(ArgLoc, Unexpanded);
3135 
3136  // Determine whether the set of unexpanded parameter packs can and should
3137  // be expanded.
3138  bool Expand = true;
3139  bool RetainExpansion = false;
3140  if (SemaRef.CheckParameterPacksForExpansion(
3141  cast<CXXFoldExpr>(TC->getImmediatelyDeclaredConstraint())
3142  ->getEllipsisLoc(),
3143  SourceRange(TC->getConceptNameLoc(),
3144  TC->hasExplicitTemplateArgs() ?
3145  TC->getTemplateArgsAsWritten()->getRAngleLoc() :
3146  TC->getConceptNameInfo().getEndLoc()),
3147  Unexpanded, TemplateArgs, Expand, RetainExpansion, NumExpanded))
3148  return nullptr;
3149  }
3150  }
3151 
3152  TemplateTypeParmDecl *Inst = TemplateTypeParmDecl::Create(
3153  SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getBeginLoc(), D->getLocation(),
3154  D->getDepth() - TemplateArgs.getNumSubstitutedLevels(), D->getIndex(),
3155  D->getIdentifier(), D->wasDeclaredWithTypename(), D->isParameterPack(),
3156  D->hasTypeConstraint(), NumExpanded);
3157 
3158  Inst->setAccess(AS_public);
3159  Inst->setImplicit(D->isImplicit());
3160  if (auto *TC = D->getTypeConstraint()) {
3161  if (!D->isImplicit()) {
3162  // Invented template parameter type constraints will be instantiated with
3163  // the corresponding auto-typed parameter as it might reference other
3164  // parameters.
3165 
3166  // TODO: Concepts: do not instantiate the constraint (delayed constraint
3167  // substitution)
3168  if (SemaRef.SubstTypeConstraint(Inst, TC, TemplateArgs))
3169  return nullptr;
3170  }
3171  }
3172  if (D->hasDefaultArgument() && !D->defaultArgumentWasInherited()) {
3173  TypeSourceInfo *InstantiatedDefaultArg =
3174  SemaRef.SubstType(D->getDefaultArgumentInfo(), TemplateArgs,
3175  D->getDefaultArgumentLoc(), D->getDeclName());
3176  if (InstantiatedDefaultArg)
3177  Inst->setDefaultArgument(InstantiatedDefaultArg);
3178  }
3179 
3180  // Introduce this template parameter's instantiation into the instantiation
3181  // scope.
3182  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(D, Inst);
3183 
3184  return Inst;
3185 }
3186 
3187 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitNonTypeTemplateParmDecl(
3188  NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *D) {
3189  // Substitute into the type of the non-type template parameter.
3190  TypeLoc TL = D->getTypeSourceInfo()->getTypeLoc();
3191  SmallVector<TypeSourceInfo *, 4> ExpandedParameterPackTypesAsWritten;
3192  SmallVector<QualType, 4> ExpandedParameterPackTypes;
3193  bool IsExpandedParameterPack = false;
3194  TypeSourceInfo *DI;
3195  QualType T;
3196  bool Invalid = false;
3197 
3198  if (D->isExpandedParameterPack()) {
3199  // The non-type template parameter pack is an already-expanded pack
3200  // expansion of types. Substitute into each of the expanded types.
3201  ExpandedParameterPackTypes.reserve(D->getNumExpansionTypes());
3202  ExpandedParameterPackTypesAsWritten.reserve(D->getNumExpansionTypes());
3203  for (unsigned I = 0, N = D->getNumExpansionTypes(); I != N; ++I) {
3204  TypeSourceInfo *NewDI =
3205  SemaRef.SubstType(D->getExpansionTypeSourceInfo(I), TemplateArgs,
3206  D->getLocation(), D->getDeclName());
3207  if (!NewDI)
3208  return nullptr;
3209 
3210  QualType NewT =
3211  SemaRef.CheckNonTypeTemplateParameterType(NewDI, D->getLocation());
3212  if (NewT.isNull())
3213  return nullptr;
3214 
3215  ExpandedParameterPackTypesAsWritten.push_back(NewDI);
3216  ExpandedParameterPackTypes.push_back(NewT);
3217  }
3218 
3219  IsExpandedParameterPack = true;
3220  DI = D->getTypeSourceInfo();
3221  T = DI->getType();
3222  } else if (D->isPackExpansion()) {
3223  // The non-type template parameter pack's type is a pack expansion of types.
3224  // Determine whether we need to expand this parameter pack into separate
3225  // types.
3226  PackExpansionTypeLoc Expansion = TL.castAs<PackExpansionTypeLoc>();
3227  TypeLoc Pattern = Expansion.getPatternLoc();
3228  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
3229  SemaRef.collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(Pattern, Unexpanded);
3230 
3231  // Determine whether the set of unexpanded parameter packs can and should
3232  // be expanded.
3233  bool Expand = true;
3234  bool RetainExpansion = false;
3235  Optional<unsigned> OrigNumExpansions
3236  = Expansion.getTypePtr()->getNumExpansions();
3237  Optional<unsigned> NumExpansions = OrigNumExpansions;
3238  if (SemaRef.CheckParameterPacksForExpansion(Expansion.getEllipsisLoc(),
3239  Pattern.getSourceRange(),
3240  Unexpanded,
3241  TemplateArgs,
3242  Expand, RetainExpansion,
3243  NumExpansions))
3244  return nullptr;
3245 
3246  if (Expand) {
3247  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
3248  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(SemaRef, I);
3249  TypeSourceInfo *NewDI = SemaRef.SubstType(Pattern, TemplateArgs,
3250  D->getLocation(),
3251  D->getDeclName());
3252  if (!NewDI)
3253  return nullptr;
3254 
3255  QualType NewT =
3256  SemaRef.CheckNonTypeTemplateParameterType(NewDI, D->getLocation());
3257  if (NewT.isNull())
3258  return nullptr;
3259 
3260  ExpandedParameterPackTypesAsWritten.push_back(NewDI);
3261  ExpandedParameterPackTypes.push_back(NewT);
3262  }
3263 
3264  // Note that we have an expanded parameter pack. The "type" of this
3265  // expanded parameter pack is the original expansion type, but callers
3266  // will end up using the expanded parameter pack types for type-checking.
3267  IsExpandedParameterPack = true;
3268  DI = D->getTypeSourceInfo();
3269  T = DI->getType();
3270  } else {
3271  // We cannot fully expand the pack expansion now, so substitute into the
3272  // pattern and create a new pack expansion type.
3273  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(SemaRef, -1);
3274  TypeSourceInfo *NewPattern = SemaRef.SubstType(Pattern, TemplateArgs,
3275  D->getLocation(),
3276  D->getDeclName());
3277  if (!NewPattern)
3278  return nullptr;
3279 
3280  SemaRef.CheckNonTypeTemplateParameterType(NewPattern, D->getLocation());
3281  DI = SemaRef.CheckPackExpansion(NewPattern, Expansion.getEllipsisLoc(),
3282  NumExpansions);
3283  if (!DI)
3284  return nullptr;
3285 
3286  T = DI->getType();
3287  }
3288  } else {
3289  // Simple case: substitution into a parameter that is not a parameter pack.
3290  DI = SemaRef.SubstType(D->getTypeSourceInfo(), TemplateArgs,
3291  D->getLocation(), D->getDeclName());
3292  if (!DI)
3293  return nullptr;
3294 
3295  // Check that this type is acceptable for a non-type template parameter.
3296  T = SemaRef.CheckNonTypeTemplateParameterType(DI, D->getLocation());
3297  if (T.isNull()) {
3298  T = SemaRef.Context.IntTy;
3299  Invalid = true;
3300  }
3301  }
3302 
3303  NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *Param;
3304  if (IsExpandedParameterPack)
3305  Param = NonTypeTemplateParmDecl::Create(
3306  SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getInnerLocStart(), D->getLocation(),
3307  D->getDepth() - TemplateArgs.getNumSubstitutedLevels(),
3308  D->getPosition(), D->getIdentifier(), T, DI, ExpandedParameterPackTypes,
3309  ExpandedParameterPackTypesAsWritten);
3310  else
3311  Param = NonTypeTemplateParmDecl::Create(
3312  SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getInnerLocStart(), D->getLocation(),
3313  D->getDepth() - TemplateArgs.getNumSubstitutedLevels(),
3314  D->getPosition(), D->getIdentifier(), T, D->isParameterPack(), DI);
3315 
3316  if (AutoTypeLoc AutoLoc = DI->getTypeLoc().getContainedAutoTypeLoc())
3317  if (AutoLoc.isConstrained())
3318  if (SemaRef.AttachTypeConstraint(
3319  AutoLoc, Param,
3320  IsExpandedParameterPack
3321  ? DI->getTypeLoc().getAs<PackExpansionTypeLoc>()
3322  .getEllipsisLoc()
3323  : SourceLocation()))
3324  Invalid = true;
3325 
3326  Param->setAccess(AS_public);
3327  Param->setImplicit(D->isImplicit());
3328  if (Invalid)
3329  Param->setInvalidDecl();
3330 
3331  if (D->hasDefaultArgument() && !D->defaultArgumentWasInherited()) {
3332  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext ConstantEvaluated(
3333  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::ConstantEvaluated);
3334  ExprResult Value = SemaRef.SubstExpr(D->getDefaultArgument(), TemplateArgs);
3335  if (!Value.isInvalid())
3336  Param->setDefaultArgument(Value.get());
3337  }
3338 
3339  // Introduce this template parameter's instantiation into the instantiation
3340  // scope.
3341  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(D, Param);
3342  return Param;
3343 }
3344 
3345 static void collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(
3346  Sema &S,
3347  TemplateParameterList *Params,
3348  SmallVectorImpl<UnexpandedParameterPack> &Unexpanded) {
3349  for (const auto &P : *Params) {
3350  if (P->isTemplateParameterPack())
3351  continue;
3352  if (NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *NTTP = dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(P))
3353  S.collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(NTTP->getTypeSourceInfo()->getTypeLoc(),
3354  Unexpanded);
3355  if (TemplateTemplateParmDecl *TTP = dyn_cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(P))
3356  collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(S, TTP->getTemplateParameters(),
3357  Unexpanded);
3358  }
3359 }
3360 
3361 Decl *
3362 TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitTemplateTemplateParmDecl(
3363  TemplateTemplateParmDecl *D) {
3364  // Instantiate the template parameter list of the template template parameter.
3365  TemplateParameterList *TempParams = D->getTemplateParameters();
3366  TemplateParameterList *InstParams;
3367  SmallVector<TemplateParameterList*, 8> ExpandedParams;
3368 
3369  bool IsExpandedParameterPack = false;
3370 
3371  if (D->isExpandedParameterPack()) {
3372  // The template template parameter pack is an already-expanded pack
3373  // expansion of template parameters. Substitute into each of the expanded
3374  // parameters.
3375  ExpandedParams.reserve(D->getNumExpansionTemplateParameters());
3376  for (unsigned I = 0, N = D->getNumExpansionTemplateParameters();
3377  I != N; ++I) {
3378  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(SemaRef);
3379  TemplateParameterList *Expansion =
3380  SubstTemplateParams(D->getExpansionTemplateParameters(I));
3381  if (!Expansion)
3382  return nullptr;
3383  ExpandedParams.push_back(Expansion);
3384  }
3385 
3386  IsExpandedParameterPack = true;
3387  InstParams = TempParams;
3388  } else if (D->isPackExpansion()) {
3389  // The template template parameter pack expands to a pack of template
3390  // template parameters. Determine whether we need to expand this parameter
3391  // pack into separate parameters.
3392  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
3393  collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(SemaRef, D->getTemplateParameters(),
3394  Unexpanded);
3395 
3396  // Determine whether the set of unexpanded parameter packs can and should
3397  // be expanded.
3398  bool Expand = true;
3399  bool RetainExpansion = false;
3400  Optional<unsigned> NumExpansions;
3401  if (SemaRef.CheckParameterPacksForExpansion(D->getLocation(),
3402  TempParams->getSourceRange(),
3403  Unexpanded,
3404  TemplateArgs,
3405  Expand, RetainExpansion,
3406  NumExpansions))
3407  return nullptr;
3408 
3409  if (Expand) {
3410  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
3411  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(SemaRef, I);
3412  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(SemaRef);
3413  TemplateParameterList *Expansion = SubstTemplateParams(TempParams);
3414  if (!Expansion)
3415  return nullptr;
3416  ExpandedParams.push_back(Expansion);
3417  }
3418 
3419  // Note that we have an expanded parameter pack. The "type" of this
3420  // expanded parameter pack is the original expansion type, but callers
3421  // will end up using the expanded parameter pack types for type-checking.
3422  IsExpandedParameterPack = true;
3423  InstParams = TempParams;
3424  } else {
3425  // We cannot fully expand the pack expansion now, so just substitute
3426  // into the pattern.
3427  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(SemaRef, -1);
3428 
3429  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(SemaRef);
3430  InstParams = SubstTemplateParams(TempParams);
3431  if (!InstParams)
3432  return nullptr;
3433  }
3434  } else {
3435  // Perform the actual substitution of template parameters within a new,
3436  // local instantiation scope.
3437  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(SemaRef);
3438  InstParams = SubstTemplateParams(TempParams);
3439  if (!InstParams)
3440  return nullptr;
3441  }
3442 
3443  // Build the template template parameter.
3444  TemplateTemplateParmDecl *Param;
3445  if (IsExpandedParameterPack)
3446  Param = TemplateTemplateParmDecl::Create(
3447  SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getLocation(),
3448  D->getDepth() - TemplateArgs.getNumSubstitutedLevels(),
3449  D->getPosition(), D->getIdentifier(), InstParams, ExpandedParams);
3450  else
3451  Param = TemplateTemplateParmDecl::Create(
3452  SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getLocation(),
3453  D->getDepth() - TemplateArgs.getNumSubstitutedLevels(),
3454  D->getPosition(), D->isParameterPack(), D->getIdentifier(), InstParams);
3455  if (D->hasDefaultArgument() && !D->defaultArgumentWasInherited()) {
3456  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc =
3457  D->getDefaultArgument().getTemplateQualifierLoc();
3458  QualifierLoc =
3459  SemaRef.SubstNestedNameSpecifierLoc(QualifierLoc, TemplateArgs);
3460  TemplateName TName = SemaRef.SubstTemplateName(
3461  QualifierLoc, D->getDefaultArgument().getArgument().getAsTemplate(),
3462  D->getDefaultArgument().getTemplateNameLoc(), TemplateArgs);
3463  if (!TName.isNull())
3464  Param->setDefaultArgument(
3465  SemaRef.Context,
3466  TemplateArgumentLoc(SemaRef.Context, TemplateArgument(TName),
3467  D->getDefaultArgument().getTemplateQualifierLoc(),
3468  D->getDefaultArgument().getTemplateNameLoc()));
3469  }
3470  Param->setAccess(AS_public);
3471  Param->setImplicit(D->isImplicit());
3472 
3473  // Introduce this template parameter's instantiation into the instantiation
3474  // scope.
3475  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(D, Param);
3476 
3477  return Param;
3478 }

3480 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitUsingDirectiveDecl(UsingDirectiveDecl *D) {
3481  // Using directives are never dependent (and never contain any types or
3482  // expressions), so they require no explicit instantiation work.
3483 
3484  UsingDirectiveDecl *Inst
3485  = UsingDirectiveDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getLocation(),
3486  D->getNamespaceKeyLocation(),
3487  D->getQualifierLoc(),
3488  D->getIdentLocation(),
3489  D->getNominatedNamespace(),
3490  D->getCommonAncestor());
3491 
3492  // Add the using directive to its declaration context
3493  // only if this is not a function or method.
3494  if (!Owner->isFunctionOrMethod())
3495  Owner->addDecl(Inst);
3496 
3497  return Inst;
3498 }
3499 
3500 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitBaseUsingDecls(BaseUsingDecl *D,
3501  BaseUsingDecl *Inst,
3502  LookupResult *Lookup) {
3503 
3504  bool isFunctionScope = Owner->isFunctionOrMethod();
3505 
3506  for (auto *Shadow : D->shadows()) {
3507  // FIXME: UsingShadowDecl doesn't preserve its immediate target, so
3508  // reconstruct it in the case where it matters. Hm, can we extract it from
3509  // the DeclSpec when parsing and save it in the UsingDecl itself?
3510  NamedDecl *OldTarget = Shadow->getTargetDecl();
3511  if (auto *CUSD = dyn_cast<ConstructorUsingShadowDecl>(Shadow))
3512  if (auto *BaseShadow = CUSD->getNominatedBaseClassShadowDecl())
3513  OldTarget = BaseShadow;
3514 
3515  NamedDecl *InstTarget = nullptr;
3516  if (auto *EmptyD =
3517  dyn_cast<UnresolvedUsingIfExistsDecl>(Shadow->getTargetDecl())) {
3518  InstTarget = UnresolvedUsingIfExistsDecl::Create(
3519  SemaRef.Context, Owner, EmptyD->getLocation(), EmptyD->getDeclName());
3520  } else {
3521  InstTarget = cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(SemaRef.FindInstantiatedDecl(
3522  Shadow->getLocation(), OldTarget, TemplateArgs));
3523  }
3524  if (!InstTarget)
3525  return nullptr;
3526 
3527  UsingShadowDecl *PrevDecl = nullptr;
3528  if (Lookup &&
3529  SemaRef.CheckUsingShadowDecl(Inst, InstTarget, *Lookup, PrevDecl))
3530  continue;
3531 
3532  if (UsingShadowDecl *OldPrev = getPreviousDeclForInstantiation(Shadow))
3533  PrevDecl = cast_or_null<UsingShadowDecl>(SemaRef.FindInstantiatedDecl(
3534  Shadow->getLocation(), OldPrev, TemplateArgs));
3535 
3536  UsingShadowDecl *InstShadow = SemaRef.BuildUsingShadowDecl(
3537  /*Scope*/ nullptr, Inst, InstTarget, PrevDecl);
3538  SemaRef.Context.setInstantiatedFromUsingShadowDecl(InstShadow, Shadow);
3539 
3540  if (isFunctionScope)
3541  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(Shadow, InstShadow);
3542  }
3543 
3544  return Inst;
3545 }
3546 
3547 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitUsingDecl(UsingDecl *D) {
3548 
3549  // The nested name specifier may be dependent, for example
3550  // template <typename T> struct t {
3551  // struct s1 { T f1(); };
3552  // struct s2 : s1 { using s1::f1; };
3553  // };
3554  // template struct t<int>;
3555  // Here, in using s1::f1, s1 refers to t<T>::s1;
3556  // we need to substitute for t<int>::s1.
3557  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc
3558  = SemaRef.SubstNestedNameSpecifierLoc(D->getQualifierLoc(),
3559  TemplateArgs);
3560  if (!QualifierLoc)
3561  return nullptr;
3562 
3563  // For an inheriting constructor declaration, the name of the using
3564  // declaration is the name of a constructor in this class, not in the
3565  // base class.
3566  DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo = D->getNameInfo();
3567  if (NameInfo.getName().getNameKind() == DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName)
3568  if (auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(SemaRef.CurContext))
3569  NameInfo.setName(SemaRef.Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXConstructorName(
3570  SemaRef.Context.getCanonicalType(SemaRef.Context.getRecordType(RD))));
3571 
3572  // We only need to do redeclaration lookups if we're in a class scope (in
3573  // fact, it's not really even possible in non-class scopes).
3574  bool CheckRedeclaration = Owner->isRecord();
3575  LookupResult Prev(SemaRef, NameInfo, Sema::LookupUsingDeclName,
3576  Sema::ForVisibleRedeclaration);
3577 
3578  UsingDecl *NewUD = UsingDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, Owner,
3579  D->getUsingLoc(),
3580  QualifierLoc,
3581  NameInfo,
3582  D->hasTypename());
3583 
3584  CXXScopeSpec SS;
3585  SS.Adopt(QualifierLoc);
3586  if (CheckRedeclaration) {
3587  Prev.setHideTags(false);
3588  SemaRef.LookupQualifiedName(Prev, Owner);
3589 
3590  // Check for invalid redeclarations.
3591  if (SemaRef.CheckUsingDeclRedeclaration(D->getUsingLoc(),
3592  D->hasTypename(), SS,
3593  D->getLocation(), Prev))
3594  NewUD->setInvalidDecl();
3595  }
3596 
3597  if (!NewUD->isInvalidDecl() &&
3598  SemaRef.CheckUsingDeclQualifier(D->getUsingLoc(), D->hasTypename(), SS,
3599  NameInfo, D->getLocation(), nullptr, D))
3600  NewUD->setInvalidDecl();
3601 
3602  SemaRef.Context.setInstantiatedFromUsingDecl(NewUD, D);
3603  NewUD->setAccess(D->getAccess());
3604  Owner->addDecl(NewUD);
3605 
3606  // Don't process the shadow decls for an invalid decl.
3607  if (NewUD->isInvalidDecl())
3608  return NewUD;
3609 
3610  // If the using scope was dependent, or we had dependent bases, we need to
3611  // recheck the inheritance
3612  if (NameInfo.getName().getNameKind() == DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName)
3613  SemaRef.CheckInheritingConstructorUsingDecl(NewUD);
3614 
3615  return VisitBaseUsingDecls(D, NewUD, CheckRedeclaration ? &Prev : nullptr);
3616 }
3617 
3618 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitUsingEnumDecl(UsingEnumDecl *D) {
3619  // Cannot be a dependent type, but still could be an instantiation
3620  EnumDecl *EnumD = cast_or_null<EnumDecl>(SemaRef.FindInstantiatedDecl(
3621  D->getLocation(), D->getEnumDecl(), TemplateArgs));
3622 
3623  if (SemaRef.RequireCompleteEnumDecl(EnumD, EnumD->getLocation()))
3624  return nullptr;
3625 
3626  UsingEnumDecl *NewUD =
3627  UsingEnumDecl::Create(SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getUsingLoc(),
3628  D->getEnumLoc(), D->getLocation(), EnumD);
3629 
3630  SemaRef.Context.setInstantiatedFromUsingEnumDecl(NewUD, D);
3631  NewUD->setAccess(D->getAccess());
3632  Owner->addDecl(NewUD);
3633 
3634  // Don't process the shadow decls for an invalid decl.
3635  if (NewUD->isInvalidDecl())
3636  return NewUD;
3637 
3638  // We don't have to recheck for duplication of the UsingEnumDecl itself, as it
3639  // cannot be dependent, and will therefore have been checked during template
3640  // definition.
3641 
3642  return VisitBaseUsingDecls(D, NewUD, nullptr);
3643 }

3646  // Ignore these; we handle them in bulk when processing the UsingDecl.
3647  return nullptr;
3648 }
3649 
3650 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitConstructorUsingShadowDecl(
3651  ConstructorUsingShadowDecl *D) {
3652  // Ignore these; we handle them in bulk when processing the UsingDecl.
3653  return nullptr;

3655 
3656 template <typename T>
3657 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::instantiateUnresolvedUsingDecl(
3658  T *D, bool InstantiatingPackElement) {
3659  // If this is a pack expansion, expand it now.
3660  if (D->isPackExpansion() && !InstantiatingPackElement) {
3661  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 2> Unexpanded;
3662  SemaRef.collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(D->getQualifierLoc(), Unexpanded);
3663  SemaRef.collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(D->getNameInfo(), Unexpanded);
3664 
3665  // Determine whether the set of unexpanded parameter packs can and should
3666  // be expanded.
3667  bool Expand = true;
3668  bool RetainExpansion = false;
3669  Optional<unsigned> NumExpansions;
3670  if (SemaRef.CheckParameterPacksForExpansion(
3671  D->getEllipsisLoc(), D->getSourceRange(), Unexpanded, TemplateArgs,
3672  Expand, RetainExpansion, NumExpansions))
3673  return nullptr;
3674 
3675  // This declaration cannot appear within a function template signature,
3676  // so we can't have a partial argument list for a parameter pack.
3677  assert(!RetainExpansion &&
3678  "should never need to retain an expansion for UsingPackDecl");
3679 
3680  if (!Expand) {
3681  // We cannot fully expand the pack expansion now, so substitute into the
3682  // pattern and create a new pack expansion.
3683  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(SemaRef, -1);
3684  return instantiateUnresolvedUsingDecl(D, true);
3685  }
3686 
3687  // Within a function, we don't have any normal way to check for conflicts
3688  // between shadow declarations from different using declarations in the
3689  // same pack expansion, but this is always ill-formed because all expansions
3690  // must produce (conflicting) enumerators.
3691  //
3692  // Sadly we can't just reject this in the template definition because it
3693  // could be valid if the pack is empty or has exactly one expansion.
3694  if (D->getDeclContext()->isFunctionOrMethod() && *NumExpansions > 1) {
3695  SemaRef.Diag(D->getEllipsisLoc(),
3696  diag::err_using_decl_redeclaration_expansion);
3697  return nullptr;
3698  }
3699 
3700  // Instantiate the slices of this pack and build a UsingPackDecl.
3701  SmallVector<NamedDecl*, 8> Expansions;
3702  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
3703  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(SemaRef, I);
3704  Decl *Slice = instantiateUnresolvedUsingDecl(D, true);
3705  if (!Slice)
3706  return nullptr;
3707  // Note that we can still get unresolved using declarations here, if we
3708  // had arguments for all packs but the pattern also contained other
3709  // template arguments (this only happens during partial substitution, eg
3710  // into the body of a generic lambda in a function template).
3711  Expansions.push_back(cast<NamedDecl>(Slice));
3712  }
3713 
3714  auto *NewD = SemaRef.BuildUsingPackDecl(D, Expansions);
3715  if (isDeclWithinFunction(D))
3716  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(D, NewD);
3717  return NewD;
3718  }
3719 
3720  UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl *TD = dyn_cast<UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl>(D);
3721  SourceLocation TypenameLoc = TD ? TD->getTypenameLoc() : SourceLocation();
3722 
3723  NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc
3724  = SemaRef.SubstNestedNameSpecifierLoc(D->getQualifierLoc(),
3725  TemplateArgs);
3726  if (!QualifierLoc)
3727  return nullptr;
3728 
3729  CXXScopeSpec SS;
3730  SS.Adopt(QualifierLoc);
3731 
3732  DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo
3733  = SemaRef.SubstDeclarationNameInfo(D->getNameInfo(), TemplateArgs);
3734 
3735  // Produce a pack expansion only if we're not instantiating a particular
3736  // slice of a pack expansion.
3737  bool InstantiatingSlice = D->getEllipsisLoc().isValid() &&
3738  SemaRef.ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndex != -1;
3739  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc =
3740  InstantiatingSlice ? SourceLocation() : D->getEllipsisLoc();
3741 
3742  bool IsUsingIfExists = D->template hasAttr<UsingIfExistsAttr>();
3743  NamedDecl *UD = SemaRef.BuildUsingDeclaration(
3744  /*Scope*/ nullptr, D->getAccess(), D->getUsingLoc(),
3745  /*HasTypename*/ TD, TypenameLoc, SS, NameInfo, EllipsisLoc,
3746  ParsedAttributesView(),
3747  /*IsInstantiation*/ true, IsUsingIfExists);
3748  if (UD) {
3749  SemaRef.InstantiateAttrs(TemplateArgs, D, UD);
3750  SemaRef.Context.setInstantiatedFromUsingDecl(UD, D);
3751  }
3752 
3753  return UD;
3754 }
3755

3757  UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl *D) {
3758  return instantiateUnresolvedUsingDecl(D);

3761 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitUnresolvedUsingValueDecl(

3766 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitUnresolvedUsingIfExistsDecl(

3771 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitUsingPackDecl(UsingPackDecl *D) {
3772  SmallVector<NamedDecl*, 8> Expansions;
3773  for (auto *UD : D->expansions()) {
3774  if (NamedDecl *NewUD =
3775  SemaRef.FindInstantiatedDecl(D->getLocation(), UD, TemplateArgs))
3776  Expansions.push_back(NewUD);
3777  else
3778  return nullptr;
3779  }
3780 
3781  auto *NewD = SemaRef.BuildUsingPackDecl(D, Expansions);
3782  if (isDeclWithinFunction(D))
3783  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(D, NewD);
3784  return NewD;
3785 }

3794 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitOMPThreadPrivateDecl(
3795  OMPThreadPrivateDecl *D) {
3796  SmallVector<Expr *, 5> Vars;
3797  for (auto *I : D->varlists()) {
3798  Expr *Var = SemaRef.SubstExpr(I, TemplateArgs).get();
3799  assert(isa<DeclRefExpr>(Var) && "threadprivate arg is not a DeclRefExpr");
3800  Vars.push_back(Var);
3801  }
3802 
3803  OMPThreadPrivateDecl *TD =
3804  SemaRef.CheckOMPThreadPrivateDecl(D->getLocation(), Vars);
3805 
3806  TD->setAccess(AS_public);
3807  Owner->addDecl(TD);
3808 
3809  return TD;
3810 }

3812 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitOMPAllocateDecl(OMPAllocateDecl *D) {
3813  SmallVector<Expr *, 5> Vars;
3814  for (auto *I : D->varlists()) {
3815  Expr *Var = SemaRef.SubstExpr(I, TemplateArgs).get();
3816  assert(isa<DeclRefExpr>(Var) && "allocate arg is not a DeclRefExpr");
3817  Vars.push_back(Var);
3818  }
3819  SmallVector<OMPClause *, 4> Clauses;
3820  // Copy map clauses from the original mapper.
3821  for (OMPClause *C : D->clauselists()) {
3822  OMPClause *IC = nullptr;
3823  if (auto *AC = dyn_cast<OMPAllocatorClause>(C)) {
3824  ExprResult NewE = SemaRef.SubstExpr(AC->getAllocator(), TemplateArgs);
3825  if (!NewE.isUsable())
3826  continue;
3827  IC = SemaRef.ActOnOpenMPAllocatorClause(
3828  NewE.get(), AC->getBeginLoc(), AC->getLParenLoc(), AC->getEndLoc());
3829  } else if (auto *AC = dyn_cast<OMPAlignClause>(C)) {
3830  ExprResult NewE = SemaRef.SubstExpr(AC->getAlignment(), TemplateArgs);
3831  if (!NewE.isUsable())
3832  continue;
3833  IC = SemaRef.ActOnOpenMPAlignClause(NewE.get(), AC->getBeginLoc(),
3834  AC->getLParenLoc(), AC->getEndLoc());
3835  // If align clause value ends up being invalid, this can end up null.
3836  if (!IC)
3837  continue;
3838  }
3839  Clauses.push_back(IC);
3840  }
3841 
3842  Sema::DeclGroupPtrTy Res = SemaRef.ActOnOpenMPAllocateDirective(
3843  D->getLocation(), Vars, Clauses, Owner);
3844  if (Res.get().isNull())
3845  return nullptr;
3846  return Res.get().getSingleDecl();
3847 }

3852 }
3853 
3854 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitOMPDeclareReductionDecl(
3855  OMPDeclareReductionDecl *D) {
3856  // Instantiate type and check if it is allowed.
3857  const bool RequiresInstantiation =
3858  D->getType()->isDependentType() ||
3859  D->getType()->isInstantiationDependentType() ||
3860  D->getType()->containsUnexpandedParameterPack();
3861  QualType SubstReductionType;
3862  if (RequiresInstantiation) {
3863  SubstReductionType = SemaRef.ActOnOpenMPDeclareReductionType(
3864  D->getLocation(),
3865  ParsedType::make(SemaRef.SubstType(
3866  D->getType(), TemplateArgs, D->getLocation(), DeclarationName())));
3867  } else {
3868  SubstReductionType = D->getType();
3869  }
3870  if (SubstReductionType.isNull())
3871  return nullptr;
3872  Expr *Combiner = D->getCombiner();
3873  Expr *Init = D->getInitializer();
3874  bool IsCorrect = true;
3875  // Create instantiated copy.
3876  std::pair<QualType, SourceLocation> ReductionTypes[] = {
3877  std::make_pair(SubstReductionType, D->getLocation())};
3878  auto *PrevDeclInScope = D->getPrevDeclInScope();
3879  if (PrevDeclInScope && !PrevDeclInScope->isInvalidDecl()) {
3880  PrevDeclInScope = cast<OMPDeclareReductionDecl>(
3881  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->findInstantiationOf(PrevDeclInScope)
3882  ->get<Decl *>());
3883  }
3884  auto DRD = SemaRef.ActOnOpenMPDeclareReductionDirectiveStart(
3885  /*S=*/nullptr, Owner, D->getDeclName(), ReductionTypes, D->getAccess(),
3886  PrevDeclInScope);
3887  auto *NewDRD = cast<OMPDeclareReductionDecl>(DRD.get().getSingleDecl());
3888  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(D, NewDRD);
3889  Expr *SubstCombiner = nullptr;
3890  Expr *SubstInitializer = nullptr;
3891  // Combiners instantiation sequence.
3892  if (Combiner) {
3893  SemaRef.ActOnOpenMPDeclareReductionCombinerStart(
3894  /*S=*/nullptr, NewDRD);
3895  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(
3896  cast<DeclRefExpr>(D->getCombinerIn())->getDecl(),
3897  cast<DeclRefExpr>(NewDRD->getCombinerIn())->getDecl());
3898  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(
3899  cast<DeclRefExpr>(D->getCombinerOut())->getDecl(),
3900  cast<DeclRefExpr>(NewDRD->getCombinerOut())->getDecl());
3901  auto *ThisContext = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(Owner);
3902  Sema::CXXThisScopeRAII ThisScope(SemaRef, ThisContext, Qualifiers(),
3903  ThisContext);
3904  SubstCombiner = SemaRef.SubstExpr(Combiner, TemplateArgs).get();
3905  SemaRef.ActOnOpenMPDeclareReductionCombinerEnd(NewDRD, SubstCombiner);
3906  }
3907  // Initializers instantiation sequence.
3908  if (Init) {
3909  VarDecl *OmpPrivParm = SemaRef.ActOnOpenMPDeclareReductionInitializerStart(
3910  /*S=*/nullptr, NewDRD);
3911  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(
3912  cast<DeclRefExpr>(D->getInitOrig())->getDecl(),
3913  cast<DeclRefExpr>(NewDRD->getInitOrig())->getDecl());
3914  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(
3915  cast<DeclRefExpr>(D->getInitPriv())->getDecl(),
3916  cast<DeclRefExpr>(NewDRD->getInitPriv())->getDecl());
3917  if (D->getInitializerKind() == OMPDeclareReductionDecl::CallInit) {
3918  SubstInitializer = SemaRef.SubstExpr(Init, TemplateArgs).get();
3919  } else {
3920  auto *OldPrivParm =
3921  cast<VarDecl>(cast<DeclRefExpr>(D->getInitPriv())->getDecl());
3922  IsCorrect = IsCorrect && OldPrivParm->hasInit();
3923  if (IsCorrect)
3924  SemaRef.InstantiateVariableInitializer(OmpPrivParm, OldPrivParm,
3925  TemplateArgs);
3926  }
3927  SemaRef.ActOnOpenMPDeclareReductionInitializerEnd(NewDRD, SubstInitializer,
3928  OmpPrivParm);
3929  }
3930  IsCorrect = IsCorrect && SubstCombiner &&
3931  (!Init ||
3932  (D->getInitializerKind() == OMPDeclareReductionDecl::CallInit &&
3933  SubstInitializer) ||
3934  (D->getInitializerKind() != OMPDeclareReductionDecl::CallInit &&
3935  !SubstInitializer));
3936 
3937  (void)SemaRef.ActOnOpenMPDeclareReductionDirectiveEnd(
3938  /*S=*/nullptr, DRD, IsCorrect && !D->isInvalidDecl());
3939 
3940  return NewDRD;
3941 }

3943 Decl *
3944 TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitOMPDeclareMapperDecl(OMPDeclareMapperDecl *D) {
3945  // Instantiate type and check if it is allowed.
3946  const bool RequiresInstantiation =
3947  D->getType()->isDependentType() ||
3948  D->getType()->isInstantiationDependentType() ||
3949  D->getType()->containsUnexpandedParameterPack();
3950  QualType SubstMapperTy;
3951  DeclarationName VN = D->getVarName();
3952  if (RequiresInstantiation) {
3953  SubstMapperTy = SemaRef.ActOnOpenMPDeclareMapperType(
3954  D->getLocation(),
3955  ParsedType::make(SemaRef.SubstType(D->getType(), TemplateArgs,
3956  D->getLocation(), VN)));
3957  } else {
3958  SubstMapperTy = D->getType();
3959  }
3960  if (SubstMapperTy.isNull())
3961  return nullptr;
3962  // Create an instantiated copy of mapper.
3963  auto *PrevDeclInScope = D->getPrevDeclInScope();
3964  if (PrevDeclInScope && !PrevDeclInScope->isInvalidDecl()) {
3965  PrevDeclInScope = cast<OMPDeclareMapperDecl>(
3966  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->findInstantiationOf(PrevDeclInScope)
3967  ->get<Decl *>());
3968  }
3969  bool IsCorrect = true;
3970  SmallVector<OMPClause *, 6> Clauses;
3971  // Instantiate the mapper variable.
3972  DeclarationNameInfo DirName;
3973  SemaRef.StartOpenMPDSABlock(llvm::omp::OMPD_declare_mapper, DirName,
3974  /*S=*/nullptr,
3975  (*D->clauselist_begin())->getBeginLoc());
3976  ExprResult MapperVarRef = SemaRef.ActOnOpenMPDeclareMapperDirectiveVarDecl(
3977  /*S=*/nullptr, SubstMapperTy, D->getLocation(), VN);
3978  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(
3979  cast<DeclRefExpr>(D->getMapperVarRef())->getDecl(),
3980  cast<DeclRefExpr>(MapperVarRef.get())->getDecl());
3981  auto *ThisContext = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(Owner);
3982  Sema::CXXThisScopeRAII ThisScope(SemaRef, ThisContext, Qualifiers(),
3983  ThisContext);
3984  // Instantiate map clauses.
3985  for (OMPClause *C : D->clauselists()) {
3986  auto *OldC = cast<OMPMapClause>(C);
3987  SmallVector<Expr *, 4> NewVars;
3988  for (Expr *OE : OldC->varlists()) {
3989  Expr *NE = SemaRef.SubstExpr(OE, TemplateArgs).get();
3990  if (!NE) {
3991  IsCorrect = false;
3992  break;
3993  }
3994  NewVars.push_back(NE);
3995  }
3996  if (!IsCorrect)
3997  break;
3998  NestedNameSpecifierLoc NewQualifierLoc =
3999  SemaRef.SubstNestedNameSpecifierLoc(OldC->getMapperQualifierLoc(),
4000  TemplateArgs);
4001  CXXScopeSpec SS;
4002  SS.Adopt(NewQualifierLoc);
4003  DeclarationNameInfo NewNameInfo =
4004  SemaRef.SubstDeclarationNameInfo(OldC->getMapperIdInfo(), TemplateArgs);
4005  OMPVarListLocTy Locs(OldC->getBeginLoc(), OldC->getLParenLoc(),
4006  OldC->getEndLoc());
4007  OMPClause *NewC = SemaRef.ActOnOpenMPMapClause(
4008  OldC->getMapTypeModifiers(), OldC->getMapTypeModifiersLoc(), SS,
4009  NewNameInfo, OldC->getMapType(), OldC->isImplicitMapType(),
4010  OldC->getMapLoc(), OldC->getColonLoc(), NewVars, Locs);
4011  Clauses.push_back(NewC);
4012  }
4013  SemaRef.EndOpenMPDSABlock(nullptr);
4014  if (!IsCorrect)
4015  return nullptr;
4016  Sema::DeclGroupPtrTy DG = SemaRef.ActOnOpenMPDeclareMapperDirective(
4017  /*S=*/nullptr, Owner, D->getDeclName(), SubstMapperTy, D->getLocation(),
4018  VN, D->getAccess(), MapperVarRef.get(), Clauses, PrevDeclInScope);
4019  Decl *NewDMD = DG.get().getSingleDecl();
4020  SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(D, NewDMD);
4021  return NewDMD;
4022 }

4049 Decl *
4050 TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitClassTemplateSpecializationDecl(
4051  ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *D) {
4052  // As a MS extension, we permit class-scope explicit specialization
4053  // of member class templates.
4054  ClassTemplateDecl *ClassTemplate = D->getSpecializedTemplate();
4055  assert(ClassTemplate->getDeclContext()->isRecord() &&
4056  D->getTemplateSpecializationKind() == TSK_ExplicitSpecialization &&
4057  "can only instantiate an explicit specialization "
4058  "for a member class template");
4059 
4060  // Lookup the already-instantiated declaration in the instantiation
4061  // of the class template.
4062  ClassTemplateDecl *InstClassTemplate =
4063  cast_or_null<ClassTemplateDecl>(SemaRef.FindInstantiatedDecl(
4064  D->getLocation(), ClassTemplate, TemplateArgs));
4065  if (!InstClassTemplate)
4066  return nullptr;
4067 
4068  // Substitute into the template arguments of the class template explicit
4069  // specialization.
4070  TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc Loc = D->getTypeAsWritten()->getTypeLoc().
4071  castAs<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>();
4072  TemplateArgumentListInfo InstTemplateArgs(Loc.getLAngleLoc(),
4073  Loc.getRAngleLoc());
4074  SmallVector<TemplateArgumentLoc, 4> ArgLocs;
4075  for (unsigned I = 0; I != Loc.getNumArgs(); ++I)
4076  ArgLocs.push_back(Loc.getArgLoc(I));
4077  if (SemaRef.SubstTemplateArguments(ArgLocs, TemplateArgs, InstTemplateArgs))
4078  return nullptr;
4079 
4080  // Check that the template argument list is well-formed for this
4081  // class template.
4082  SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 4> Converted;
4083  if (SemaRef.CheckTemplateArgumentList(InstClassTemplate,
4084  D->getLocation(),
4085  InstTemplateArgs,
4086  false,
4087  Converted,
4088  /*UpdateArgsWithConversions=*/true))
4089  return nullptr;
4090 
4091  // Figure out where to insert this class template explicit specialization
4092  // in the member template's set of class template explicit specializations.
4093  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4094  ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *PrevDecl =
4095  InstClassTemplate->findSpecialization(Converted, InsertPos);
4096 
4097  // Check whether we've already seen a conflicting instantiation of this
4098  // declaration (for instance, if there was a prior implicit instantiation).
4099  bool Ignored;
4100  if (PrevDecl &&
4101  SemaRef.CheckSpecializationInstantiationRedecl(D->getLocation(),
4102  D->getSpecializationKind(),
4103  PrevDecl,
4104  PrevDecl->getSpecializationKind(),
4105  PrevDecl->getPointOfInstantiation(),
4106  Ignored))
4107  return nullptr;
4108 
4109  // If PrevDecl was a definition and D is also a definition, diagnose.
4110  // This happens in cases like:
4111  //
4112  // template<typename T, typename U>
4113  // struct Outer {
4114  // template<typename X> struct Inner;
4115  // template<> struct Inner<T> {};
4116  // template<> struct Inner<U> {};
4117  // };
4118  //
4119  // Outer<int, int> outer; // error: the explicit specializations of Inner
4120  // // have the same signature.
4121  if (PrevDecl && PrevDecl->getDefinition() &&
4122  D->isThisDeclarationADefinition()) {
4123  SemaRef.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_redefinition) << PrevDecl;
4124  SemaRef.Diag(PrevDecl->getDefinition()->getLocation(),
4125  diag::note_previous_definition);
4126  return nullptr;
4127  }
4128 
4129  // Create the class template partial specialization declaration.
4130  ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *InstD =
4131  ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl::Create(
4132  SemaRef.Context, D->getTagKind(), Owner, D->getBeginLoc(),
4133  D->getLocation(), InstClassTemplate, Converted, PrevDecl);
4134 
4135  // Add this partial specialization to the set of class template partial
4136  // specializations.
4137  if (!PrevDecl)
4138  InstClassTemplate->AddSpecialization(InstD, InsertPos);
4139 
4140  // Substitute the nested name specifier, if any.
4141  if (SubstQualifier(D, InstD))
4142  return nullptr;
4143 
4144  // Build the canonical type that describes the converted template
4145  // arguments of the class template explicit specialization.
4146  QualType CanonType = SemaRef.Context.getTemplateSpecializationType(
4147  TemplateName(InstClassTemplate), Converted,
4148  SemaRef.Context.getRecordType(InstD));
4149 
4150  // Build the fully-sugared type for this class template
4151  // specialization as the user wrote in the specialization
4152  // itself. This means that we'll pretty-print the type retrieved
4153  // from the specialization's declaration the way that the user
4154  // actually wrote the specialization, rather than formatting the
4155  // name based on the "canonical" representation used to store the
4156  // template arguments in the specialization.
4157  TypeSourceInfo *WrittenTy = SemaRef.Context.getTemplateSpecializationTypeInfo(
4158  TemplateName(InstClassTemplate), D->getLocation(), InstTemplateArgs,
4159  CanonType);
4160 
4161  InstD->setAccess(D->getAccess());
4162  InstD->setInstantiationOfMemberClass(D, TSK_ImplicitInstantiation);
4163  InstD->setSpecializationKind(D->getSpecializationKind());
4164  InstD->setTypeAsWritten(WrittenTy);
4165  InstD->setExternLoc(D->getExternLoc());
4166  InstD->setTemplateKeywordLoc(D->getTemplateKeywordLoc());
4167 
4168  Owner->addDecl(InstD);
4169 
4170  // Instantiate the members of the class-scope explicit specialization eagerly.
4171  // We don't have support for lazy instantiation of an explicit specialization
4172  // yet, and MSVC eagerly instantiates in this case.
4173  // FIXME: This is wrong in standard C++.
4174  if (D->isThisDeclarationADefinition() &&
4175  SemaRef.InstantiateClass(D->getLocation(), InstD, D, TemplateArgs,
4176  TSK_ImplicitInstantiation,
4177  /*Complain=*/true))
4178  return nullptr;
4179 
4180  return InstD;
4181 }
4182 
4183 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitVarTemplateSpecializationDecl(
4184  VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *D) {
4185 
4186  TemplateArgumentListInfo VarTemplateArgsInfo;
4187  VarTemplateDecl *VarTemplate = D->getSpecializedTemplate();
4188  assert(VarTemplate &&
4189  "A template specialization without specialized template?");
4190 
4191  VarTemplateDecl *InstVarTemplate =
4192  cast_or_null<VarTemplateDecl>(SemaRef.FindInstantiatedDecl(
4193  D->getLocation(), VarTemplate, TemplateArgs));
4194  if (!InstVarTemplate)
4195  return nullptr;
4196 
4197  // Substitute the current template arguments.
4198  const TemplateArgumentListInfo &TemplateArgsInfo = D->getTemplateArgsInfo();
4199  VarTemplateArgsInfo.setLAngleLoc(TemplateArgsInfo.getLAngleLoc());
4200  VarTemplateArgsInfo.setRAngleLoc(TemplateArgsInfo.getRAngleLoc());
4201 
4202  if (SemaRef.SubstTemplateArguments(TemplateArgsInfo.arguments(), TemplateArgs,
4203  VarTemplateArgsInfo))
4204  return nullptr;
4205 
4206  // Check that the template argument list is well-formed for this template.
4207  SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 4> Converted;
4208  if (SemaRef.CheckTemplateArgumentList(InstVarTemplate, D->getLocation(),
4209  VarTemplateArgsInfo, false, Converted,
4210  /*UpdateArgsWithConversions=*/true))
4211  return nullptr;
4212 
4213  // Check whether we've already seen a declaration of this specialization.
4214  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4215  VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *PrevDecl =
4216  InstVarTemplate->findSpecialization(Converted, InsertPos);
4217 
4218  // Check whether we've already seen a conflicting instantiation of this
4219  // declaration (for instance, if there was a prior implicit instantiation).
4220  bool Ignored;
4221  if (PrevDecl && SemaRef.CheckSpecializationInstantiationRedecl(
4222  D->getLocation(), D->getSpecializationKind(), PrevDecl,
4223  PrevDecl->getSpecializationKind(),
4224  PrevDecl->getPointOfInstantiation(), Ignored))
4225  return nullptr;
4226 
4227  return VisitVarTemplateSpecializationDecl(
4228  InstVarTemplate, D, VarTemplateArgsInfo, Converted, PrevDecl);
4229 }
4230 
4231 Decl *TemplateDeclInstantiator::VisitVarTemplateSpecializationDecl(
4232  VarTemplateDecl *VarTemplate, VarDecl *D,
4233  const TemplateArgumentListInfo &TemplateArgsInfo,
4234  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Converted,
4235  VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *PrevDecl) {
4236 
4237  // Do substitution on the type of the declaration
4238  TypeSourceInfo *DI =
4239  SemaRef.SubstType(D->getTypeSourceInfo(), TemplateArgs,
4240  D->getTypeSpecStartLoc(), D->getDeclName());
4241  if (!DI)
4242  return nullptr;
4243 
4244  if (DI->getType()->isFunctionType()) {
4245  SemaRef.Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::err_variable_instantiates_to_function)
4246  << D->isStaticDataMember() << DI->getType();
4247  return nullptr;
4248  }
4249 
4250  // Build the instantiated declaration
4251  VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *Var = VarTemplateSpecializationDecl::Create(
4252  SemaRef.Context, Owner, D->getInnerLocStart(), D->getLocation(),
4253  VarTemplate, DI->getType(), DI, D->getStorageClass(), Converted);
4254  Var->setTemplateArgsInfo(TemplateArgsInfo);
4255  if (!PrevDecl) {
4256  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4257  VarTemplate->findSpecialization(Converted, InsertPos);
4258  VarTemplate->AddSpecialization(Var, InsertPos);
4259  }
4260 
4261  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().OpenCL)
4262  SemaRef.deduceOpenCLAddressSpace(Var);
4263 
4264  // Substitute the nested name specifier, if any.
4265  if (SubstQualifier(D, Var))
4266  return nullptr;
4267 
4268  SemaRef.BuildVariableInstantiation(Var, D, TemplateArgs, LateAttrs, Owner,
4269  StartingScope, false, PrevDecl);
4270 
4271  return Var;
4272 }

4281  DiagnosticsEngine::Error,
4282  "cannot instantiate %0 yet");
4283  SemaRef.Diag(D->getLocation(), DiagID)
4284  << D->getDeclKindName();
4285 
4286  return nullptr;
4287 }
