4302 
4303 Decl *Sema::SubstDecl(Decl *D, DeclContext *Owner,
4304  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs) {
4305  TemplateDeclInstantiator Instantiator(*this, Owner, TemplateArgs);
4306  if (D->isInvalidDecl())
4307  return nullptr;
4308 
4309  Decl *SubstD;
4310  runWithSufficientStackSpace(D->getLocation(), [&] {
4311  SubstD = Instantiator.Visit(D);
4312  });
4313  return SubstD;
4314 }
4315 
4316 void TemplateDeclInstantiator::adjustForRewrite(RewriteKind RK,
4317  FunctionDecl *Orig, QualType &T,
4318  TypeSourceInfo *&TInfo,
4319  DeclarationNameInfo &NameInfo) {
4320  assert(RK == RewriteKind::RewriteSpaceshipAsEqualEqual);
4321 
4322  // C++2a [class.compare.default]p3:
4323  // the return type is replaced with bool
4324  auto *FPT = T->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
4325  T = SemaRef.Context.getFunctionType(
4326  SemaRef.Context.BoolTy, FPT->getParamTypes(), FPT->getExtProtoInfo());
4327 
4328  // Update the return type in the source info too. The most straightforward
4329  // way is to create new TypeSourceInfo for the new type. Use the location of
4330  // the '= default' as the location of the new type.
4331  //
4332  // FIXME: Set the correct return type when we initially transform the type,
4333  // rather than delaying it to now.
4334  TypeSourceInfo *NewTInfo =
4335  SemaRef.Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T, Orig->getEndLoc());
4336  auto OldLoc = TInfo->getTypeLoc().getAsAdjusted<FunctionProtoTypeLoc>();
4337  assert(OldLoc && "type of function is not a function type?");
4338  auto NewLoc = NewTInfo->getTypeLoc().castAs<FunctionProtoTypeLoc>();
4339  for (unsigned I = 0, N = OldLoc.getNumParams(); I != N; ++I)
4340  NewLoc.setParam(I, OldLoc.getParam(I));
4341  TInfo = NewTInfo;
4342 
4343  // and the declarator-id is replaced with operator==
4344  NameInfo.setName(
4345  SemaRef.Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(OO_EqualEqual));
4346 }
4347 
4348 FunctionDecl *Sema::SubstSpaceshipAsEqualEqual(CXXRecordDecl *RD,
4349  FunctionDecl *Spaceship) {
4350  if (Spaceship->isInvalidDecl())
4351  return nullptr;
4352 
4353  // C++2a [class.compare.default]p3:
4354  // an == operator function is declared implicitly [...] with the same
4355  // access and function-definition and in the same class scope as the
4356  // three-way comparison operator function
4357  MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList NoTemplateArgs;
4358  NoTemplateArgs.setKind(TemplateSubstitutionKind::Rewrite);
4359  NoTemplateArgs.addOuterRetainedLevels(RD->getTemplateDepth());
4360  TemplateDeclInstantiator Instantiator(*this, RD, NoTemplateArgs);
4361  Decl *R;
4362  if (auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(Spaceship)) {
4363  R = Instantiator.VisitCXXMethodDecl(
4364  MD, nullptr, None,
4365  TemplateDeclInstantiator::RewriteKind::RewriteSpaceshipAsEqualEqual);
4366  } else {
4367  assert(Spaceship->getFriendObjectKind() &&
4368  "defaulted spaceship is neither a member nor a friend");
4369 
4370  R = Instantiator.VisitFunctionDecl(
4371  Spaceship, nullptr,
4372  TemplateDeclInstantiator::RewriteKind::RewriteSpaceshipAsEqualEqual);
4373  if (!R)
4374  return nullptr;
4375 
4376  FriendDecl *FD =
4377  FriendDecl::Create(Context, RD, Spaceship->getLocation(),
4378  cast<NamedDecl>(R), Spaceship->getBeginLoc());
4379  FD->setAccess(AS_public);
4380  RD->addDecl(FD);
4381  }
4382  return cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(R);
4383 }
4384 
4385 /// Instantiates a nested template parameter list in the current
4386 /// instantiation context.
4387 ///
4388 /// \param L The parameter list to instantiate
4389 ///
4390 /// \returns NULL if there was an error
4391 TemplateParameterList *
4392 TemplateDeclInstantiator::SubstTemplateParams(TemplateParameterList *L) {
4393  // Get errors for all the parameters before bailing out.
4394  bool Invalid = false;
4395 
4396  unsigned N = L->size();
4397  typedef SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 8> ParamVector;
4398  ParamVector Params;
4399  Params.reserve(N);
4400  for (auto &P : *L) {
4401  NamedDecl *D = cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(Visit(P));
4402  Params.push_back(D);
4403  Invalid = Invalid || !D || D->isInvalidDecl();
4404  }
4405 
4406  // Clean up if we had an error.
4407  if (Invalid)
4408  return nullptr;
4409 
4410  // FIXME: Concepts: Substitution into requires clause should only happen when
4411  // checking satisfaction.
4412  Expr *InstRequiresClause = nullptr;
4413  if (Expr *E = L->getRequiresClause()) {
4414  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext ConstantEvaluated(
4415  SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
4416  ExprResult Res = SemaRef.SubstExpr(E, TemplateArgs);
4417  if (Res.isInvalid() || !Res.isUsable()) {
4418  return nullptr;
4419  }
4420  InstRequiresClause = Res.get();
4421  }
4422 
4423  TemplateParameterList *InstL
4424  = TemplateParameterList::Create(SemaRef.Context, L->getTemplateLoc(),
4425  L->getLAngleLoc(), Params,
4426  L->getRAngleLoc(), InstRequiresClause);
4427  return InstL;
4428 }
4429 
4430 TemplateParameterList *
4431 Sema::SubstTemplateParams(TemplateParameterList *Params, DeclContext *Owner,
4432  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs) {
4433  TemplateDeclInstantiator Instantiator(*this, Owner, TemplateArgs);
4434  return Instantiator.SubstTemplateParams(Params);
4435 }
4436 
4437 /// Instantiate the declaration of a class template partial
4438 /// specialization.
4439 ///
4440 /// \param ClassTemplate the (instantiated) class template that is partially
4441 // specialized by the instantiation of \p PartialSpec.
4442 ///
4443 /// \param PartialSpec the (uninstantiated) class template partial
4444 /// specialization that we are instantiating.
4445 ///
4446 /// \returns The instantiated partial specialization, if successful; otherwise,
4447 /// NULL to indicate an error.
4448 ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *
4449 TemplateDeclInstantiator::InstantiateClassTemplatePartialSpecialization(
4450  ClassTemplateDecl *ClassTemplate,
4451  ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *PartialSpec) {
4452  // Create a local instantiation scope for this class template partial
4453  // specialization, which will contain the instantiations of the template
4454  // parameters.
4455  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(SemaRef);
4456 
4457  // Substitute into the template parameters of the class template partial
4458  // specialization.
4459  TemplateParameterList *TempParams = PartialSpec->getTemplateParameters();
4460  TemplateParameterList *InstParams = SubstTemplateParams(TempParams);
4461  if (!InstParams)
4462  return nullptr;
4463 
4464  // Substitute into the template arguments of the class template partial
4465  // specialization.
4466  const ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo *TemplArgInfo
4467  = PartialSpec->getTemplateArgsAsWritten();
4468  TemplateArgumentListInfo InstTemplateArgs(TemplArgInfo->LAngleLoc,
4469  TemplArgInfo->RAngleLoc);
4470  if (SemaRef.SubstTemplateArguments(TemplArgInfo->arguments(), TemplateArgs,
4471  InstTemplateArgs))
4472  return nullptr;
4473 
4474  // Check that the template argument list is well-formed for this
4475  // class template.
4476  SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 4> Converted;
4477  if (SemaRef.CheckTemplateArgumentList(ClassTemplate,
4478  PartialSpec->getLocation(),
4479  InstTemplateArgs,
4480  false,
4481  Converted))
4482  return nullptr;
4483 
4484  // Check these arguments are valid for a template partial specialization.
4485  if (SemaRef.CheckTemplatePartialSpecializationArgs(
4486  PartialSpec->getLocation(), ClassTemplate, InstTemplateArgs.size(),
4487  Converted))
4488  return nullptr;
4489 
4490  // Figure out where to insert this class template partial specialization
4491  // in the member template's set of class template partial specializations.
4492  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4493  ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *PrevDecl
4494  = ClassTemplate->findPartialSpecialization(Converted, InstParams,
4495  InsertPos);
4496 
4497  // Build the canonical type that describes the converted template
4498  // arguments of the class template partial specialization.
4499  QualType CanonType
4500  = SemaRef.Context.getTemplateSpecializationType(TemplateName(ClassTemplate),
4501  Converted);
4502 
4503  // Build the fully-sugared type for this class template
4504  // specialization as the user wrote in the specialization
4505  // itself. This means that we'll pretty-print the type retrieved
4506  // from the specialization's declaration the way that the user
4507  // actually wrote the specialization, rather than formatting the
4508  // name based on the "canonical" representation used to store the
4509  // template arguments in the specialization.
4510  TypeSourceInfo *WrittenTy
4511  = SemaRef.Context.getTemplateSpecializationTypeInfo(
4512  TemplateName(ClassTemplate),
4513  PartialSpec->getLocation(),
4514  InstTemplateArgs,
4515  CanonType);
4516 
4517  if (PrevDecl) {
4518  // We've already seen a partial specialization with the same template
4519  // parameters and template arguments. This can happen, for example, when
4520  // substituting the outer template arguments ends up causing two
4521  // class template partial specializations of a member class template
4522  // to have identical forms, e.g.,
4523  //
4524  // template<typename T, typename U>
4525  // struct Outer {
4526  // template<typename X, typename Y> struct Inner;
4527  // template<typename Y> struct Inner<T, Y>;
4528  // template<typename Y> struct Inner<U, Y>;
4529  // };
4530  //
4531  // Outer<int, int> outer; // error: the partial specializations of Inner
4532  // // have the same signature.
4533  SemaRef.Diag(PartialSpec->getLocation(), diag::err_partial_spec_redeclared)
4534  << WrittenTy->getType();
4535  SemaRef.Diag(PrevDecl->getLocation(), diag::note_prev_partial_spec_here)
4536  << SemaRef.Context.getTypeDeclType(PrevDecl);
4537  return nullptr;
4538  }
4539 
4540 
4541  // Create the class template partial specialization declaration.
4542  ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *InstPartialSpec =
4543  ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl::Create(
4544  SemaRef.Context, PartialSpec->getTagKind(), Owner,
4545  PartialSpec->getBeginLoc(), PartialSpec->getLocation(), InstParams,
4546  ClassTemplate, Converted, InstTemplateArgs, CanonType, nullptr);
4547  // Substitute the nested name specifier, if any.
4548  if (SubstQualifier(PartialSpec, InstPartialSpec))
4549  return nullptr;
4550 
4551  InstPartialSpec->setInstantiatedFromMember(PartialSpec);
4552  InstPartialSpec->setTypeAsWritten(WrittenTy);
4553 
4554  // Check the completed partial specialization.
4555  SemaRef.CheckTemplatePartialSpecialization(InstPartialSpec);
4556 
4557  // Add this partial specialization to the set of class template partial
4558  // specializations.
4559  ClassTemplate->AddPartialSpecialization(InstPartialSpec,
4560  /*InsertPos=*/nullptr);
4561  return InstPartialSpec;
4562 }
4563 
4564 /// Instantiate the declaration of a variable template partial
4565 /// specialization.
4566 ///
4567 /// \param VarTemplate the (instantiated) variable template that is partially
4568 /// specialized by the instantiation of \p PartialSpec.
4569 ///
4570 /// \param PartialSpec the (uninstantiated) variable template partial
4571 /// specialization that we are instantiating.
4572 ///
4573 /// \returns The instantiated partial specialization, if successful; otherwise,
4574 /// NULL to indicate an error.
4575 VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *
4576 TemplateDeclInstantiator::InstantiateVarTemplatePartialSpecialization(
4577  VarTemplateDecl *VarTemplate,
4578  VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *PartialSpec) {
4579  // Create a local instantiation scope for this variable template partial
4580  // specialization, which will contain the instantiations of the template
4581  // parameters.
4582  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(SemaRef);
4583 
4584  // Substitute into the template parameters of the variable template partial
4585  // specialization.
4586  TemplateParameterList *TempParams = PartialSpec->getTemplateParameters();
4587  TemplateParameterList *InstParams = SubstTemplateParams(TempParams);
4588  if (!InstParams)
4589  return nullptr;
4590 
4591  // Substitute into the template arguments of the variable template partial
4592  // specialization.
4593  const ASTTemplateArgumentListInfo *TemplArgInfo
4594  = PartialSpec->getTemplateArgsAsWritten();
4595  TemplateArgumentListInfo InstTemplateArgs(TemplArgInfo->LAngleLoc,
4596  TemplArgInfo->RAngleLoc);
4597  if (SemaRef.SubstTemplateArguments(TemplArgInfo->arguments(), TemplateArgs,
4598  InstTemplateArgs))
4599  return nullptr;
4600 
4601  // Check that the template argument list is well-formed for this
4602  // class template.
4603  SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 4> Converted;
4604  if (SemaRef.CheckTemplateArgumentList(VarTemplate, PartialSpec->getLocation(),
4605  InstTemplateArgs, false, Converted))
4606  return nullptr;
4607 
4608  // Check these arguments are valid for a template partial specialization.
4609  if (SemaRef.CheckTemplatePartialSpecializationArgs(
4610  PartialSpec->getLocation(), VarTemplate, InstTemplateArgs.size(),
4611  Converted))
4612  return nullptr;
4613 
4614  // Figure out where to insert this variable template partial specialization
4615  // in the member template's set of variable template partial specializations.
4616  void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4617  VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *PrevDecl =
4618  VarTemplate->findPartialSpecialization(Converted, InstParams, InsertPos);
4619 
4620  // Build the canonical type that describes the converted template
4621  // arguments of the variable template partial specialization.
4622  QualType CanonType = SemaRef.Context.getTemplateSpecializationType(
4623  TemplateName(VarTemplate), Converted);
4624 
4625  // Build the fully-sugared type for this variable template
4626  // specialization as the user wrote in the specialization
4627  // itself. This means that we'll pretty-print the type retrieved
4628  // from the specialization's declaration the way that the user
4629  // actually wrote the specialization, rather than formatting the
4630  // name based on the "canonical" representation used to store the
4631  // template arguments in the specialization.
4632  TypeSourceInfo *WrittenTy = SemaRef.Context.getTemplateSpecializationTypeInfo(
4633  TemplateName(VarTemplate), PartialSpec->getLocation(), InstTemplateArgs,
4634  CanonType);
4635 
4636  if (PrevDecl) {
4637  // We've already seen a partial specialization with the same template
4638  // parameters and template arguments. This can happen, for example, when
4639  // substituting the outer template arguments ends up causing two
4640  // variable template partial specializations of a member variable template
4641  // to have identical forms, e.g.,
4642  //
4643  // template<typename T, typename U>
4644  // struct Outer {
4645  // template<typename X, typename Y> pair<X,Y> p;
4646  // template<typename Y> pair<T, Y> p;
4647  // template<typename Y> pair<U, Y> p;
4648  // };
4649  //
4650  // Outer<int, int> outer; // error: the partial specializations of Inner
4651  // // have the same signature.
4652  SemaRef.Diag(PartialSpec->getLocation(),
4653  diag::err_var_partial_spec_redeclared)
4654  << WrittenTy->getType();
4655  SemaRef.Diag(PrevDecl->getLocation(),
4656  diag::note_var_prev_partial_spec_here);
4657  return nullptr;
4658  }
4659 
4660  // Do substitution on the type of the declaration
4661  TypeSourceInfo *DI = SemaRef.SubstType(
4662  PartialSpec->getTypeSourceInfo(), TemplateArgs,
4663  PartialSpec->getTypeSpecStartLoc(), PartialSpec->getDeclName());
4664  if (!DI)
4665  return nullptr;
4666 
4667  if (DI->getType()->isFunctionType()) {
4668  SemaRef.Diag(PartialSpec->getLocation(),
4669  diag::err_variable_instantiates_to_function)
4670  << PartialSpec->isStaticDataMember() << DI->getType();
4671  return nullptr;
4672  }
4673 
4674  // Create the variable template partial specialization declaration.
4675  VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *InstPartialSpec =
4676  VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl::Create(
4677  SemaRef.Context, Owner, PartialSpec->getInnerLocStart(),
4678  PartialSpec->getLocation(), InstParams, VarTemplate, DI->getType(),
4679  DI, PartialSpec->getStorageClass(), Converted, InstTemplateArgs);
4680 
4681  // Substitute the nested name specifier, if any.
4682  if (SubstQualifier(PartialSpec, InstPartialSpec))
4683  return nullptr;
4684 
4685  InstPartialSpec->setInstantiatedFromMember(PartialSpec);
4686  InstPartialSpec->setTypeAsWritten(WrittenTy);
4687 
4688  // Check the completed partial specialization.
4689  SemaRef.CheckTemplatePartialSpecialization(InstPartialSpec);
4690 
4691  // Add this partial specialization to the set of variable template partial
4692  // specializations. The instantiation of the initializer is not necessary.
4693  VarTemplate->AddPartialSpecialization(InstPartialSpec, /*InsertPos=*/nullptr);
4694 
4695  SemaRef.BuildVariableInstantiation(InstPartialSpec, PartialSpec, TemplateArgs,
4696  LateAttrs, Owner, StartingScope);
4697 
4698  return InstPartialSpec;
4699 }
4700 
4701 TypeSourceInfo*
4702 TemplateDeclInstantiator::SubstFunctionType(FunctionDecl *D,
4703  SmallVectorImpl<ParmVarDecl *> &Params) {
4704  TypeSourceInfo *OldTInfo = D->getTypeSourceInfo();
4705  assert(OldTInfo && "substituting function without type source info");
4706  assert(Params.empty() && "parameter vector is non-empty at start");
4707 
4708  CXXRecordDecl *ThisContext = nullptr;
4709  Qualifiers ThisTypeQuals;
4710  if (CXXMethodDecl *Method = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D)) {
4711  ThisContext = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Owner);
4712  ThisTypeQuals = Method->getMethodQualifiers();
4713  }
4714 
4715  TypeSourceInfo *NewTInfo
4716  = SemaRef.SubstFunctionDeclType(OldTInfo, TemplateArgs,
4717  D->getTypeSpecStartLoc(),
4718  D->getDeclName(),
4719  ThisContext, ThisTypeQuals);
4720  if (!NewTInfo)
4721  return nullptr;
4722 
4723  TypeLoc OldTL = OldTInfo->getTypeLoc().IgnoreParens();
4724  if (FunctionProtoTypeLoc OldProtoLoc = OldTL.getAs<FunctionProtoTypeLoc>()) {
4725  if (NewTInfo != OldTInfo) {
4726  // Get parameters from the new type info.
4727  TypeLoc NewTL = NewTInfo->getTypeLoc().IgnoreParens();
4728  FunctionProtoTypeLoc NewProtoLoc = NewTL.castAs<FunctionProtoTypeLoc>();
4729  unsigned NewIdx = 0;
4730  for (unsigned OldIdx = 0, NumOldParams = OldProtoLoc.getNumParams();
4731  OldIdx != NumOldParams; ++OldIdx) {
4732  ParmVarDecl *OldParam = OldProtoLoc.getParam(OldIdx);
4733  if (!OldParam)
4734  return nullptr;
4735 
4736  LocalInstantiationScope *Scope = SemaRef.CurrentInstantiationScope;
4737 
4738  Optional<unsigned> NumArgumentsInExpansion;
4739  if (OldParam->isParameterPack())
4740  NumArgumentsInExpansion =
4741  SemaRef.getNumArgumentsInExpansion(OldParam->getType(),
4742  TemplateArgs);
4743  if (!NumArgumentsInExpansion) {
4744  // Simple case: normal parameter, or a parameter pack that's
4745  // instantiated to a (still-dependent) parameter pack.
4746  ParmVarDecl *NewParam = NewProtoLoc.getParam(NewIdx++);
4747  Params.push_back(NewParam);
4748  Scope->InstantiatedLocal(OldParam, NewParam);
4749  } else {
4750  // Parameter pack expansion: make the instantiation an argument pack.
4751  Scope->MakeInstantiatedLocalArgPack(OldParam);
4752  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumArgumentsInExpansion; ++I) {
4753  ParmVarDecl *NewParam = NewProtoLoc.getParam(NewIdx++);
4754  Params.push_back(NewParam);
4755  Scope->InstantiatedLocalPackArg(OldParam, NewParam);
4756  }
4757  }
4758  }
4759  } else {
4760  // The function type itself was not dependent and therefore no
4761  // substitution occurred. However, we still need to instantiate
4762  // the function parameters themselves.
4763  const FunctionProtoType *OldProto =
4764  cast<FunctionProtoType>(OldProtoLoc.getType());
4765  for (unsigned i = 0, i_end = OldProtoLoc.getNumParams(); i != i_end;
4766  ++i) {
4767  ParmVarDecl *OldParam = OldProtoLoc.getParam(i);
4768  if (!OldParam) {
4769  Params.push_back(SemaRef.BuildParmVarDeclForTypedef(
4770  D, D->getLocation(), OldProto->getParamType(i)));
4771  continue;
4772  }
4773 
4774  ParmVarDecl *Parm =
4775  cast_or_null<ParmVarDecl>(VisitParmVarDecl(OldParam));
4776  if (!Parm)
4777  return nullptr;
4778  Params.push_back(Parm);
4779  }
4780  }
4781  } else {
4782  // If the type of this function, after ignoring parentheses, is not
4783  // *directly* a function type, then we're instantiating a function that
4784  // was declared via a typedef or with attributes, e.g.,
4785  //
4786  // typedef int functype(int, int);
4787  // functype func;
4788  // int __cdecl meth(int, int);
4789  //
4790  // In this case, we'll just go instantiate the ParmVarDecls that we
4791  // synthesized in the method declaration.
4792  SmallVector<QualType, 4> ParamTypes;
4793  Sema::ExtParameterInfoBuilder ExtParamInfos;
4794  if (SemaRef.SubstParmTypes(D->getLocation(), D->parameters(), nullptr,
4795  TemplateArgs, ParamTypes, &Params,
4796  ExtParamInfos))
4797  return nullptr;
4798  }
4799 
4800  return NewTInfo;
4801 }
4802 
4803 /// Introduce the instantiated function parameters into the local
4804 /// instantiation scope, and set the parameter names to those used
4805 /// in the template.
4806 bool Sema::addInstantiatedParametersToScope(
4807  FunctionDecl *Function, const FunctionDecl *PatternDecl,
4808  LocalInstantiationScope &Scope,
4809  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs) {
4810  unsigned FParamIdx = 0;
4811  for (unsigned I = 0, N = PatternDecl->getNumParams(); I != N; ++I) {
4812  const ParmVarDecl *PatternParam = PatternDecl->getParamDecl(I);
4813  if (!PatternParam->isParameterPack()) {
4814  // Simple case: not a parameter pack.
4815  assert(FParamIdx < Function->getNumParams());
4816  ParmVarDecl *FunctionParam = Function->getParamDecl(FParamIdx);
4817  FunctionParam->setDeclName(PatternParam->getDeclName());
4818  // If the parameter's type is not dependent, update it to match the type
4819  // in the pattern. They can differ in top-level cv-qualifiers, and we want
4820  // the pattern's type here. If the type is dependent, they can't differ,
4821  // per core issue 1668. Substitute into the type from the pattern, in case
4822  // it's instantiation-dependent.
4823  // FIXME: Updating the type to work around this is at best fragile.
4824  if (!PatternDecl->getType()->isDependentType()) {
4825  QualType T = SubstType(PatternParam->getType(), TemplateArgs,
4826  FunctionParam->getLocation(),
4827  FunctionParam->getDeclName());
4828  if (T.isNull())
4829  return true;
4830  FunctionParam->setType(T);
4831  }
4832 
4833  Scope.InstantiatedLocal(PatternParam, FunctionParam);
4834  ++FParamIdx;
4835  continue;
4836  }
4837 
4838  // Expand the parameter pack.
4839  Scope.MakeInstantiatedLocalArgPack(PatternParam);
4840  Optional<unsigned> NumArgumentsInExpansion =
4841  getNumArgumentsInExpansion(PatternParam->getType(), TemplateArgs);
4842  if (NumArgumentsInExpansion) {
4843  QualType PatternType =
4844  PatternParam->getType()->castAs<PackExpansionType>()->getPattern();
4845  for (unsigned Arg = 0; Arg < *NumArgumentsInExpansion; ++Arg) {
4846  ParmVarDecl *FunctionParam = Function->getParamDecl(FParamIdx);
4847  FunctionParam->setDeclName(PatternParam->getDeclName());
4848  if (!PatternDecl->getType()->isDependentType()) {
4849  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(*this, Arg);
4850  QualType T =
4851  SubstType(PatternType, TemplateArgs, FunctionParam->getLocation(),
4852  FunctionParam->getDeclName());
4853  if (T.isNull())
4854  return true;
4855  FunctionParam->setType(T);
4856  }
4857 
4858  Scope.InstantiatedLocalPackArg(PatternParam, FunctionParam);
4859  ++FParamIdx;
4860  }
4861  }
4862  }
4863 
4864  return false;
4865 }
4866 
4867 bool Sema::InstantiateDefaultArgument(SourceLocation CallLoc, FunctionDecl *FD,
4868  ParmVarDecl *Param) {
4869  assert(Param->hasUninstantiatedDefaultArg());
4870  Expr *UninstExpr = Param->getUninstantiatedDefaultArg();
4871 
4872  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext EvalContext(
4873  *this, ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated, Param);
4874 
4875  // Instantiate the expression.
4876  //
4877  // FIXME: Pass in a correct Pattern argument, otherwise
4878  // getTemplateInstantiationArgs uses the lexical context of FD, e.g.
4879  //
4880  // template<typename T>
4881  // struct A {
4882  // static int FooImpl();
4883  //
4884  // template<typename Tp>
4885  // // bug: default argument A<T>::FooImpl() is evaluated with 2-level
4886  // // template argument list [[T], [Tp]], should be [[Tp]].
4887  // friend A<Tp> Foo(int a);
4888  // };
4889  //
4890  // template<typename T>
4891  // A<T> Foo(int a = A<T>::FooImpl());
4892  MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList TemplateArgs
4893  = getTemplateInstantiationArgs(FD, nullptr, /*RelativeToPrimary=*/true);
4894 
4895  InstantiatingTemplate Inst(*this, CallLoc, Param,
4896  TemplateArgs.getInnermost());
4897  if (Inst.isInvalid())
4898  return true;
4899  if (Inst.isAlreadyInstantiating()) {
4900  Diag(Param->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_recursive_default_argument) << FD;
4901  Param->setInvalidDecl();
4902  return true;
4903  }
4904 
4905  ExprResult Result;
4906  {
4907  // C++ [dcl.fct.default]p5:
4908  // The names in the [default argument] expression are bound, and
4909  // the semantic constraints are checked, at the point where the
4910  // default argument expression appears.
4911  ContextRAII SavedContext(*this, FD);
4912  LocalInstantiationScope Local(*this);
4913 
4914  FunctionDecl *Pattern = FD->getTemplateInstantiationPattern(
4915  /*ForDefinition*/ false);
4916  if (addInstantiatedParametersToScope(FD, Pattern, Local, TemplateArgs))
4917  return true;
4918 
4919  runWithSufficientStackSpace(CallLoc, [&] {
4920  Result = SubstInitializer(UninstExpr, TemplateArgs,
4921  /*DirectInit*/false);
4922  });
4923  }
4924  if (Result.isInvalid())
4925  return true;
4926 
4927  // Check the expression as an initializer for the parameter.
4928  InitializedEntity Entity
4929  = InitializedEntity::InitializeParameter(Context, Param);
4930  InitializationKind Kind = InitializationKind::CreateCopy(
4931  Param->getLocation(),
4932  /*FIXME:EqualLoc*/ UninstExpr->getBeginLoc());
4933  Expr *ResultE = Result.getAs<Expr>();
4934 
4935  InitializationSequence InitSeq(*this, Entity, Kind, ResultE);
4936  Result = InitSeq.Perform(*this, Entity, Kind, ResultE);
4937  if (Result.isInvalid())
4938  return true;
4939 
4940  Result =
4941  ActOnFinishFullExpr(Result.getAs<Expr>(), Param->getOuterLocStart(),
4942  /*DiscardedValue*/ false);
4943  if (Result.isInvalid())
4944  return true;
4945 
4946  // Remember the instantiated default argument.
4947  Param->setDefaultArg(Result.getAs<Expr>());
4948  if (ASTMutationListener *L = getASTMutationListener())
4949  L->DefaultArgumentInstantiated(Param);
4950 
4951  return false;
4952 }
4953 
4954 void Sema::InstantiateExceptionSpec(SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation,
4955  FunctionDecl *Decl) {
4956  const FunctionProtoType *Proto = Decl->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
4957  if (Proto->getExceptionSpecType() != EST_Uninstantiated)
4958  return;
4959 
4960  InstantiatingTemplate Inst(*this, PointOfInstantiation, Decl,
4961  InstantiatingTemplate::ExceptionSpecification());
4962  if (Inst.isInvalid()) {
4963  // We hit the instantiation depth limit. Clear the exception specification
4964  // so that our callers don't have to cope with EST_Uninstantiated.
4965  UpdateExceptionSpec(Decl, EST_None);
4966  return;
4967  }
4968  if (Inst.isAlreadyInstantiating()) {
4969  // This exception specification indirectly depends on itself. Reject.
4970  // FIXME: Corresponding rule in the standard?
4971  Diag(PointOfInstantiation, diag::err_exception_spec_cycle) << Decl;
4972  UpdateExceptionSpec(Decl, EST_None);
4973  return;
4974  }
4975 
4976  // Enter the scope of this instantiation. We don't use
4977  // PushDeclContext because we don't have a scope.
4978  Sema::ContextRAII savedContext(*this, Decl);
4979  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(*this);
4980 
4981  MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList TemplateArgs =
4982  getTemplateInstantiationArgs(Decl, nullptr, /*RelativeToPrimary*/true);
4983 
4984  // FIXME: We can't use getTemplateInstantiationPattern(false) in general
4985  // here, because for a non-defining friend declaration in a class template,
4986  // we don't store enough information to map back to the friend declaration in
4987  // the template.
4988  FunctionDecl *Template = Proto->getExceptionSpecTemplate();
4989  if (addInstantiatedParametersToScope(Decl, Template, Scope, TemplateArgs)) {
4990  UpdateExceptionSpec(Decl, EST_None);
4991  return;
4992  }
4993 
4994  SubstExceptionSpec(Decl, Template->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>(),
4995  TemplateArgs);
4996 }
4997 
4998 /// Initializes the common fields of an instantiation function
4999 /// declaration (New) from the corresponding fields of its template (Tmpl).
5000 ///
5001 /// \returns true if there was an error
5002 bool
5003 TemplateDeclInstantiator::InitFunctionInstantiation(FunctionDecl *New,
5004  FunctionDecl *Tmpl) {
5005  New->setImplicit(Tmpl->isImplicit());
5006 
5007  // Forward the mangling number from the template to the instantiated decl.
5008  SemaRef.Context.setManglingNumber(New,
5009  SemaRef.Context.getManglingNumber(Tmpl));
5010 
5011  // If we are performing substituting explicitly-specified template arguments
5012  // or deduced template arguments into a function template and we reach this
5013  // point, we are now past the point where SFINAE applies and have committed
5014  // to keeping the new function template specialization. We therefore
5015  // convert the active template instantiation for the function template
5016  // into a template instantiation for this specific function template
5017  // specialization, which is not a SFINAE context, so that we diagnose any
5018  // further errors in the declaration itself.
5019  //
5020  // FIXME: This is a hack.
5021  typedef Sema::CodeSynthesisContext ActiveInstType;
5022  ActiveInstType &ActiveInst = SemaRef.CodeSynthesisContexts.back();
5023  if (ActiveInst.Kind == ActiveInstType::ExplicitTemplateArgumentSubstitution ||
5024  ActiveInst.Kind == ActiveInstType::DeducedTemplateArgumentSubstitution) {
5025  if (FunctionTemplateDecl *FunTmpl
5026  = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(ActiveInst.Entity)) {
5027  assert(FunTmpl->getTemplatedDecl() == Tmpl &&
5028  "Deduction from the wrong function template?");
5029  (void) FunTmpl;
5030  SemaRef.InstantiatingSpecializations.erase(
5031  {ActiveInst.Entity->getCanonicalDecl(), ActiveInst.Kind});
5032  atTemplateEnd(SemaRef.TemplateInstCallbacks, SemaRef, ActiveInst);
5033  ActiveInst.Kind = ActiveInstType::TemplateInstantiation;
5034  ActiveInst.Entity = New;
5035  atTemplateBegin(SemaRef.TemplateInstCallbacks, SemaRef, ActiveInst);
5036  }
5037  }
5038 
5039  const FunctionProtoType *Proto = Tmpl->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
5040  assert(Proto && "Function template without prototype?");
5041 
5042  if (Proto->hasExceptionSpec() || Proto->getNoReturnAttr()) {
5043  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = Proto->getExtProtoInfo();
5044 
5045  // DR1330: In C++11, defer instantiation of a non-trivial
5046  // exception specification.
5047  // DR1484: Local classes and their members are instantiated along with the
5048  // containing function.
5049  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 &&
5050  EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type != EST_None &&
5051  EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type != EST_DynamicNone &&
5052  EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type != EST_BasicNoexcept &&
5053  !Tmpl->isInLocalScopeForInstantiation()) {
5054  FunctionDecl *ExceptionSpecTemplate = Tmpl;
5055  if (EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type == EST_Uninstantiated)
5056  ExceptionSpecTemplate = EPI.ExceptionSpec.SourceTemplate;
5057  ExceptionSpecificationType NewEST = EST_Uninstantiated;
5058  if (EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type == EST_Unevaluated)
5059  NewEST = EST_Unevaluated;
5060 
5061  // Mark the function has having an uninstantiated exception specification.
5062  const FunctionProtoType *NewProto
5063  = New->getType()->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
5064  assert(NewProto && "Template instantiation without function prototype?");
5065  EPI = NewProto->getExtProtoInfo();
5066  EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type = NewEST;
5067  EPI.ExceptionSpec.SourceDecl = New;
5068  EPI.ExceptionSpec.SourceTemplate = ExceptionSpecTemplate;
5069  New->setType(SemaRef.Context.getFunctionType(
5070  NewProto->getReturnType(), NewProto->getParamTypes(), EPI));
5071  } else {
5072  Sema::ContextRAII SwitchContext(SemaRef, New);
5073  SemaRef.SubstExceptionSpec(New, Proto, TemplateArgs);
5074  }
5075  }
5076 
5077  // Get the definition. Leaves the variable unchanged if undefined.
5078  const FunctionDecl *Definition = Tmpl;
5079  Tmpl->isDefined(Definition);
5080 
5081  SemaRef.InstantiateAttrs(TemplateArgs, Definition, New,
5082  LateAttrs, StartingScope);
5083 
5084  return false;
5085 }
5086 
5087 /// Initializes common fields of an instantiated method
5088 /// declaration (New) from the corresponding fields of its template
5089 /// (Tmpl).
5090 ///
5091 /// \returns true if there was an error
5092 bool
5093 TemplateDeclInstantiator::InitMethodInstantiation(CXXMethodDecl *New,
5094  CXXMethodDecl *Tmpl) {
5095  if (InitFunctionInstantiation(New, Tmpl))
5096  return true;
5097 
5098  if (isa<CXXDestructorDecl>(New) && SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
5099  SemaRef.AdjustDestructorExceptionSpec(cast<CXXDestructorDecl>(New));
5100 
5101  New->setAccess(Tmpl->getAccess());
5102  if (Tmpl->isVirtualAsWritten())
5103  New->setVirtualAsWritten(true);
5104 
5105  // FIXME: New needs a pointer to Tmpl
5106  return false;
5107 }
5108 
5109 bool TemplateDeclInstantiator::SubstDefaultedFunction(FunctionDecl *New,
5110  FunctionDecl *Tmpl) {
5111  // Transfer across any unqualified lookups.
5112  if (auto *DFI = Tmpl->getDefaultedFunctionInfo()) {
5113  SmallVector<DeclAccessPair, 32> Lookups;
5114  Lookups.reserve(DFI->getUnqualifiedLookups().size());
5115  bool AnyChanged = false;
5116  for (DeclAccessPair DA : DFI->getUnqualifiedLookups()) {
5117  NamedDecl *D = SemaRef.FindInstantiatedDecl(New->getLocation(),
5118  DA.getDecl(), TemplateArgs);
5119  if (!D)
5120  return true;
5121  AnyChanged |= (D != DA.getDecl());
5122  Lookups.push_back(DeclAccessPair::make(D, DA.getAccess()));
5123  }
5124 
5125  // It's unlikely that substitution will change any declarations. Don't
5126  // store an unnecessary copy in that case.
5127  New->setDefaultedFunctionInfo(
5128  AnyChanged ? FunctionDecl::DefaultedFunctionInfo::Create(
5129  SemaRef.Context, Lookups)
5130  : DFI);
5131  }
5132 
5133  SemaRef.SetDeclDefaulted(New, Tmpl->getLocation());
5134  return false;
5135 }
5136 
5137 /// Instantiate (or find existing instantiation of) a function template with a
5138 /// given set of template arguments.
5139 ///
5140 /// Usually this should not be used, and template argument deduction should be
5141 /// used in its place.
5142 FunctionDecl *
5143 Sema::InstantiateFunctionDeclaration(FunctionTemplateDecl *FTD,
5144  const TemplateArgumentList *Args,
5145  SourceLocation Loc) {
5146  FunctionDecl *FD = FTD->getTemplatedDecl();
5147 
5148  sema::TemplateDeductionInfo Info(Loc);
5149  InstantiatingTemplate Inst(
5150  *this, Loc, FTD, Args->asArray(),
5151  CodeSynthesisContext::ExplicitTemplateArgumentSubstitution, Info);
5152  if (Inst.isInvalid())
5153  return nullptr;
5154 
5155  ContextRAII SavedContext(*this, FD);
5156  MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList MArgs(*Args);
5157 
5158  return cast_or_null<FunctionDecl>(SubstDecl(FD, FD->getParent(), MArgs));
5159 }
5160 
5161 /// Instantiate the definition of the given function from its
5162 /// template.
5163 ///
5164 /// \param PointOfInstantiation the point at which the instantiation was
5165 /// required. Note that this is not precisely a "point of instantiation"
5166 /// for the function, but it's close.
5167 ///
5168 /// \param Function the already-instantiated declaration of a
5169 /// function template specialization or member function of a class template
5170 /// specialization.
5171 ///
5172 /// \param Recursive if true, recursively instantiates any functions that
5173 /// are required by this instantiation.
5174 ///
5175 /// \param DefinitionRequired if true, then we are performing an explicit
5176 /// instantiation where the body of the function is required. Complain if
5177 /// there is no such body.
5178 void Sema::InstantiateFunctionDefinition(SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation,
5179  FunctionDecl *Function,
5180  bool Recursive,
5181  bool DefinitionRequired,
5182  bool AtEndOfTU) {
5183  if (Function->isInvalidDecl() || isa<CXXDeductionGuideDecl>(Function))
5184  return;
5185 
5186  // Never instantiate an explicit specialization except if it is a class scope
5187  // explicit specialization.
5188  TemplateSpecializationKind TSK =
5189  Function->getTemplateSpecializationKindForInstantiation();
5190  if (TSK == TSK_ExplicitSpecialization)
5191  return;
5192 
5193  // Don't instantiate a definition if we already have one.
5194  const FunctionDecl *ExistingDefn = nullptr;
5195  if (Function->isDefined(ExistingDefn,
5196  /*CheckForPendingFriendDefinition=*/true)) {
5197  if (ExistingDefn->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
5198  return;
5199 
5200  // If we're asked to instantiate a function whose body comes from an
5201  // instantiated friend declaration, attach the instantiated body to the
5202  // corresponding declaration of the function.
5203  assert(ExistingDefn->isThisDeclarationInstantiatedFromAFriendDefinition());
5204  Function = const_cast<FunctionDecl*>(ExistingDefn);
5205  }
5206 
5207  // Find the function body that we'll be substituting.
5208  const FunctionDecl *PatternDecl = Function->getTemplateInstantiationPattern();
5209  assert(PatternDecl && "instantiating a non-template");
5210 
5211  const FunctionDecl *PatternDef = PatternDecl->getDefinition();
5212  Stmt *Pattern = nullptr;
5213  if (PatternDef) {
5214  Pattern = PatternDef->getBody(PatternDef);
5215  PatternDecl = PatternDef;
5216  if (PatternDef->willHaveBody())
5217  PatternDef = nullptr;
5218  }
5219 
5220  // FIXME: We need to track the instantiation stack in order to know which
5221  // definitions should be visible within this instantiation.
5222  if (DiagnoseUninstantiableTemplate(PointOfInstantiation, Function,
5223  Function->getInstantiatedFromMemberFunction(),
5224  PatternDecl, PatternDef, TSK,
5225  /*Complain*/DefinitionRequired)) {
5226  if (DefinitionRequired)
5227  Function->setInvalidDecl();
5228  else if (TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition) {
5229  // Try again at the end of the translation unit (at which point a
5230  // definition will be required).
5231  assert(!Recursive);
5232  Function->setInstantiationIsPending(true);
5233  PendingInstantiations.push_back(
5234  std::make_pair(Function, PointOfInstantiation));
5235  } else if (TSK == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation) {
5236  if (AtEndOfTU && !getDiagnostics().hasErrorOccurred() &&
5237  !getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(PatternDecl->getBeginLoc())) {
5238  Diag(PointOfInstantiation, diag::warn_func_template_missing)
5239  << Function;
5240  Diag(PatternDecl->getLocation(), diag::note_forward_template_decl);
5241  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
5242  Diag(PointOfInstantiation, diag::note_inst_declaration_hint)
5243  << Function;
5244  }
5245  }
5246 
5247  return;
5248  }
5249 
5250  // Postpone late parsed template instantiations.
5251  if (PatternDecl->isLateTemplateParsed() &&
5252  !LateTemplateParser) {
5253  Function->setInstantiationIsPending(true);
5254  LateParsedInstantiations.push_back(
5255  std::make_pair(Function, PointOfInstantiation));
5256  return;
5257  }
5258 
5259  llvm::TimeTraceScope TimeScope("InstantiateFunction", [&]() {
5260  std::string Name;
5261  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(Name);
5262  Function->getNameForDiagnostic(OS, getPrintingPolicy(),
5263  /*Qualified=*/true);
5264  return Name;
5265  });
5266 
5267  // If we're performing recursive template instantiation, create our own
5268  // queue of pending implicit instantiations that we will instantiate later,
5269  // while we're still within our own instantiation context.
5270  // This has to happen before LateTemplateParser below is called, so that
5271  // it marks vtables used in late parsed templates as used.
5272  GlobalEagerInstantiationScope GlobalInstantiations(*this,
5273  /*Enabled=*/Recursive);
5274  LocalEagerInstantiationScope LocalInstantiations(*this);
5275 
5276  // Call the LateTemplateParser callback if there is a need to late parse
5277  // a templated function definition.
5278  if (!Pattern && PatternDecl->isLateTemplateParsed() &&
5279  LateTemplateParser) {
5280  // FIXME: Optimize to allow individual templates to be deserialized.
5281  if (PatternDecl->isFromASTFile())
5282  ExternalSource->ReadLateParsedTemplates(LateParsedTemplateMap);
5283 
5284  auto LPTIter = LateParsedTemplateMap.find(PatternDecl);
5285  assert(LPTIter != LateParsedTemplateMap.end() &&
5286  "missing LateParsedTemplate");
5287  LateTemplateParser(OpaqueParser, *LPTIter->second);
5288  Pattern = PatternDecl->getBody(PatternDecl);
5289  }
5290 
5291  // Note, we should never try to instantiate a deleted function template.
5292  assert((Pattern || PatternDecl->isDefaulted() ||
5293  PatternDecl->hasSkippedBody()) &&
5294  "unexpected kind of function template definition");
5295 
5296  // C++1y [temp.explicit]p10:
5297  // Except for inline functions, declarations with types deduced from their
5298  // initializer or return value, and class template specializations, other
5299  // explicit instantiation declarations have the effect of suppressing the
5300  // implicit instantiation of the entity to which they refer.
5301  if (TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration &&
5302  !PatternDecl->isInlined() &&
5303  !PatternDecl->getReturnType()->getContainedAutoType())
5304  return;
5305 
5306  if (PatternDecl->isInlined()) {
5307  // Function, and all later redeclarations of it (from imported modules,
5308  // for instance), are now implicitly inline.
5309  for (auto *D = Function->getMostRecentDecl(); /**/;
5310  D = D->getPreviousDecl()) {
5311  D->setImplicitlyInline();
5312  if (D == Function)
5313  break;
5314  }
5315  }
5316 
5317  InstantiatingTemplate Inst(*this, PointOfInstantiation, Function);
5318  if (Inst.isInvalid() || Inst.isAlreadyInstantiating())
5319  return;
5320  PrettyDeclStackTraceEntry CrashInfo(Context, Function, SourceLocation(),
5321  "instantiating function definition");
5322 
5323  // The instantiation is visible here, even if it was first declared in an
5324  // unimported module.
5325  Function->setVisibleDespiteOwningModule();
5326 
5327  // Copy the inner loc start from the pattern.
5328  Function->setInnerLocStart(PatternDecl->getInnerLocStart());
5329 
5330  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext EvalContext(
5331  *this, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated);
5332 
5333  // Introduce a new scope where local variable instantiations will be
5334  // recorded, unless we're actually a member function within a local
5335  // class, in which case we need to merge our results with the parent
5336  // scope (of the enclosing function). The exception is instantiating
5337  // a function template specialization, since the template to be
5338  // instantiated already has references to locals properly substituted.
5339  bool MergeWithParentScope = false;
5340  if (CXXRecordDecl *Rec = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Function->getDeclContext()))
5341  MergeWithParentScope =
5342  Rec->isLocalClass() && !Function->isFunctionTemplateSpecialization();
5343 
5344  LocalInstantiationScope Scope(*this, MergeWithParentScope);
5345  auto RebuildTypeSourceInfoForDefaultSpecialMembers = [&]() {
5346  // Special members might get their TypeSourceInfo set up w.r.t the
5347  // PatternDecl context, in which case parameters could still be pointing
5348  // back to the original class, make sure arguments are bound to the
5349  // instantiated record instead.
5350  assert(PatternDecl->isDefaulted() &&
5351  "Special member needs to be defaulted");
5352  auto PatternSM = getDefaultedFunctionKind(PatternDecl).asSpecialMember();
5353  if (!(PatternSM == Sema::CXXCopyConstructor ||
5354  PatternSM == Sema::CXXCopyAssignment ||
5355  PatternSM == Sema::CXXMoveConstructor ||
5356  PatternSM == Sema::CXXMoveAssignment))
5357  return;
5358 
5359  auto *NewRec = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Function->getDeclContext());
5360  const auto *PatternRec =
5361  dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(PatternDecl->getDeclContext());
5362  if (!NewRec || !PatternRec)
5363  return;
5364  if (!PatternRec->isLambda())
5365  return;
5366 
5367  struct SpecialMemberTypeInfoRebuilder
5368  : TreeTransform<SpecialMemberTypeInfoRebuilder> {
5369  using Base = TreeTransform<SpecialMemberTypeInfoRebuilder>;
5370  const CXXRecordDecl *OldDecl;
5371  CXXRecordDecl *NewDecl;
5372 
5373  SpecialMemberTypeInfoRebuilder(Sema &SemaRef, const CXXRecordDecl *O,
5374  CXXRecordDecl *N)
5375  : TreeTransform(SemaRef), OldDecl(O), NewDecl(N) {}
5376 
5377  bool TransformExceptionSpec(SourceLocation Loc,
5378  FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo &ESI,
5379  SmallVectorImpl<QualType> &Exceptions,
5380  bool &Changed) {
5381  return false;
5382  }
5383 
5384  QualType TransformRecordType(TypeLocBuilder &TLB, RecordTypeLoc TL) {
5385  const RecordType *T = TL.getTypePtr();
5386  RecordDecl *Record = cast_or_null<RecordDecl>(
5387  getDerived().TransformDecl(TL.getNameLoc(), T->getDecl()));
5388  if (Record != OldDecl)
5389  return Base::TransformRecordType(TLB, TL);
5390 
5391  QualType Result = getDerived().RebuildRecordType(NewDecl);
5392  if (Result.isNull())
5393  return QualType();
5394 
5395  RecordTypeLoc NewTL = TLB.push<RecordTypeLoc>(Result);
5396  NewTL.setNameLoc(TL.getNameLoc());
5397  return Result;
5398  }
5399  } IR{*this, PatternRec, NewRec};
5400 
5401  TypeSourceInfo *NewSI = IR.TransformType(Function->getTypeSourceInfo());
5402  Function->setType(NewSI->getType());
5403  Function->setTypeSourceInfo(NewSI);
5404 
5405  ParmVarDecl *Parm = Function->getParamDecl(0);
5406  TypeSourceInfo *NewParmSI = IR.TransformType(Parm->getTypeSourceInfo());
5407  Parm->setType(NewParmSI->getType());
5408  Parm->setTypeSourceInfo(NewParmSI);
5409  };
5410 
5411  if (PatternDecl->isDefaulted()) {
5412  RebuildTypeSourceInfoForDefaultSpecialMembers();
5413  SetDeclDefaulted(Function, PatternDecl->getLocation());
5414  } else {
5415  MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList TemplateArgs =
5416  getTemplateInstantiationArgs(Function, nullptr, false, PatternDecl);
5417 
5418  // Substitute into the qualifier; we can get a substitution failure here
5419  // through evil use of alias templates.
5420  // FIXME: Is CurContext correct for this? Should we go to the (instantiation
5421  // of the) lexical context of the pattern?
5422  SubstQualifier(*this, PatternDecl, Function, TemplateArgs);
5423 
5424  ActOnStartOfFunctionDef(nullptr, Function);
5425 
5426  // Enter the scope of this instantiation. We don't use
5427  // PushDeclContext because we don't have a scope.
5428  Sema::ContextRAII savedContext(*this, Function);
5429 
5430  if (addInstantiatedParametersToScope(Function, PatternDecl, Scope,
5431  TemplateArgs))
5432  return;
5433 
5434  StmtResult Body;
5435  if (PatternDecl->hasSkippedBody()) {
5436  ActOnSkippedFunctionBody(Function);
5437  Body = nullptr;
5438  } else {
5439  if (CXXConstructorDecl *Ctor = dyn_cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(Function)) {
5440  // If this is a constructor, instantiate the member initializers.
5441  InstantiateMemInitializers(Ctor, cast<CXXConstructorDecl>(PatternDecl),
5442  TemplateArgs);
5443 
5444  // If this is an MS ABI dllexport default constructor, instantiate any
5445  // default arguments.
5446  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() &&
5447  Ctor->isDefaultConstructor()) {
5448  InstantiateDefaultCtorDefaultArgs(Ctor);
5449  }
5450  }
5451 
5452  // Instantiate the function body.
5453  Body = SubstStmt(Pattern, TemplateArgs);
5454 
5455  if (Body.isInvalid())
5456  Function->setInvalidDecl();
5457  }
5458  // FIXME: finishing the function body while in an expression evaluation
5459  // context seems wrong. Investigate more.
5460  ActOnFinishFunctionBody(Function, Body.get(), /*IsInstantiation=*/true);
5461 
5462  PerformDependentDiagnostics(PatternDecl, TemplateArgs);
5463 
5464  if (auto *Listener = getASTMutationListener())
5465  Listener->FunctionDefinitionInstantiated(Function);
5466 
5467  savedContext.pop();
5468  }
5469 
5470  DeclGroupRef DG(Function);
5471  Consumer.HandleTopLevelDecl(DG);
5472 
5473  // This class may have local implicit instantiations that need to be
5474  // instantiation within this scope.
5475  LocalInstantiations.perform();
5476  Scope.Exit();
5477  GlobalInstantiations.perform();
5478 }
5479 
5480 VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *Sema::BuildVarTemplateInstantiation(
5481  VarTemplateDecl *VarTemplate, VarDecl *FromVar,
5482  const TemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgList,
5483  const TemplateArgumentListInfo &TemplateArgsInfo,
5484  SmallVectorImpl<TemplateArgument> &Converted,
5485  SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation,
5486  LateInstantiatedAttrVec *LateAttrs,
5487  LocalInstantiationScope *StartingScope) {
5488  if (FromVar->isInvalidDecl())
5489  return nullptr;
5490 
5491  InstantiatingTemplate Inst(*this, PointOfInstantiation, FromVar);
5492  if (Inst.isInvalid())
5493  return nullptr;
5494 
5495  MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList TemplateArgLists;
5496  TemplateArgLists.addOuterTemplateArguments(&TemplateArgList);
5497 
5498  // Instantiate the first declaration of the variable template: for a partial
5499  // specialization of a static data member template, the first declaration may
5500  // or may not be the declaration in the class; if it's in the class, we want
5501  // to instantiate a member in the class (a declaration), and if it's outside,
5502  // we want to instantiate a definition.
5503  //
5504  // If we're instantiating an explicitly-specialized member template or member
5505  // partial specialization, don't do this. The member specialization completely
5506  // replaces the original declaration in this case.
5507  bool IsMemberSpec = false;
5508  if (VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *PartialSpec =
5509  dyn_cast<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(FromVar))
5510  IsMemberSpec = PartialSpec->isMemberSpecialization();
5511  else if (VarTemplateDecl *FromTemplate = FromVar->getDescribedVarTemplate())
5512  IsMemberSpec = FromTemplate->isMemberSpecialization();
5513  if (!IsMemberSpec)
5514  FromVar = FromVar->getFirstDecl();
5515 
5516  MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList MultiLevelList(TemplateArgList);
5517  TemplateDeclInstantiator Instantiator(*this, FromVar->getDeclContext(),
5518  MultiLevelList);
5519 
5520  // TODO: Set LateAttrs and StartingScope ...
5521 
5522  auto *VD = cast_or_null<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(
5523  Instantiator.VisitVarTemplateSpecializationDecl(
5524  VarTemplate, FromVar, TemplateArgsInfo, Converted));
5525 
5526  addSyclVarDecl(VD);
5527 
5528  return VD;
5529 }
5530 
5531 /// Instantiates a variable template specialization by completing it
5532 /// with appropriate type information and initializer.
5533 VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *Sema::CompleteVarTemplateSpecializationDecl(
5534  VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *VarSpec, VarDecl *PatternDecl,
5535  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs) {
5536  assert(PatternDecl->isThisDeclarationADefinition() &&
5537  "don't have a definition to instantiate from");
5538 
5539  // Do substitution on the type of the declaration
5540  TypeSourceInfo *DI =
5541  SubstType(PatternDecl->getTypeSourceInfo(), TemplateArgs,
5542  PatternDecl->getTypeSpecStartLoc(), PatternDecl->getDeclName());
5543  if (!DI)
5544  return nullptr;
5545 
5546  // Update the type of this variable template specialization.
5547  VarSpec->setType(DI->getType());
5548 
5549  // Convert the declaration into a definition now.
5550  VarSpec->setCompleteDefinition();
5551 
5552  // Instantiate the initializer.
5553  InstantiateVariableInitializer(VarSpec, PatternDecl, TemplateArgs);
5554 
5555  if (getLangOpts().OpenCL)
5556  deduceOpenCLAddressSpace(VarSpec);
5557 
5558  return VarSpec;
5559 }
5560 
5561 /// BuildVariableInstantiation - Used after a new variable has been created.
5562 /// Sets basic variable data and decides whether to postpone the
5563 /// variable instantiation.
5564 void Sema::BuildVariableInstantiation(
5565  VarDecl *NewVar, VarDecl *OldVar,
5566  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
5567  LateInstantiatedAttrVec *LateAttrs, DeclContext *Owner,
5568  LocalInstantiationScope *StartingScope,
5569  bool InstantiatingVarTemplate,
5570  VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *PrevDeclForVarTemplateSpecialization) {
5571  // Instantiating a partial specialization to produce a partial
5572  // specialization.
5573  bool InstantiatingVarTemplatePartialSpec =
5574  isa<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(OldVar) &&
5575  isa<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(NewVar);
5576  // Instantiating from a variable template (or partial specialization) to
5577  // produce a variable template specialization.
5578  bool InstantiatingSpecFromTemplate =
5579  isa<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(NewVar) &&
5580  (OldVar->getDescribedVarTemplate() ||
5581  isa<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(OldVar));
5582 
5583  // If we are instantiating a local extern declaration, the
5584  // instantiation belongs lexically to the containing function.
5585  // If we are instantiating a static data member defined
5586  // out-of-line, the instantiation will have the same lexical
5587  // context (which will be a namespace scope) as the template.
5588  if (OldVar->isLocalExternDecl()) {
5589  NewVar->setLocalExternDecl();
5590  NewVar->setLexicalDeclContext(Owner);
5591  } else if (OldVar->isOutOfLine())
5592  NewVar->setLexicalDeclContext(OldVar->getLexicalDeclContext());
5593  NewVar->setTSCSpec(OldVar->getTSCSpec());
5594  NewVar->setInitStyle(OldVar->getInitStyle());
5595  NewVar->setCXXForRangeDecl(OldVar->isCXXForRangeDecl());
5596  NewVar->setObjCForDecl(OldVar->isObjCForDecl());
5597  NewVar->setConstexpr(OldVar->isConstexpr());
5598  NewVar->setInitCapture(OldVar->isInitCapture());
5599  NewVar->setPreviousDeclInSameBlockScope(
5600  OldVar->isPreviousDeclInSameBlockScope());
5601  NewVar->setAccess(OldVar->getAccess());
5602 
5603  if (!OldVar->isStaticDataMember()) {
5604  if (OldVar->isUsed(false))
5605  NewVar->setIsUsed();
5606  NewVar->setReferenced(OldVar->isReferenced());
5607  }
5608 
5609  InstantiateAttrs(TemplateArgs, OldVar, NewVar, LateAttrs, StartingScope);
5610 
5611  LookupResult Previous(
5612  *this, NewVar->getDeclName(), NewVar->getLocation(),
5613  NewVar->isLocalExternDecl() ? Sema::LookupRedeclarationWithLinkage
5614  : Sema::LookupOrdinaryName,
5615  NewVar->isLocalExternDecl() ? Sema::ForExternalRedeclaration
5616  : forRedeclarationInCurContext());
5617 
5618  if (NewVar->isLocalExternDecl() && OldVar->getPreviousDecl() &&
5619  (!OldVar->getPreviousDecl()->getDeclContext()->isDependentContext() ||
5620  OldVar->getPreviousDecl()->getDeclContext()==OldVar->getDeclContext())) {
5621  // We have a previous declaration. Use that one, so we merge with the
5622  // right type.
5623  if (NamedDecl *NewPrev = FindInstantiatedDecl(
5624  NewVar->getLocation(), OldVar->getPreviousDecl(), TemplateArgs))
5625  Previous.addDecl(NewPrev);
5626  } else if (!isa<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(NewVar) &&
5627  OldVar->hasLinkage()) {
5628  LookupQualifiedName(Previous, NewVar->getDeclContext(), false);
5629  } else if (PrevDeclForVarTemplateSpecialization) {
5630  Previous.addDecl(PrevDeclForVarTemplateSpecialization);
5631  }
5632  CheckVariableDeclaration(NewVar, Previous);
5633 
5634  if (!InstantiatingVarTemplate) {
5635  NewVar->getLexicalDeclContext()->addHiddenDecl(NewVar);
5636  if (!NewVar->isLocalExternDecl() || !NewVar->getPreviousDecl())
5637  NewVar->getDeclContext()->makeDeclVisibleInContext(NewVar);
5638  }
5639 
5640  if (!OldVar->isOutOfLine()) {
5641  if (NewVar->getDeclContext()->isFunctionOrMethod())
5642  CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(OldVar, NewVar);
5643  }
5644 
5645  // Link instantiations of static data members back to the template from
5646  // which they were instantiated.
5647  //
5648  // Don't do this when instantiating a template (we link the template itself
5649  // back in that case) nor when instantiating a static data member template
5650  // (that's not a member specialization).
5651  if (NewVar->isStaticDataMember() && !InstantiatingVarTemplate &&
5652  !InstantiatingSpecFromTemplate)
5653  NewVar->setInstantiationOfStaticDataMember(OldVar,
5654  TSK_ImplicitInstantiation);
5655 
5656  // If the pattern is an (in-class) explicit specialization, then the result
5657  // is also an explicit specialization.
5658  if (VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *OldVTSD =
5659  dyn_cast<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(OldVar)) {
5660  if (OldVTSD->getSpecializationKind() == TSK_ExplicitSpecialization &&
5661  !isa<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(OldVTSD))
5662  cast<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(NewVar)->setSpecializationKind(
5663  TSK_ExplicitSpecialization);
5664  }
5665 
5666  // Forward the mangling number from the template to the instantiated decl.
5667  Context.setManglingNumber(NewVar, Context.getManglingNumber(OldVar));
5668  Context.setStaticLocalNumber(NewVar, Context.getStaticLocalNumber(OldVar));
5669 
5670  // Figure out whether to eagerly instantiate the initializer.
5671  if (InstantiatingVarTemplate || InstantiatingVarTemplatePartialSpec) {
5672  // We're producing a template. Don't instantiate the initializer yet.
5673  } else if (NewVar->getType()->isUndeducedType()) {
5674  // We need the type to complete the declaration of the variable.
5675  InstantiateVariableInitializer(NewVar, OldVar, TemplateArgs);
5676  } else if (InstantiatingSpecFromTemplate ||
5677  (OldVar->isInline() && OldVar->isThisDeclarationADefinition() &&
5678  !NewVar->isThisDeclarationADefinition())) {
5679  // Delay instantiation of the initializer for variable template
5680  // specializations or inline static data members until a definition of the
5681  // variable is needed.
5682  } else {
5683  InstantiateVariableInitializer(NewVar, OldVar, TemplateArgs);
5684  }
5685 
5686  // Diagnose unused local variables with dependent types, where the diagnostic
5687  // will have been deferred.
5688  if (!NewVar->isInvalidDecl() &&
5689  NewVar->getDeclContext()->isFunctionOrMethod() &&
5690  OldVar->getType()->isDependentType())
5691  DiagnoseUnusedDecl(NewVar);
5692 }
5693 
5694 /// Instantiate the initializer of a variable.
5695 void Sema::InstantiateVariableInitializer(
5696  VarDecl *Var, VarDecl *OldVar,
5697  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs) {
5698  if (ASTMutationListener *L = getASTContext().getASTMutationListener())
5699  L->VariableDefinitionInstantiated(Var);
5700 
5701  // We propagate the 'inline' flag with the initializer, because it
5702  // would otherwise imply that the variable is a definition for a
5703  // non-static data member.
5704  if (OldVar->isInlineSpecified())
5705  Var->setInlineSpecified();
5706  else if (OldVar->isInline())
5707  Var->setImplicitlyInline();
5708 
5709  if (OldVar->getInit()) {
5710  EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Evaluated(
5711  *this, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::PotentiallyEvaluated, Var);
5712 
5713  // Instantiate the initializer.
5714  ExprResult Init;
5715 
5716  {
5717  ContextRAII SwitchContext(*this, Var->getDeclContext());
5718  Init = SubstInitializer(OldVar->getInit(), TemplateArgs,
5719  OldVar->getInitStyle() == VarDecl::CallInit);
5720  }
5721 
5722  if (!Init.isInvalid()) {
5723  Expr *InitExpr = Init.get();
5724 
5725  if (Var->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>() &&
5726  (!InitExpr ||
5727  !InitExpr->isConstantInitializer(getASTContext(), false))) {
5728  // Do not dynamically initialize dllimport variables.
5729  } else if (InitExpr) {
5730  bool DirectInit = OldVar->isDirectInit();
5731  AddInitializerToDecl(Var, InitExpr, DirectInit);
5732  } else
5733  ActOnUninitializedDecl(Var);
5734  } else {
5735  // FIXME: Not too happy about invalidating the declaration
5736  // because of a bogus initializer.
5737  Var->setInvalidDecl();
5738  }
5739  } else {
5740  // `inline` variables are a definition and declaration all in one; we won't
5741  // pick up an initializer from anywhere else.
5742  if (Var->isStaticDataMember() && !Var->isInline()) {
5743  if (!Var->isOutOfLine())
5744  return;
5745 
5746  // If the declaration inside the class had an initializer, don't add
5747  // another one to the out-of-line definition.
5748  if (OldVar->getFirstDecl()->hasInit())
5749  return;
5750  }
5751 
5752  // We'll add an initializer to a for-range declaration later.
5753  if (Var->isCXXForRangeDecl() || Var->isObjCForDecl())
5754  return;
5755 
5756  ActOnUninitializedDecl(Var);
5757  }
5758 
5759  if (getLangOpts().CUDA)
5760  checkAllowedCUDAInitializer(Var);
5761 }
5762 
5763 /// Instantiate the definition of the given variable from its
5764 /// template.
5765 ///
5766 /// \param PointOfInstantiation the point at which the instantiation was
5767 /// required. Note that this is not precisely a "point of instantiation"
5768 /// for the variable, but it's close.
5769 ///
5770 /// \param Var the already-instantiated declaration of a templated variable.
5771 ///
5772 /// \param Recursive if true, recursively instantiates any functions that
5773 /// are required by this instantiation.
5774 ///
5775 /// \param DefinitionRequired if true, then we are performing an explicit
5776 /// instantiation where a definition of the variable is required. Complain
5777 /// if there is no such definition.
5778 void Sema::InstantiateVariableDefinition(SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation,
5779  VarDecl *Var, bool Recursive,
5780  bool DefinitionRequired, bool AtEndOfTU) {
5781  if (Var->isInvalidDecl())
5782  return;
5783 
5784  // Never instantiate an explicitly-specialized entity.
5785  TemplateSpecializationKind TSK =
5786  Var->getTemplateSpecializationKindForInstantiation();
5787  if (TSK == TSK_ExplicitSpecialization)
5788  return;
5789 
5790  // Find the pattern and the arguments to substitute into it.
5791  VarDecl *PatternDecl = Var->getTemplateInstantiationPattern();
5792  assert(PatternDecl && "no pattern for templated variable");
5793  MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList TemplateArgs =
5794  getTemplateInstantiationArgs(Var);
5795 
5796  VarTemplateSpecializationDecl *VarSpec =
5797  dyn_cast<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(Var);
5798  if (VarSpec) {
5799  // If this is a static data member template, there might be an
5800  // uninstantiated initializer on the declaration. If so, instantiate
5801  // it now.
5802  //
5803  // FIXME: This largely duplicates what we would do below. The difference
5804  // is that along this path we may instantiate an initializer from an
5805  // in-class declaration of the template and instantiate the definition
5806  // from a separate out-of-class definition.
5807  if (PatternDecl->isStaticDataMember() &&
5808  (PatternDecl = PatternDecl->getFirstDecl())->hasInit() &&
5809  !Var->hasInit()) {
5810  // FIXME: Factor out the duplicated instantiation context setup/tear down
5811  // code here.
5812  InstantiatingTemplate Inst(*this, PointOfInstantiation, Var);
5813  if (Inst.isInvalid() || Inst.isAlreadyInstantiating())
5814  return;
5815  PrettyDeclStackTraceEntry CrashInfo(Context, Var, SourceLocation(),
5816  "instantiating variable initializer");
5817 
5818  // The instantiation is visible here, even if it was first declared in an
5819  // unimported module.
5820  Var->setVisibleDespiteOwningModule();
5821 
5822  // If we're performing recursive template instantiation, create our own
5823  // queue of pending implicit instantiations that we will instantiate
5824  // later, while we're still within our own instantiation context.
5825  GlobalEagerInstantiationScope GlobalInstantiations(*this,
5826  /*Enabled=*/Recursive);
5827  LocalInstantiationScope Local(*this);
5828  LocalEagerInstantiationScope LocalInstantiations(*this);
5829 
5830  // Enter the scope of this instantiation. We don't use
5831  // PushDeclContext because we don't have a scope.
5832  ContextRAII PreviousContext(*this, Var->getDeclContext());
5833  InstantiateVariableInitializer(Var, PatternDecl, TemplateArgs);
5834  PreviousContext.pop();
5835 
5836  // This variable may have local implicit instantiations that need to be
5837  // instantiated within this scope.
5838  LocalInstantiations.perform();
5839  Local.Exit();
5840  GlobalInstantiations.perform();
5841  }
5842  } else {
5843  assert(Var->isStaticDataMember() && PatternDecl->isStaticDataMember() &&
5844  "not a static data member?");
5845  }
5846 
5847  VarDecl *Def = PatternDecl->getDefinition(getASTContext());
5848 
5849  // If we don't have a definition of the variable template, we won't perform
5850  // any instantiation. Rather, we rely on the user to instantiate this
5851  // definition (or provide a specialization for it) in another translation
5852  // unit.
5853  if (!Def && !DefinitionRequired) {
5854  if (TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition) {
5855  PendingInstantiations.push_back(
5856  std::make_pair(Var, PointOfInstantiation));
5857  } else if (TSK == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation) {
5858  // Warn about missing definition at the end of translation unit.
5859  if (AtEndOfTU && !getDiagnostics().hasErrorOccurred() &&
5860  !getSourceManager().isInSystemHeader(PatternDecl->getBeginLoc())) {
5861  Diag(PointOfInstantiation, diag::warn_var_template_missing)
5862  << Var;
5863  Diag(PatternDecl->getLocation(), diag::note_forward_template_decl);
5864  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11)
5865  Diag(PointOfInstantiation, diag::note_inst_declaration_hint) << Var;
5866  }
5867  return;
5868  }
5869  }
5870 
5871  // FIXME: We need to track the instantiation stack in order to know which
5872  // definitions should be visible within this instantiation.
5873  // FIXME: Produce diagnostics when Var->getInstantiatedFromStaticDataMember().
5874  if (DiagnoseUninstantiableTemplate(PointOfInstantiation, Var,
5875  /*InstantiatedFromMember*/false,
5876  PatternDecl, Def, TSK,
5877  /*Complain*/DefinitionRequired))
5878  return;
5879 
5880  // C++11 [temp.explicit]p10:
5881  // Except for inline functions, const variables of literal types, variables
5882  // of reference types, [...] explicit instantiation declarations
5883  // have the effect of suppressing the implicit instantiation of the entity
5884  // to which they refer.
5885  //
5886  // FIXME: That's not exactly the same as "might be usable in constant
5887  // expressions", which only allows constexpr variables and const integral
5888  // types, not arbitrary const literal types.
5889  if (TSK == TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration &&
5890  !Var->mightBeUsableInConstantExpressions(getASTContext()))
5891  return;
5892 
5893  // Make sure to pass the instantiated variable to the consumer at the end.
5894  struct PassToConsumerRAII {
5895  Sema &SemaRef;
5896  ASTConsumer &Consumer;
5897  VarDecl *Var;
5898 
5899  PassToConsumerRAII(Sema &SemaRef, ASTConsumer &Consumer, VarDecl *Var)
5900  : SemaRef(SemaRef), Consumer(Consumer), Var(Var) {}
5901 
5902  ~PassToConsumerRAII() {
5903  // Do not explicitly emit non-const static data member definitions
5904  // on SYCL device.
5905  if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice || !Var->isStaticDataMember() ||
5906  Var->isConstexpr() ||
5907  (Var->getType().isConstQualified() && Var->getInit() &&
5908  Var->getInit()->isConstantInitializer(SemaRef.getASTContext(),
5909  false)))
5910  Consumer.HandleCXXStaticMemberVarInstantiation(Var);
5911  }
5912  } PassToConsumerRAII(*this, Consumer, Var);
5913 
5914  // If we already have a definition, we're done.
5915  if (VarDecl *Def = Var->getDefinition()) {
5916  // We may be explicitly instantiating something we've already implicitly
5917  // instantiated.
5918  Def->setTemplateSpecializationKind(Var->getTemplateSpecializationKind(),
5919  PointOfInstantiation);
5920  return;
5921  }
5922 
5923  InstantiatingTemplate Inst(*this, PointOfInstantiation, Var);
5924  if (Inst.isInvalid() || Inst.isAlreadyInstantiating())
5925  return;
5926  PrettyDeclStackTraceEntry CrashInfo(Context, Var, SourceLocation(),
5927  "instantiating variable definition");
5928 
5929  // If we're performing recursive template instantiation, create our own
5930  // queue of pending implicit instantiations that we will instantiate later,
5931  // while we're still within our own instantiation context.
5932  GlobalEagerInstantiationScope GlobalInstantiations(*this,
5933  /*Enabled=*/Recursive);
5934 
5935  // Enter the scope of this instantiation. We don't use
5936  // PushDeclContext because we don't have a scope.
5937  ContextRAII PreviousContext(*this, Var->getDeclContext());
5938  LocalInstantiationScope Local(*this);
5939 
5940  LocalEagerInstantiationScope LocalInstantiations(*this);
5941 
5942  VarDecl *OldVar = Var;
5943  if (Def->isStaticDataMember() && !Def->isOutOfLine()) {
5944  // We're instantiating an inline static data member whose definition was
5945  // provided inside the class.
5946  InstantiateVariableInitializer(Var, Def, TemplateArgs);
5947  } else if (!VarSpec) {
5948  Var = cast_or_null<VarDecl>(SubstDecl(Def, Var->getDeclContext(),
5949  TemplateArgs));
5950  } else if (Var->isStaticDataMember() &&
5951  Var->getLexicalDeclContext()->isRecord()) {
5952  // We need to instantiate the definition of a static data member template,
5953  // and all we have is the in-class declaration of it. Instantiate a separate
5954  // declaration of the definition.
5955  TemplateDeclInstantiator Instantiator(*this, Var->getDeclContext(),
5956  TemplateArgs);
5957  Var = cast_or_null<VarDecl>(Instantiator.VisitVarTemplateSpecializationDecl(
5958  VarSpec->getSpecializedTemplate(), Def, VarSpec->getTemplateArgsInfo(),
5959  VarSpec->getTemplateArgs().asArray(), VarSpec));
5960  if (Var) {
5961  llvm::PointerUnion<VarTemplateDecl *,
5962  VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *> PatternPtr =
5963  VarSpec->getSpecializedTemplateOrPartial();
5964  if (VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *Partial =
5965  PatternPtr.dyn_cast<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *>())
5966  cast<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(Var)->setInstantiationOf(
5967  Partial, &VarSpec->getTemplateInstantiationArgs());
5968 
5969  // Attach the initializer.
5970  InstantiateVariableInitializer(Var, Def, TemplateArgs);
5971  }
5972  } else
5973  // Complete the existing variable's definition with an appropriately
5974  // substituted type and initializer.
5975  Var = CompleteVarTemplateSpecializationDecl(VarSpec, Def, TemplateArgs);
5976 
5977  PreviousContext.pop();
5978 
5979  if (Var) {
5980  PassToConsumerRAII.Var = Var;
5981  Var->setTemplateSpecializationKind(OldVar->getTemplateSpecializationKind(),
5982  OldVar->getPointOfInstantiation());
5983  }
5984 
5985  // This variable may have local implicit instantiations that need to be
5986  // instantiated within this scope.
5987  LocalInstantiations.perform();
5988  Local.Exit();
5989  GlobalInstantiations.perform();
5990 }
5991 
5992 void
5993 Sema::InstantiateMemInitializers(CXXConstructorDecl *New,
5994  const CXXConstructorDecl *Tmpl,
5995  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs) {
5996 
5997  SmallVector<CXXCtorInitializer*, 4> NewInits;
5998  bool AnyErrors = Tmpl->isInvalidDecl();
5999 
6000  // Instantiate all the initializers.
6001  for (const auto *Init : Tmpl->inits()) {
6002  // Only instantiate written initializers, let Sema re-construct implicit
6003  // ones.
6004  if (!Init->isWritten())
6005  continue;
6006 
6007  SourceLocation EllipsisLoc;
6008 
6009  if (Init->isPackExpansion()) {
6010  // This is a pack expansion. We should expand it now.
6011  TypeLoc BaseTL = Init->getTypeSourceInfo()->getTypeLoc();
6012  SmallVector<UnexpandedParameterPack, 4> Unexpanded;
6013  collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(BaseTL, Unexpanded);
6014  collectUnexpandedParameterPacks(Init->getInit(), Unexpanded);
6015  bool ShouldExpand = false;
6016  bool RetainExpansion = false;
6017  Optional<unsigned> NumExpansions;
6018  if (CheckParameterPacksForExpansion(Init->getEllipsisLoc(),
6019  BaseTL.getSourceRange(),
6020  Unexpanded,
6021  TemplateArgs, ShouldExpand,
6022  RetainExpansion,
6023  NumExpansions)) {
6024  AnyErrors = true;
6025  New->setInvalidDecl();
6026  continue;
6027  }
6028  assert(ShouldExpand && "Partial instantiation of base initializer?");
6029 
6030  // Loop over all of the arguments in the argument pack(s),
6031  for (unsigned I = 0; I != *NumExpansions; ++I) {
6032  Sema::ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndexRAII SubstIndex(*this, I);
6033 
6034  // Instantiate the initializer.
6035  ExprResult TempInit = SubstInitializer(Init->getInit(), TemplateArgs,
6036  /*CXXDirectInit=*/true);
6037  if (TempInit.isInvalid()) {
6038  AnyErrors = true;
6039  break;
6040  }
6041 
6042  // Instantiate the base type.
6043  TypeSourceInfo *BaseTInfo = SubstType(Init->getTypeSourceInfo(),
6044  TemplateArgs,
6045  Init->getSourceLocation(),
6046  New->getDeclName());
6047  if (!BaseTInfo) {
6048  AnyErrors = true;
6049  break;
6050  }
6051 
6052  // Build the initializer.
6053  MemInitResult NewInit = BuildBaseInitializer(BaseTInfo->getType(),
6054  BaseTInfo, TempInit.get(),
6055  New->getParent(),
6056  SourceLocation());
6057  if (NewInit.isInvalid()) {
6058  AnyErrors = true;
6059  break;
6060  }
6061 
6062  NewInits.push_back(NewInit.get());
6063  }
6064 
6065  continue;
6066  }
6067 
6068  // Instantiate the initializer.
6069  ExprResult TempInit = SubstInitializer(Init->getInit(), TemplateArgs,
6070  /*CXXDirectInit=*/true);
6071  if (TempInit.isInvalid()) {
6072  AnyErrors = true;
6073  continue;
6074  }
6075 
6076  MemInitResult NewInit;
6077  if (Init->isDelegatingInitializer() || Init->isBaseInitializer()) {
6078  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = SubstType(Init->getTypeSourceInfo(),
6079  TemplateArgs,
6080  Init->getSourceLocation(),
6081  New->getDeclName());
6082  if (!TInfo) {
6083  AnyErrors = true;
6084  New->setInvalidDecl();
6085  continue;
6086  }
6087 
6088  if (Init->isBaseInitializer())
6089  NewInit = BuildBaseInitializer(TInfo->getType(), TInfo, TempInit.get(),
6090  New->getParent(), EllipsisLoc);
6091  else
6092  NewInit = BuildDelegatingInitializer(TInfo, TempInit.get(),
6093  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(CurContext->getParent()));
6094  } else if (Init->isMemberInitializer()) {
6095  FieldDecl *Member = cast_or_null<FieldDecl>(FindInstantiatedDecl(
6096  Init->getMemberLocation(),
6097  Init->getMember(),
6098  TemplateArgs));
6099  if (!Member) {
6100  AnyErrors = true;
6101  New->setInvalidDecl();
6102  continue;
6103  }
6104 
6105  NewInit = BuildMemberInitializer(Member, TempInit.get(),
6106  Init->getSourceLocation());
6107  } else if (Init->isIndirectMemberInitializer()) {
6108  IndirectFieldDecl *IndirectMember =
6109  cast_or_null<IndirectFieldDecl>(FindInstantiatedDecl(
6110  Init->getMemberLocation(),
6111  Init->getIndirectMember(), TemplateArgs));
6112 
6113  if (!IndirectMember) {
6114  AnyErrors = true;
6115  New->setInvalidDecl();
6116  continue;
6117  }
6118 
6119  NewInit = BuildMemberInitializer(IndirectMember, TempInit.get(),
6120  Init->getSourceLocation());
6121  }
6122 
6123  if (NewInit.isInvalid()) {
6124  AnyErrors = true;
6125  New->setInvalidDecl();
6126  } else {
6127  NewInits.push_back(NewInit.get());
6128  }
6129  }
6130 
6131  // Assign all the initializers to the new constructor.
6132  ActOnMemInitializers(New,
6133  /*FIXME: ColonLoc */
6134  SourceLocation(),
6135  NewInits,
6136  AnyErrors);
6137 }

6144

6146  Instance = Instance->getCanonicalDecl();
6147  if (Pattern == Instance) return true;
6148  Instance = Instance->getInstantiatedFromMemberTemplate();
6149  } while (Instance);
6150 
6151  return false;
6152 }

6226  Pattern);
