6233 
6234 template<typename T>
6235 static bool isInstantiationOfUnresolvedUsingDecl(T *Pattern, Decl *Other,
6236  ASTContext &Ctx) {
6237  // An unresolved using declaration can instantiate to an unresolved using
6238  // declaration, or to a using declaration or a using declaration pack.
6239  //
6240  // Multiple declarations can claim to be instantiated from an unresolved
6241  // using declaration if it's a pack expansion. We want the UsingPackDecl
6242  // in that case, not the individual UsingDecls within the pack.
6243  bool OtherIsPackExpansion;
6244  NamedDecl *OtherFrom;
6245  if (auto *OtherUUD = dyn_cast<T>(Other)) {
6246  OtherIsPackExpansion = OtherUUD->isPackExpansion();
6247  OtherFrom = Ctx.getInstantiatedFromUsingDecl(OtherUUD);
6248  } else if (auto *OtherUPD = dyn_cast<UsingPackDecl>(Other)) {
6249  OtherIsPackExpansion = true;
6250  OtherFrom = OtherUPD->getInstantiatedFromUsingDecl();
6251  } else if (auto *OtherUD = dyn_cast<UsingDecl>(Other)) {
6252  OtherIsPackExpansion = false;
6253  OtherFrom = Ctx.getInstantiatedFromUsingDecl(OtherUD);
6254  } else {
6255  return false;
6256  }
6257  return Pattern->isPackExpansion() == OtherIsPackExpansion &&
6258  declaresSameEntity(OtherFrom, Pattern);
6259 }
6260 
6261 static bool isInstantiationOfStaticDataMember(VarDecl *Pattern,
6262  VarDecl *Instance) {
6263  assert(Instance->isStaticDataMember());
6264 
6265  Pattern = Pattern->getCanonicalDecl();
6266 
6267  do {
6268  Instance = Instance->getCanonicalDecl();
6269  if (Pattern == Instance) return true;
6270  Instance = Instance->getInstantiatedFromStaticDataMember();
6271  } while (Instance);
6272 
6273  return false;
6274 }
6275 
6276 // Other is the prospective instantiation
6277 // D is the prospective pattern
6278 static bool isInstantiationOf(ASTContext &Ctx, NamedDecl *D, Decl *Other) {
6279  if (auto *UUD = dyn_cast<UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl>(D))
6280  return isInstantiationOfUnresolvedUsingDecl(UUD, Other, Ctx);
6281 
6282  if (auto *UUD = dyn_cast<UnresolvedUsingValueDecl>(D))
6283  return isInstantiationOfUnresolvedUsingDecl(UUD, Other, Ctx);
6284 
6285  if (D->getKind() != Other->getKind())
6286  return false;
6287 
6288  if (auto *Record = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(Other))
6289  return isInstantiationOf(cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D), Record);
6290 
6291  if (auto *Function = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Other))
6292  return isInstantiationOf(cast<FunctionDecl>(D), Function);
6293 
6294  if (auto *Enum = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(Other))
6295  return isInstantiationOf(cast<EnumDecl>(D), Enum);
6296 
6297  if (auto *Var = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(Other))
6298  if (Var->isStaticDataMember())
6299  return isInstantiationOfStaticDataMember(cast<VarDecl>(D), Var);
6300 
6301  if (auto *Temp = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateDecl>(Other))
6302  return isInstantiationOf(cast<ClassTemplateDecl>(D), Temp);
6303 
6304  if (auto *Temp = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(Other))
6305  return isInstantiationOf(cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D), Temp);
6306 
6307  if (auto *PartialSpec =
6308  dyn_cast<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(Other))
6309  return isInstantiationOf(cast<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(D),
6310  PartialSpec);
6311 
6312  if (auto *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(Other)) {
6313  if (!Field->getDeclName()) {
6314  // This is an unnamed field.
6315  return declaresSameEntity(Ctx.getInstantiatedFromUnnamedFieldDecl(Field),
6316  cast<FieldDecl>(D));
6317  }
6318  }
6319 
6320  if (auto *Using = dyn_cast<UsingDecl>(Other))
6321  return isInstantiationOf(cast<UsingDecl>(D), Using, Ctx);
6322 
6323  if (auto *Shadow = dyn_cast<UsingShadowDecl>(Other))
6324  return isInstantiationOf(cast<UsingShadowDecl>(D), Shadow, Ctx);
6325 
6326  return D->getDeclName() &&
6327  D->getDeclName() == cast<NamedDecl>(Other)->getDeclName();
6328 }
6329 
6330 template<typename ForwardIterator>
6331 static NamedDecl *findInstantiationOf(ASTContext &Ctx,
6332  NamedDecl *D,
6333  ForwardIterator first,
6334  ForwardIterator last) {
6335  for (; first != last; ++first)
6336  if (isInstantiationOf(Ctx, D, *first))
6337  return cast<NamedDecl>(*first);
6338 
6339  return nullptr;
6340 }
6341 
6342 /// Finds the instantiation of the given declaration context
6343 /// within the current instantiation.
6344 ///
6345 /// \returns NULL if there was an error
6346 DeclContext *Sema::FindInstantiatedContext(SourceLocation Loc, DeclContext* DC,
6347  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs) {
6348  if (NamedDecl *D = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(DC)) {
6349  Decl* ID = FindInstantiatedDecl(Loc, D, TemplateArgs, true);
6350  return cast_or_null<DeclContext>(ID);
6351  } else return DC;
6352 }
6353 
6354 /// Determine whether the given context is dependent on template parameters at
6355 /// level \p Level or below.
6356 ///
6357 /// Sometimes we only substitute an inner set of template arguments and leave
6358 /// the outer templates alone. In such cases, contexts dependent only on the
6359 /// outer levels are not effectively dependent.
6360 static bool isDependentContextAtLevel(DeclContext *DC, unsigned Level) {
6361  if (!DC->isDependentContext())
6362  return false;
6363  if (!Level)
6364  return true;
6365  return cast<Decl>(DC)->getTemplateDepth() > Level;
6366 }
6367 
6368 /// Find the instantiation of the given declaration within the
6369 /// current instantiation.
6370 ///
6371 /// This routine is intended to be used when \p D is a declaration
6372 /// referenced from within a template, that needs to mapped into the
6373 /// corresponding declaration within an instantiation. For example,
6374 /// given:
6375 ///
6376 /// \code
6377 /// template<typename T>
6378 /// struct X {
6379 /// enum Kind {
6380 /// KnownValue = sizeof(T)
6381 /// };
6382 ///
6383 /// bool getKind() const { return KnownValue; }
6384 /// };
6385 ///
6386 /// template struct X<int>;
6387 /// \endcode
6388 ///
6389 /// In the instantiation of X<int>::getKind(), we need to map the \p
6390 /// EnumConstantDecl for \p KnownValue (which refers to
6391 /// X<T>::<Kind>::KnownValue) to its instantiation (X<int>::<Kind>::KnownValue).
6392 /// \p FindInstantiatedDecl performs this mapping from within the instantiation
6393 /// of X<int>.
6394 NamedDecl *Sema::FindInstantiatedDecl(SourceLocation Loc, NamedDecl *D,
6395  const MultiLevelTemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs,
6396  bool FindingInstantiatedContext) {
6397  DeclContext *ParentDC = D->getDeclContext();
6398  // Determine whether our parent context depends on any of the template
6399  // arguments we're currently substituting.
6400  bool ParentDependsOnArgs = isDependentContextAtLevel(
6401  ParentDC, TemplateArgs.getNumRetainedOuterLevels());
6402  // FIXME: Parameters of pointer to functions (y below) that are themselves
6403  // parameters (p below) can have their ParentDC set to the translation-unit
6404  // - thus we can not consistently check if the ParentDC of such a parameter
6405  // is Dependent or/and a FunctionOrMethod.
6406  // For e.g. this code, during Template argument deduction tries to
6407  // find an instantiated decl for (T y) when the ParentDC for y is
6408  // the translation unit.
6409  // e.g. template <class T> void Foo(auto (*p)(T y) -> decltype(y())) {}
6410  // float baz(float(*)()) { return 0.0; }
6411  // Foo(baz);
6412  // The better fix here is perhaps to ensure that a ParmVarDecl, by the time
6413  // it gets here, always has a FunctionOrMethod as its ParentDC??
6414  // For now:
6415  // - as long as we have a ParmVarDecl whose parent is non-dependent and
6416  // whose type is not instantiation dependent, do nothing to the decl
6417  // - otherwise find its instantiated decl.
6418  if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(D) && !ParentDependsOnArgs &&
6419  !cast<ParmVarDecl>(D)->getType()->isInstantiationDependentType())
6420  return D;
6421  if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(D) || isa<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(D) ||
6422  isa<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(D) || isa<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(D) ||
6423  (ParentDependsOnArgs && (ParentDC->isFunctionOrMethod() ||
6424  isa<OMPDeclareReductionDecl>(ParentDC) ||
6425  isa<OMPDeclareMapperDecl>(ParentDC))) ||
6426  (isa<CXXRecordDecl>(D) && cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)->isLambda() &&
6427  cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)->getTemplateDepth() >
6428  TemplateArgs.getNumRetainedOuterLevels())) {
6429  // D is a local of some kind. Look into the map of local
6430  // declarations to their instantiations.
6431  if (CurrentInstantiationScope) {
6432  if (auto Found = CurrentInstantiationScope->findInstantiationOf(D)) {
6433  if (Decl *FD = Found->dyn_cast<Decl *>())
6434  return cast<NamedDecl>(FD);
6435 
6436  int PackIdx = ArgumentPackSubstitutionIndex;
6437  assert(PackIdx != -1 &&
6438  "found declaration pack but not pack expanding");
6439  typedef LocalInstantiationScope::DeclArgumentPack DeclArgumentPack;
6440  return cast<NamedDecl>((*Found->get<DeclArgumentPack *>())[PackIdx]);
6441  }
6442  }
6443 
6444  // If we're performing a partial substitution during template argument
6445  // deduction, we may not have values for template parameters yet. They
6446  // just map to themselves.
6447  if (isa<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(D) || isa<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(D) ||
6448  isa<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(D))
6449  return D;
6450 
6451  if (D->isInvalidDecl())
6452  return nullptr;
6453 
6454  // Normally this function only searches for already instantiated declaration
6455  // however we have to make an exclusion for local types used before
6456  // definition as in the code:
6457  //
6458  // template<typename T> void f1() {
6459  // void g1(struct x1);
6460  // struct x1 {};
6461  // }
6462  //
6463  // In this case instantiation of the type of 'g1' requires definition of
6464  // 'x1', which is defined later. Error recovery may produce an enum used
6465  // before definition. In these cases we need to instantiate relevant
6466  // declarations here.
6467  bool NeedInstantiate = false;
6468  if (CXXRecordDecl *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D))
6469  NeedInstantiate = RD->isLocalClass();
6470  else if (isa<TypedefNameDecl>(D) &&
6471  isa<CXXDeductionGuideDecl>(D->getDeclContext()))
6472  NeedInstantiate = true;
6473  else
6474  NeedInstantiate = isa<EnumDecl>(D);
6475  if (NeedInstantiate) {
6476  Decl *Inst = SubstDecl(D, CurContext, TemplateArgs);
6477  CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(D, Inst);
6478  return cast<TypeDecl>(Inst);
6479  }
6480 
6481  // If we didn't find the decl, then we must have a label decl that hasn't
6482  // been found yet. Lazily instantiate it and return it now.
6483  assert(isa<LabelDecl>(D));
6484 
6485  Decl *Inst = SubstDecl(D, CurContext, TemplateArgs);
6486  assert(Inst && "Failed to instantiate label??");
6487 
6488  CurrentInstantiationScope->InstantiatedLocal(D, Inst);
6489  return cast<LabelDecl>(Inst);
6490  }
6491 
6492  if (CXXRecordDecl *Record = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) {
6493  if (!Record->isDependentContext())
6494  return D;
6495 
6496  // Determine whether this record is the "templated" declaration describing
6497  // a class template or class template partial specialization.
6498  ClassTemplateDecl *ClassTemplate = Record->getDescribedClassTemplate();
6499  if (ClassTemplate)
6500  ClassTemplate = ClassTemplate->getCanonicalDecl();
6501  else if (ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *PartialSpec
6502  = dyn_cast<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(Record))
6503  ClassTemplate = PartialSpec->getSpecializedTemplate()->getCanonicalDecl();
6504 
6505  // Walk the current context to find either the record or an instantiation of
6506  // it.
6507  DeclContext *DC = CurContext;
6508  while (!DC->isFileContext()) {
6509  // If we're performing substitution while we're inside the template
6510  // definition, we'll find our own context. We're done.
6511  if (DC->Equals(Record))
6512  return Record;
6513 
6514  if (CXXRecordDecl *InstRecord = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(DC)) {
6515  // Check whether we're in the process of instantiating a class template
6516  // specialization of the template we're mapping.
6517  if (ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *InstSpec
6518  = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(InstRecord)){
6519  ClassTemplateDecl *SpecTemplate = InstSpec->getSpecializedTemplate();
6520  if (ClassTemplate && isInstantiationOf(ClassTemplate, SpecTemplate))
6521  return InstRecord;
6522  }
6523 
6524  // Check whether we're in the process of instantiating a member class.
6525  if (isInstantiationOf(Record, InstRecord))
6526  return InstRecord;
6527  }
6528 
6529  // Move to the outer template scope.
6530  if (FunctionDecl *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(DC)) {
6531  if (FD->getFriendObjectKind() && FD->getDeclContext()->isFileContext()){
6532  DC = FD->getLexicalDeclContext();
6533  continue;
6534  }
6535  // An implicit deduction guide acts as if it's within the class template
6536  // specialization described by its name and first N template params.
6537  auto *Guide = dyn_cast<CXXDeductionGuideDecl>(FD);
6538  if (Guide && Guide->isImplicit()) {
6539  TemplateDecl *TD = Guide->getDeducedTemplate();
6540  // Convert the arguments to an "as-written" list.
6541  TemplateArgumentListInfo Args(Loc, Loc);
6542  for (TemplateArgument Arg : TemplateArgs.getInnermost().take_front(
6543  TD->getTemplateParameters()->size())) {
6544  ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Unpacked(Arg);
6545  if (Arg.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Pack)
6546  Unpacked = Arg.pack_elements();
6547  for (TemplateArgument UnpackedArg : Unpacked)
6548  Args.addArgument(
6549  getTrivialTemplateArgumentLoc(UnpackedArg, QualType(), Loc));
6550  }
6551  QualType T = CheckTemplateIdType(TemplateName(TD), Loc, Args);
6552  if (T.isNull())
6553  return nullptr;
6554  auto *SubstRecord = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
6555  assert(SubstRecord && "class template id not a class type?");
6556  // Check that this template-id names the primary template and not a
6557  // partial or explicit specialization. (In the latter cases, it's
6558  // meaningless to attempt to find an instantiation of D within the
6559  // specialization.)
6560  // FIXME: The standard doesn't say what should happen here.
6561  if (FindingInstantiatedContext &&
6562  usesPartialOrExplicitSpecialization(
6563  Loc, cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(SubstRecord))) {
6564  Diag(Loc, diag::err_specialization_not_primary_template)
6565  << T << (SubstRecord->getTemplateSpecializationKind() ==
6566  TSK_ExplicitSpecialization);
6567  return nullptr;
6568  }
6569  DC = SubstRecord;
6570  continue;
6571  }
6572  }
6573 
6574  DC = DC->getParent();
6575  }
6576 
6577  // Fall through to deal with other dependent record types (e.g.,
6578  // anonymous unions in class templates).
6579  }
6580 
6581  if (!ParentDependsOnArgs)
6582  return D;
6583 
6584  ParentDC = FindInstantiatedContext(Loc, ParentDC, TemplateArgs);
6585  if (!ParentDC)
6586  return nullptr;
6587 
6588  if (ParentDC != D->getDeclContext()) {
6589  // We performed some kind of instantiation in the parent context,
6590  // so now we need to look into the instantiated parent context to
6591  // find the instantiation of the declaration D.
6592 
6593  // If our context used to be dependent, we may need to instantiate
6594  // it before performing lookup into that context.
6595  bool IsBeingInstantiated = false;
6596  if (CXXRecordDecl *Spec = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(ParentDC)) {
6597  if (!Spec->isDependentContext()) {
6598  QualType T = Context.getTypeDeclType(Spec);
6599  const RecordType *Tag = T->getAs<RecordType>();
6600  assert(Tag && "type of non-dependent record is not a RecordType");
6601  if (Tag->isBeingDefined())
6602  IsBeingInstantiated = true;
6603  if (!Tag->isBeingDefined() &&
6604  RequireCompleteType(Loc, T, diag::err_incomplete_type))
6605  return nullptr;
6606 
6607  ParentDC = Tag->getDecl();
6608  }
6609  }
6610 
6611  NamedDecl *Result = nullptr;
6612  // FIXME: If the name is a dependent name, this lookup won't necessarily
6613  // find it. Does that ever matter?
6614  if (auto Name = D->getDeclName()) {
6615  DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo(Name, D->getLocation());
6616  DeclarationNameInfo NewNameInfo =
6617  SubstDeclarationNameInfo(NameInfo, TemplateArgs);
6618  Name = NewNameInfo.getName();
6619  if (!Name)
6620  return nullptr;
6621  DeclContext::lookup_result Found = ParentDC->lookup(Name);
6622 
6623  Result = findInstantiationOf(Context, D, Found.begin(), Found.end());
6624  } else {
6625  // Since we don't have a name for the entity we're looking for,
6626  // our only option is to walk through all of the declarations to
6627  // find that name. This will occur in a few cases:
6628  //
6629  // - anonymous struct/union within a template
6630  // - unnamed class/struct/union/enum within a template
6631  //
6632  // FIXME: Find a better way to find these instantiations!
6633  Result = findInstantiationOf(Context, D,
6634  ParentDC->decls_begin(),
6635  ParentDC->decls_end());
6636  }
6637 
6638  if (!Result) {
6639  if (isa<UsingShadowDecl>(D)) {
6640  // UsingShadowDecls can instantiate to nothing because of using hiding.
6641  } else if (hasUncompilableErrorOccurred()) {
6642  // We've already complained about some ill-formed code, so most likely
6643  // this declaration failed to instantiate. There's no point in
6644  // complaining further, since this is normal in invalid code.
6645  // FIXME: Use more fine-grained 'invalid' tracking for this.
6646  } else if (IsBeingInstantiated) {
6647  // The class in which this member exists is currently being
6648  // instantiated, and we haven't gotten around to instantiating this
6649  // member yet. This can happen when the code uses forward declarations
6650  // of member classes, and introduces ordering dependencies via
6651  // template instantiation.
6652  Diag(Loc, diag::err_member_not_yet_instantiated)
6653  << D->getDeclName()
6654  << Context.getTypeDeclType(cast<CXXRecordDecl>(ParentDC));
6655  Diag(D->getLocation(), diag::note_non_instantiated_member_here);
6656  } else if (EnumConstantDecl *ED = dyn_cast<EnumConstantDecl>(D)) {
6657  // This enumeration constant was found when the template was defined,
6658  // but can't be found in the instantiation. This can happen if an
6659  // unscoped enumeration member is explicitly specialized.
6660  EnumDecl *Enum = cast<EnumDecl>(ED->getLexicalDeclContext());
6661  EnumDecl *Spec = cast<EnumDecl>(FindInstantiatedDecl(Loc, Enum,
6662  TemplateArgs));
6663  assert(Spec->getTemplateSpecializationKind() ==
6664  TSK_ExplicitSpecialization);
6665  Diag(Loc, diag::err_enumerator_does_not_exist)
6666  << D->getDeclName()
6667  << Context.getTypeDeclType(cast<TypeDecl>(Spec->getDeclContext()));
6668  Diag(Spec->getLocation(), diag::note_enum_specialized_here)
6669  << Context.getTypeDeclType(Spec);
6670  } else {
6671  // We should have found something, but didn't.
6672  llvm_unreachable("Unable to find instantiation of declaration!");
6673  }
6674  }
6675 
6676  D = Result;
6677  }
6678 
6679  return D;
6680 }
6681 
6682 static void processFunctionInstantiation(Sema &S,
6683  SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation,
6684  FunctionDecl *FD,
6685  bool DefinitionRequired,
6686  MangleContext &MC) {
6687  S.InstantiateFunctionDefinition(/*FIXME:*/ PointOfInstantiation, FD, true,
6688  DefinitionRequired, true);
6689  if (!FD->isDefined())
6690  return;
6691  if (S.LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice && FD->hasAttr<SYCLKernelAttr>())
6692  S.ConstructOpenCLKernel(FD, MC);
6693  FD->setInstantiationIsPending(false);
6694 }
6695 
6696 /// Performs template instantiation for all implicit template
6697 /// instantiations we have seen until this point.
6698 void Sema::PerformPendingInstantiations(bool LocalOnly) {
6699  std::unique_ptr<MangleContext> MangleCtx(
6700  getASTContext().createMangleContext());
6701  std::deque<PendingImplicitInstantiation> delayedPCHInstantiations;
6702  while (!PendingLocalImplicitInstantiations.empty() ||
6703  (!LocalOnly && !PendingInstantiations.empty())) {
6704  PendingImplicitInstantiation Inst;
6705 
6706  if (PendingLocalImplicitInstantiations.empty()) {
6707  Inst = PendingInstantiations.front();
6708  PendingInstantiations.pop_front();
6709  } else {
6710  Inst = PendingLocalImplicitInstantiations.front();
6711  PendingLocalImplicitInstantiations.pop_front();
6712  }
6713 
6714  // Instantiate function definitions
6715  if (FunctionDecl *Function = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(Inst.first)) {
6716  bool DefinitionRequired = Function->getTemplateSpecializationKind() ==
6717  TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition;
6718  if (Function->isMultiVersion())
6719  getASTContext().forEachMultiversionedFunctionVersion(
6720  Function, [this, Inst, DefinitionRequired,
6721  MangleCtx = move(MangleCtx)](FunctionDecl *CurFD) {
6722  processFunctionInstantiation(*this, Inst.second, CurFD,
6723  DefinitionRequired, *MangleCtx);
6724  });
6725  else
6726  processFunctionInstantiation(*this, Inst.second, Function,
6727  DefinitionRequired, *MangleCtx);
6728  // Definition of a PCH-ed template declaration may be available only in the TU.
6729  if (!LocalOnly && LangOpts.PCHInstantiateTemplates &&
6730  TUKind == TU_Prefix && Function->instantiationIsPending())
6731  delayedPCHInstantiations.push_back(Inst);
6732  continue;
6733  }
6734 
6735  // Instantiate variable definitions
6736  VarDecl *Var = cast<VarDecl>(Inst.first);
6737 
6738  assert((Var->isStaticDataMember() ||
6739  isa<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(Var)) &&
6740  "Not a static data member, nor a variable template"
6741  " specialization?");
6742 
6743  // Don't try to instantiate declarations if the most recent redeclaration
6744  // is invalid.
6745  if (Var->getMostRecentDecl()->isInvalidDecl())
6746  continue;
6747 
6748  // Check if the most recent declaration has changed the specialization kind
6749  // and removed the need for implicit instantiation.
6750  switch (Var->getMostRecentDecl()
6751  ->getTemplateSpecializationKindForInstantiation()) {
6752  case TSK_Undeclared:
6753  llvm_unreachable("Cannot instantitiate an undeclared specialization.");
6754  case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration:
6755  case TSK_ExplicitSpecialization:
6756  continue; // No longer need to instantiate this type.
6757  case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition:
6758  // We only need an instantiation if the pending instantiation *is* the
6759  // explicit instantiation.
6760  if (Var != Var->getMostRecentDecl())
6761  continue;
6762  break;
6763  case TSK_ImplicitInstantiation:
6764  break;
6765  }
6766 
6767  PrettyDeclStackTraceEntry CrashInfo(Context, Var, SourceLocation(),
6768  "instantiating variable definition");
6769  bool DefinitionRequired = Var->getTemplateSpecializationKind() ==
6770  TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition;
6771 
6772  // Instantiate static data member definitions or variable template
6773  // specializations.
6774  InstantiateVariableDefinition(/*FIXME:*/ Inst.second, Var, true,
6775  DefinitionRequired, true);
6776  }
6777 
6778  if (!LocalOnly && LangOpts.PCHInstantiateTemplates)
6779  PendingInstantiations.swap(delayedPCHInstantiations);
6780 }

6784  for (auto DD : Pattern->ddiags()) {
6785  switch (DD->getKind()) {

6788  break;
6789  }
6790  }
6791 }
